 6095: // fn(a, b, c, null, undefined, '') => fn(a,b,c)
 6096: function genNullableArgs(args) {
 6097:   let i = args.length
 6098:   while (i--) {
 6099:     if (args[i] != null) break
 6100:   }
 6101:   return args.slice(0, i + 1).map(arg => arg || `null`)
 6102: }
 6103: 
 6104: //  key  { [a + b + c]: value }
 6105: function genExpressionAsPropertyKey(node, context) {
 6106:   const { push } = context
 6107:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION) {
 6108:     push(`[`)
 6109:     genCompoundExpression(node, context)
 6110:     push(`]`)
 6111:   } else if (node.isStatic) {
 6112:     // only quote keys if necessary
 6113:     const text = isSimpleIdentifier(node.content)
 6114:       ? node.content
 6115:       : JSON.stringify(node.content)
 6116:     push(text, node)
 6117:   } else {
 6118:     push(`[${node.content}]`, node)
 6119:   }
 6120: }
 6121: function createCodegenContext(
 6122:   ast,
 6123:   {
 6124:     mode = 'function',
 6125:     prefixIdentifiers = mode === 'module',
 6126:     sourceMap = false,
 6127:     filename = `template.vue.html`,
 6128:     scopeId = null,
 6129:     optimizeImports = false,
 6130:     runtimeGlobalName = `Vue`,
 6131:     runtimeModuleName = `vue`,
 6132:     ssrRuntimeModuleName = 'vue/server-renderer',
 6133:     ssr = false,
 6134:     isTS = false,
 6135:     inSSR = false
 6136:   }
 6137: ) {
 6138:   const context = {
 6139:     mode,
 6140:     prefixIdentifiers,
 6141:     sourceMap,
 6142:     filename,
 6143:     scopeId,
 6144:     optimizeImports,
 6145:     runtimeGlobalName,
 6146:     runtimeModuleName,
 6147:     ssrRuntimeModuleName,
 6148:     ssr,
 6149:     isTS,
 6150:     inSSR,
 6151:     source: ast.loc.source,
 6152:     code: ``,
 6153:     column: 1,
 6154:     line: 1,
 6155:     offset: 0,
 6156:     indentLevel: 0,
 6157:     pure: false,
 6158:     map: undefined,
 6159:     helper(key) {
 6160:       return `_${helperNameMap[key]}`
 6161:     },
 6162:     push(code, node) {
 6163:       context.code += code
 6164:       if (!__BROWSER__ && context.map) {
 6165:         if (node) {
 6166:           let name
 6167:           if (node.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION && !node.isStatic) {
 6168:             const content = node.content.replace(/^_ctx\./, '')
 6169:             if (content !== node.content && isSimpleIdentifier(content)) {
 6170:               name = content
 6171:             }
 6172:           }
 6173:           addMapping(node.loc.start, name)
 6174:         }
 6175:         advancePositionWithMutation(context, code)
 6176:         if (node && node.loc !== locStub) {
 6177:           addMapping(node.loc.end)
 6178:         }
 6179:       }
 6180:     },
 6181:     indent() {
 6182:       newline(++context.indentLevel)
 6183:     },
 6184:     deindent(withoutNewLine = false) {
 6185:       if (withoutNewLine) {
 6186:         --context.indentLevel
 6187:       } else {
 6188:         newline(--context.indentLevel)
 6189:       }
 6190:     },
 6191:     newline() {
 6192:       newline(context.indentLevel)
 6193:     }
 6194:   }
 6195: 
 6196:   function newline(n) {
 6197:     context.push('\n' + `  `.repeat(n))
 6198:   }
 6199: 
 6200:   function addMapping(loc, name) {
 6201:     context.map.addMapping({
 6202:       name,
 6203:       source: context.filename,
 6204:       original: {
 6205:         line: loc.line,
 6206:         column: loc.column - 1 // source-map column is 0 based
 6207:       },
 6208:       generated: {
 6209:         line: context.line,
 6210:         column: context.column - 1
 6211:       }
 6212:     })
 6213:   }
 6214: 
 6215:   return context
 6216: }
 6217: 
 6218: function genModulePreamble(ast, context, genScopeId, inline) {
 6219:   const {
 6220:     push,
 6221:     newline,
 6222:     optimizeImports,
 6223:     runtimeModuleName,
 6224:     ssrRuntimeModuleName
 6225:   } = context
 6226: 
 6227:   if (genScopeId && ast.hoists.length) {
 6228:     ast.helpers.push(PUSH_SCOPE_ID, POP_SCOPE_ID)
 6229:   }
 6230: 
 6231:   // generate import statements for helpers
 6232:   if (ast.helpers.length) {
 6233:     if (optimizeImports) {
 6234:       // when bundled with webpack with code-split, calling an import binding
 6235:       // as a function leads to it being wrapped with `Object(a.b)` or `(0,a.b)`,
 6236:       // incurring both payload size increase and potential perf overhead.
 6237:       // therefore we assign the imports to variables (which is a constant ~50b
 6238:       // cost per-component instead of scaling with template size)
 6239:       push(
 6240:         `import { ${ast.helpers
 6241:           .map(s => helperNameMap[s])
 6242:           .join(', ')} } from ${JSON.stringify(runtimeModuleName)}\n`
 6243:       )
 6244:       push(
 6245:         `\n// Binding optimization for webpack code-split\nconst ${ast.helpers
 6246:           .map(s => `_${helperNameMap[s]} = ${helperNameMap[s]}`)
 6247:           .join(', ')}\n`
 6248:       )
 6249:     } else {
 6250:       push(
 6251:         `import { ${ast.helpers
 6252:           .map(s => `${helperNameMap[s]} as _${helperNameMap[s]}`)
 6253:           .join(', ')} } from ${JSON.stringify(runtimeModuleName)}\n`
 6254:       )
 6255:     }
 6256:   }
 6257: 
 6258:   if (ast.ssrHelpers && ast.ssrHelpers.length) {
 6259:     push(
 6260:       `import { ${ast.ssrHelpers
 6261:         .map(s => `${helperNameMap[s]} as _${helperNameMap[s]}`)
 6262:         .join(', ')} } from "${ssrRuntimeModuleName}"\n`
 6263:     )
 6264:   }
 6265: 
 6266:   if (ast.imports.length) {
 6267:     genImports(ast.imports, context)
 6268:     newline()
 6269:   }
 6270: 
 6271:   genHoists(ast.hoists, context)
 6272:   newline()
 6273: 
 6274:   if (!inline) {
 6275:     push(`export `)
 6276:   }
 6277: }
 6278: function genImports(importsOptions, context) {
 6279:   if (!importsOptions.length) {
 6280:     return
 6281:   }
 6282:   importsOptions.forEach(imports => {
 6283:     context.push(`import `)
 6284:     genNode(imports.exp, context)
 6285:     context.push(` from '${imports.path}'`)
 6286:     context.newline()
 6287:   })
 6288: }
 6289: function genFunctionPreamble(ast, context) {
 6290:   const {
 6291:     ssr,
 6292:     prefixIdentifiers,
 6293:     push,
 6294:     newline,
 6295:     runtimeModuleName,
 6296:     runtimeGlobalName,
 6297:     ssrRuntimeModuleName
 6298:   } = context
 6299:   const VueBinding =
 6300:     !__BROWSER__ && ssr
 6301:       ? `require(${JSON.stringify(runtimeModuleName)})`
 6302:       : runtimeGlobalName
 6303:   const aliasHelper = (s) => `${helperNameMap[s]}: _${helperNameMap[s]}`
 6304:   // Generate const declaration for helpers
 6305:   // In prefix mode, we place the const declaration at top so it's done
 6306:   // only once; But if we not prefixing, we place the declaration inside the
 6307:   // with block so it doesn't incur the `in` check cost for every helper access.
 6308:   if (ast.helpers.length > 0) {
 6309:     if (!__BROWSER__ && prefixIdentifiers) {
 6310:       push(
 6311:         `const { ${ast.helpers.map(aliasHelper).join(', ')} } = ${VueBinding}\n`
 6312:       )
 6313:     } else {
 6314:       // "with" mode.
 6315:       // save Vue in a separate variable to avoid collision
 6316:       push(`const _Vue = ${VueBinding}\n`)
 6317:       // in "with" mode, helpers are declared inside the with block to avoid
 6318:       // has check cost, but hoists are lifted out of the function - we need
 6319:       // to provide the helper here.
 6320:       if (ast.hoists.length) {
 6321:         const staticHelpers = [
 6322:           CREATE_VNODE,
 6323:           CREATE_ELEMENT_VNODE,
 6324:           CREATE_COMMENT,
 6325:           CREATE_TEXT,
 6326:           CREATE_STATIC
 6327:         ]
 6328:           .filter(helper => ast.helpers.includes(helper))
 6329:           .map(aliasHelper)
 6330:           .join(', ')
 6331:         push(`const { ${staticHelpers} } = _Vue\n`)
 6332:       }
 6333:     }
 6334:   }
 6335:   // generate variables for ssr helpers
 6336:   if (!__BROWSER__ && ast.ssrHelpers && ast.ssrHelpers.length) {
 6337:     // ssr guarantees prefixIdentifier: true
 6338:     push(
 6339:       `const { ${ast.ssrHelpers
 6340:         .map(aliasHelper)
 6341:         .join(', ')} } = require("${ssrRuntimeModuleName}")\n`
 6342:     )
 6343:   }
 6344:   genHoists(ast.hoists, context)
 6345:   newline()
 6346:   push(`return `)
 6347: }
 6348: function genHoists(hoists, context) {
 6349:   if (!hoists.length) {
 6350:     return
 6351:   }
 6352:   context.pure = true
 6353:   const { push, newline, helper, scopeId, mode } = context
 6354:   const genScopeId = !__BROWSER__ && scopeId != null && mode !== 'function'
 6355:   newline()
 6356: 
 6357:   // generate inlined withScopeId helper
 6358:   if (genScopeId) {
 6359:     push(
 6360:       `const _withScopeId = n => (${helper(
 6361:         PUSH_SCOPE_ID
 6362:       )}("${scopeId}"),n=n(),${helper(POP_SCOPE_ID)}(),n)`
 6363:     )
 6364:     newline()
 6365:   }
 6366: 
 6367:   for (let i = 0; i < hoists.length; i++) {
 6368:     const exp = hoists[i]
 6369:     if (exp) {
 6370:       const needScopeIdWrapper = genScopeId && exp.type === NodeTypes.VNODE_CALL
 6371:       push(
 6372:         `const _hoisted_${i + 1} = ${
 6373:           needScopeIdWrapper ? `${PURE_ANNOTATION} _withScopeId(() => ` : ``
 6374:         }`
 6375:       )
 6376:       genNode(exp, context)
 6377:       if (needScopeIdWrapper) {
 6378:         push(`)`)
 6379:       }
 6380:       newline()
 6381:     }
 6382:   }
 6383: 
 6384:   context.pure = false
 6385: }
 6386: // type = 'component' | 'directive' | 'filter'
 6387: function genAssets(assets, type, { helper, push, newline, isTS }) {
 6388:   const resolver = helper(
 6389:     type === 'component'
 6390:       ? RESOLVE_COMPONENT
 6391:       : RESOLVE_DIRECTIVE
 6392:   )
 6393:   for (let i = 0; i < assets.length; i++) {
 6394:     let id = assets[i]
 6395:     // potential component implicit self-reference inferred from SFC filename
 6396:     const maybeSelfReference = id.endsWith('__self')
 6397:     if (maybeSelfReference) {
 6398:       id = id.slice(0, -6)
 6399:     }
 6400:     push(
 6401:       `const ${toValidAssetId(id, type)} = ${resolver}(${JSON.stringify(id)}${
 6402:         maybeSelfReference ? `, true` : ``
 6403:       })${isTS ? `!` : ``}`
 6404:     )
 6405:     if (i < assets.length - 1) {
 6406:       newline()
 6407:     }
 6408:   }
 6409: }
 6410: function genText(node, context) {
 6411:   context.push(JSON.stringify(node.content), node)
 6412: }
 6413: function genExpression(node, context) {
 6414:   const { content, isStatic } = node
 6415:   context.push(isStatic ? JSON.stringify(content) : content, node)
 6416: }
 6417: function genInterpolation(node, context) {
 6418:   const { push, helper, pure } = context
 6419:   if (pure) push(PURE_ANNOTATION)
 6420:   push(`${helper(TO_DISPLAY_STRING)}(`)
 6421:   genNode(node.content, context)
 6422:   push(`)`)
 6423: }
 6424: function genCompoundExpression(node, context) {
 6425:   for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
 6426:     const child = node.children[i]
 6427:     if (isString(child)) {
 6428:       context.push(child)
 6429:     } else {
 6430:       genNode(child, context)
 6431:     }
 6432:   }
 6433: }
 6434: function genComment(node, context) {
 6435:   const { push, helper, pure } = context
 6436:   if (pure) {
 6437:     push(PURE_ANNOTATION)
 6438:   }
 6439:   push(`${helper(CREATE_COMMENT)}(${JSON.stringify(node.content)})`, node)
 6440: }
 6441: function genVNodeCall(node, context) {
 6442:   const { push, helper, pure } = context
 6443:   const {
 6444:     tag,
 6445:     props,
 6446:     children,
 6447:     patchFlag,
 6448:     dynamicProps,
 6449:     directives,
 6450:     isBlock,
 6451:     disableTracking,
 6452:     isComponent
 6453:   } = node
 6454:   if (directives) {
 6455:     push(helper(WITH_DIRECTIVES) + `(`)
 6456:   }
 6457:   if (isBlock) {
 6458:     push(`(${helper(OPEN_BLOCK)}(${disableTracking ? `true` : ``}), `)
 6459:   }
 6460:   if (pure) {
 6461:     push(PURE_ANNOTATION)
 6462:   }
 6463:   const callHelper = isBlock
 6464:     ? getVNodeBlockHelper(context.inSSR, isComponent)
 6465:     : getVNodeHelper(context.inSSR, isComponent)
 6466:   push(helper(callHelper) + `(`, node)
 6467:   genNodeList(
 6468:     genNullableArgs([tag, props, children, patchFlag, dynamicProps]),
 6469:     context
 6470:   )
 6471:   push(`)`)
 6472:   if (isBlock) {
 6473:     push(`)`)
 6474:   }
 6475:   if (directives) {
 6476:     push(`, `)
 6477:     genNode(directives, context)
 6478:     push(`)`)
 6479:   }
 6480: }
 6481: // JavaScript
 6482: function genCallExpression(node, context) {
 6483:   const { push, helper, pure } = context
 6484:   const callee = isString(node.callee) ? node.callee : helper(node.callee)
 6485:   if (pure) {
 6486:     push(PURE_ANNOTATION)
 6487:   }
 6488:   push(callee + `(`, node)
 6489:   genNodeList(node.arguments, context)
 6490:   push(`)`)
 6491: }
 6492: function genObjectExpression(node, context) {
 6493:   const { push, indent, deindent, newline } = context
 6494:   const { properties } = node
 6495:   if (!properties.length) {
 6496:     push(`{}`, node)
 6497:     return
 6498:   }
 6499:   const multilines =
 6500:     properties.length > 1 ||
 6501:     ((!__BROWSER__ || __DEV__) &&
 6502:       properties.some(p => p.value.type !== NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION))
 6503:   push(multilines ? `{` : `{ `)
 6504:   multilines && indent()
 6505:   for (let i = 0; i < properties.length; i++) {
 6506:     const { key, value } = properties[i]
 6507:     // key
 6508:     genExpressionAsPropertyKey(key, context)
 6509:     push(`: `)
 6510:     // value
 6511:     genNode(value, context)
 6512:     if (i < properties.length - 1) {
 6513:       // will only reach this if it's multilines
 6514:       push(`,`)
 6515:       newline()
 6516:     }
 6517:   }
 6518:   multilines && deindent()
 6519:   push(multilines ? `}` : ` }`)
 6520: }
 6521: function genArrayExpression(node, context) {
 6522:   genNodeListAsArray(node.elements, context)
 6523: }
 6524: function genFunctionExpression(node, context) {
 6525:   const { push, indent, deindent } = context
 6526:   const { params, returns, body, newline, isSlot } = node
 6527:   if (isSlot) {
 6528:     // wrap slot functions with owner context
 6529:     push(`_${helperNameMap[WITH_CTX]}(`)
 6530:   }
 6531:   push(`(`, node)
 6532:   if (isArray(params)) {
 6533:     genNodeList(params, context)
 6534:   } else if (params) {
 6535:     genNode(params, context)
 6536:   }
 6537:   push(`) => `)
 6538:   if (newline || body) {
 6539:     push(`{`)
 6540:     indent()
 6541:   }
 6542:   if (returns) {
 6543:     if (newline) {
 6544:       push(`return `)
 6545:     }
 6546:     if (isArray(returns)) {
 6547:       genNodeListAsArray(returns, context)
 6548:     } else {
 6549:       genNode(returns, context)
 6550:     }
 6551:   } else if (body) {
 6552:     genNode(body, context)
 6553:   }
 6554:   if (newline || body) {
 6555:     deindent()
 6556:     push(`}`)
 6557:   }
 6558:   if (isSlot) {
 6559:     push(`)`)
 6560:   }
 6561: }
 6562: function genConditionalExpression(node, context) {
 6563:   const { test, consequent, alternate, newline: needNewline } = node
 6564:   const { push, indent, deindent, newline } = context
 6565:   if (test.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION) {
 6566:     const needsParens = !isSimpleIdentifier(test.content)
 6567:     needsParens && push(`(`)
 6568:     genExpression(test, context)
 6569:     needsParens && push(`)`)
 6570:   } else {
 6571:     push(`(`)
 6572:     genNode(test, context)
 6573:     push(`)`)
 6574:   }
 6575:   needNewline && indent()
 6576:   context.indentLevel++
 6577:   needNewline || push(` `)
 6578:   push(`? `)
 6579:   genNode(consequent, context)
 6580:   context.indentLevel--
 6581:   needNewline && newline()
 6582:   needNewline || push(` `)
 6583:   push(`: `)
 6584:   const isNested = alternate.type === NodeTypes.JS_CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION
 6585:   if (!isNested) {
 6586:     context.indentLevel++
 6587:   }
 6588:   genNode(alternate, context)
 6589:   if (!isNested) {
 6590:     context.indentLevel--
 6591:   }
 6592:   needNewline && deindent(true /* without newline */)
 6593: }
 6594: function genCacheExpression(node, context) {
 6595:   const { push, helper, indent, deindent, newline } = context
 6596:   push(`_cache[${node.index}] || (`)
 6597:   if (node.isVNode) {
 6598:     indent()
 6599:     push(`${helper(SET_BLOCK_TRACKING)}(-1),`)
 6600:     newline()
 6601:   }
 6602:   push(`_cache[${node.index}] = `)
 6603:   genNode(node.value, context)
 6604:   if (node.isVNode) {
 6605:     push(`,`)
 6606:     newline()
 6607:     push(`${helper(SET_BLOCK_TRACKING)}(1),`)
 6608:     newline()
 6609:     push(`_cache[${node.index}]`)
 6610:     deindent()
 6611:   }
 6612:   push(`)`)
 6613: }
 6614: function genNodeList(nodes, context, multilines = false, comma = true) {
 6615:   const { push, newline } = context
 6616:   for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
 6617:     const node = nodes[i]
 6618:     if (isString(node)) {
 6619:       push(node)
 6620:     } else if (isArray(node)) {
 6621:       genNodeListAsArray(node, context)
 6622:     } else {
 6623:       genNode(node, context)
 6624:     }
 6625:     if (i < nodes.length - 1) {
 6626:       if (multilines) {
 6627:         comma && push(',')
 6628:         newline()
 6629:       } else {
 6630:         comma && push(', ')
 6631:       }
 6632:     }
 6633:   }
 6634: }
 6635: function genTemplateLiteral(node, context) {
 6636:   const { push, indent, deindent } = context
 6637:   push('`')
 6638:   const l = node.elements.length
 6639:   const multilines = l > 3
 6640:   for (let i = 0; i < l; i++) {
 6641:     const e = node.elements[i]
 6642:     if (isString(e)) {
 6643:       push(e.replace(/(`|\$|\\)/g, '\\$1'))
 6644:     } else {
 6645:       push('${')
 6646:       if (multilines) indent()
 6647:       genNode(e, context)
 6648:       if (multilines) deindent()
 6649:       push('}')
 6650:     }
 6651:   }
 6652:   push('`')
 6653: }
 6654: function genIfStatement(node, context) {
 6655:   const { push, indent, deindent } = context
 6656:   const { test, consequent, alternate } = node
 6657:   push(`if (`)
 6658:   genNode(test, context)
 6659:   push(`) {`)
 6660:   indent()
 6661:   genNode(consequent, context)
 6662:   deindent()
 6663:   push(`}`)
 6664:   if (alternate) {
 6665:     push(` else `)
 6666:     if (alternate.type === NodeTypes.JS_IF_STATEMENT) {
 6667:       genIfStatement(alternate, context)
 6668:     } else {
 6669:       push(`{`)
 6670:       indent()
 6671:       genNode(alternate, context)
 6672:       deindent()
 6673:       push(`}`)
 6674:     }
 6675:   }
 6676: }
 6677: function genAssignmentExpression(node, context) {
 6678:   genNode(node.left, context)
 6679:   context.push(` = `)
 6680:   genNode(node.right, context)
 6681: }
 6682: function genSequenceExpression(node, context) {
 6683:   context.push(`(`)
 6684:   genNodeList(node.expressions, context)
 6685:   context.push(`)`)
 6686: }
 6687: function genReturnStatement({ returns }, context) {
 6688:   context.push(`return `)
 6689:   if (isArray(returns)) {
 6690:     genNodeListAsArray(returns, context)
 6691:   } else {
 6692:     genNode(returns, context)
 6693:   }
 6694: }
 6695: 
 6696: function genNode(node, context) {
 6697:   if (isString(node)) {
 6698:     context.push(node)
 6699:     return
 6700:   }
 6701:   if (isSymbol(node)) {
 6702:     context.push(context.helper(node))
 6703:     return
 6704:   }
 6705:   switch (node.type) {
 6706:     case NodeTypes.ELEMENT:
 6707:     case NodeTypes.IF:
 6708:     case NodeTypes.FOR:
 6709:       genNode(node.codegenNode, context)
 6710:       break
 6711:     case NodeTypes.TEXT:
 6712:       genText(node, context)
 6713:       break
 6714:     case NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION:
 6715:       genExpression(node, context)
 6716:       break
 6717:     case NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION:
 6718:       genInterpolation(node, context)
 6719:       break
 6720:     case NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL:
 6721:       genNode(node.codegenNode, context)
 6722:       break
 6723:     case NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION:
 6724:       genCompoundExpression(node, context)
 6725:       break
 6726:     case NodeTypes.COMMENT:
 6727:       genComment(node, context)
 6728:       break
 6729:     case NodeTypes.VNODE_CALL:
 6730:       genVNodeCall(node, context)
 6731:       break
 6732: 
 6733:     case NodeTypes.JS_CALL_EXPRESSION:
 6734:       genCallExpression(node, context)
 6735:       break
 6736:     case NodeTypes.JS_OBJECT_EXPRESSION:
 6737:       genObjectExpression(node, context)
 6738:       break
 6739:     case NodeTypes.JS_ARRAY_EXPRESSION:
 6740:       genArrayExpression(node, context)
 6741:       break
 6742:     case NodeTypes.JS_FUNCTION_EXPRESSION:
 6743:       genFunctionExpression(node, context)
 6744:       break
 6745:     case NodeTypes.JS_CONDITIONAL_EXPRESSION:
 6746:       genConditionalExpression(node, context)
 6747:       break
 6748:     case NodeTypes.JS_CACHE_EXPRESSION:
 6749:       genCacheExpression(node, context)
 6750:       break
 6751:     case NodeTypes.JS_BLOCK_STATEMENT:
 6752:       genNodeList(node.body, context, true, false)
 6753:       break
 6754: 
 6755:     // SSR only types
 6756:     case NodeTypes.JS_TEMPLATE_LITERAL:
 6757:       !__BROWSER__ && genTemplateLiteral(node, context)
 6758:       break
 6759:     case NodeTypes.JS_IF_STATEMENT:
 6760:       !__BROWSER__ && genIfStatement(node, context)
 6761:       break
 6762:     case NodeTypes.JS_ASSIGNMENT_EXPRESSION:
 6763:       !__BROWSER__ && genAssignmentExpression(node, context)
 6764:       break
 6765:     case NodeTypes.JS_SEQUENCE_EXPRESSION:
 6766:       !__BROWSER__ && genSequenceExpression(node, context)
 6767:       break
 6768:     case NodeTypes.JS_RETURN_STATEMENT:
 6769:       !__BROWSER__ && genReturnStatement(node, context)
 6770:       break
 6771: 
 6772:     /* istanbul ignore next */
 6773:     case NodeTypes.IF_BRANCH:
 6774:       // noop
 6775:       break
 6776:     default:
 6777:       logg(`unhandled codegen node type: ${node.type}`)
 6778:   }
 6779: }
 6780: function genNodeListAsArray(nodes, context) {
 6781:   const multilines =
 6782:     nodes.length > 3 ||
 6783:     ((!__BROWSER__ || __DEV__) && nodes.some(n => isArray(n) || !isText(n)))
 6784:   context.push(`[`)
 6785:   multilines && context.indent()
 6786:   genNodeList(nodes, context, multilines)
 6787:   multilines && context.deindent()
 6788:   context.push(`]`)
 6789: }
 6790: 
 6791: function generate(ast, options = {}) {
 6792:   const context = createCodegenContext(ast, options)
 6793:   if (options.onContextCreated) options.onContextCreated(context)
 6794:   const {
 6795:     mode,
 6796:     push,
 6797:     prefixIdentifiers,
 6798:     indent,
 6799:     deindent,
 6800:     newline,
 6801:     scopeId,
 6802:     ssr
 6803:   } = context
 6804: 
 6805:   const hasHelpers = ast.helpers.length > 0
 6806:   const useWithBlock = !prefixIdentifiers && mode !== 'module'
 6807:   const genScopeId = !__BROWSER__ && scopeId != null && mode === 'module'
 6808:   const isSetupInlined = !__BROWSER__ && !!options.inline
 6809: 
 6810:   // preambles
 6811:   // in setup() inline mode, the preamble is generated in a sub context
 6812:   // and returned separately.
 6813:   const preambleContext = isSetupInlined
 6814:     ? createCodegenContext(ast, options)
 6815:     : context
 6816:   if (!__BROWSER__ && mode === 'module') {
 6817:     genModulePreamble(ast, preambleContext, genScopeId, isSetupInlined)
 6818:   } else {
 6819:     genFunctionPreamble(ast, preambleContext)
 6820:   }
 6821:   // enter render function
 6822:   const functionName = ssr ? `ssrRender` : `render`
 6823:   const args = ssr ? ['_ctx', '_push', '_parent', '_attrs'] : ['_ctx', '_cache']
 6824:   if (!__BROWSER__ && options.bindingMetadata && !options.inline) {
 6825:     // binding optimization args
 6826:     args.push('$props', '$setup', '$data', '$options')
 6827:   }
 6828:   const signature =
 6829:     !__BROWSER__ && options.isTS
 6830:       ? args.map(arg => `${arg}: any`).join(',')
 6831:       : args.join(', ')
 6832: 
 6833:   if (isSetupInlined) {
 6834:     push(`(${signature}) => {`)
 6835:   } else {
 6836:     push(`function ${functionName}(${signature}) {`)
 6837:   }
 6838:   indent()
 6839: 
 6840:   if (useWithBlock) {
 6841:     push(`with (_ctx) {`)
 6842:     indent()
 6843:     // function mode const declarations should be inside with block
 6844:     // also they should be renamed to avoid collision with user properties
 6845:     if (hasHelpers) {
 6846:       push(
 6847:         `const { ${ast.helpers
 6848:           .map(s => `${helperNameMap[s]}: _${helperNameMap[s]}`)
 6849:           .join(', ')} } = _Vue`
 6850:       )
 6851:       push(`\n`)
 6852:       newline()
 6853:     }
 6854:   }
 6855: 
 6856:   // generate asset resolution statements
 6857:   if (ast.components.length) {
 6858:     genAssets(ast.components, 'component', context)
 6859:     if (ast.directives.length || ast.temps > 0) {
 6860:       newline()
 6861:     }
 6862:   }
 6863:   if (ast.directives.length) {
 6864:     genAssets(ast.directives, 'directive', context)
 6865:     if (ast.temps > 0) {
 6866:       newline()
 6867:     }
 6868:   }
 6869: 
 6870:   // 
 6871:   if (ast.temps > 0) {
 6872:     push(`let `)
 6873:     for (let i = 0; i < ast.temps; i++) {
 6874:       push(`${i > 0 ? `, ` : ``}_temp${i}`)
 6875:     }
 6876:   }
 6877:   if (ast.components.length || ast.directives.length || ast.temps) {
 6878:     push(`\n`)
 6879:     newline()
 6880:   }
 6881: 
 6882:   // generate the VNode tree expression
 6883:   if (!ssr) {
 6884:     push(`return `)
 6885:   }
 6886:   if (ast.codegenNode) {
 6887:     genNode(ast.codegenNode, context)
 6888:   } else {
 6889:     push(`null`)
 6890:   }
 6891: 
 6892:   if (useWithBlock) {
 6893:     deindent()
 6894:     push(`}`)
 6895:   }
 6896: 
 6897:   deindent()
 6898:   push(`}`)
 6899: 
 6900:   return {
 6901:     ast,
 6902:     code: context.code,
 6903:     preamble: isSetupInlined ? preambleContext.code : ``,
 6904:     // SourceMapGenerator does have toJSON() method but it's not in the types
 6905:     map: context.map ? context.map.toJSON() : undefined
 6906:   }
 6907: }
 6908: 
 6909: function baseCompile(template, options = {}) {
 6910:   const isModuleMode = options.mode === 'module'
 6911: 
 6912:   const prefixIdentifiers =
 6913:     !__BROWSER__ && (options.prefixIdentifiers === true || isModuleMode)
 6914: 
 6915:   const ast = isString(template) ? baseParse(template, options) : template
 6916:   const [nodeTransforms, directiveTransforms] = getBaseTransformPreset(prefixIdentifiers)
 6917: 
 6918:   //  codegenNode
 6919:   transform(
 6920:     ast,
 6921:     extend({}, options, {
 6922:       prefixIdentifiers,
 6923:       nodeTransforms: [
 6924:         ...nodeTransforms,
 6925:         ...(options.nodeTransforms || []) // user transforms
 6926:       ],
 6927:       directiveTransforms: extend(
 6928:         {},
 6929:         directiveTransforms,
 6930:         options.directiveTransforms || {} // user transforms
 6931:       )
 6932:     })
 6933:   )
 6934: 
 6935:   //  codegen
 6936:   return generate(ast, extend({}, options, { prefixIdentifiers }))
 6937: }

 9172: const decodeHtml = (rawText, asAttr) => {
 9173:   let offset = 0
 9174:   const end = rawText.length
 9175:   let decodedText = ''
 9176: 
 9177:   function advance(length) {
 9178:     offset += length
 9179:     rawText = rawText.slice(length)
 9180:   }
 9181: 
 9182:   while (offset < end) {
 9183:     const head = /&(?:#x?)?/i.exec(rawText)
 9184:     if (!head || offset + head.index >= end) {
 9185:       const remaining = end - offset
 9186:       decodedText += rawText.slice(0, remaining)
 9187:       advance(remaining)
 9188:       break
 9189:     }
 9190: 
 9191:     // Advance to the "&".
 9192:     decodedText += rawText.slice(0, head.index)
 9193:     advance(head.index)
 9194: 
 9195:     if (head[0] === '&') {
 9196:       // Named character reference.
 9197:       let name = ''
 9198:       let value = undefined
 9199:       if (/[0-9a-z]/i.test(rawText[1])) {
 9200:         if (!maxCRNameLength) {
 9201:           maxCRNameLength = Object.keys(namedCharacterReferences).reduce(
 9202:             (max, name) => Math.max(max, name.length),
 9203:             0
 9204:           )
 9205:         }
 9206:         for (let length = maxCRNameLength; !value && length > 0; --length) {
 9207:           name = rawText.slice(1, 1 + length)
 9208:           value = namedCharacterReferences[name]
 9209:         }
 9210:         if (value) {
 9211:           const semi = name.endsWith(';')
 9212:           if (
 9213:             asAttr &&
 9214:             !semi &&
 9215:             /[=a-z0-9]/i.test(rawText[name.length + 1] || '')
 9216:           ) {
 9217:             decodedText += '&' + name
 9218:             advance(1 + name.length)
 9219:           } else {
 9220:             decodedText += value
 9221:             advance(1 + name.length)
 9222:           }
 9223:         } else {
 9224:           decodedText += '&' + name
 9225:           advance(1 + name.length)
 9226:         }
 9227:       } else {
 9228:         decodedText += '&'
 9229:         advance(1)
 9230:       }
 9231:     } else {
 9232:       // Numeric character reference.
 9233:       const hex = head[0] === '&#x'
 9234:       const pattern = hex ? /^&#x([0-9a-f]+);?/i : /^&#([0-9]+);?/
 9235:       const body = pattern.exec(rawText)
 9236:       if (!body) {
 9237:         decodedText += head[0]
 9238:         advance(head[0].length)
 9239:       } else {
 9240:         // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/parsing.html#numeric-character-reference-end-state
 9241:         let cp = Number.parseInt(body[1], hex ? 16 : 10)
 9242:         if (cp === 0) {
 9243:           cp = 0xfffd
 9244:         } else if (cp > 0x10ffff) {
 9245:           cp = 0xfffd
 9246:         } else if (cp >= 0xd800 && cp <= 0xdfff) {
 9247:           cp = 0xfffd
 9248:         } else if ((cp >= 0xfdd0 && cp <= 0xfdef) || (cp & 0xfffe) === 0xfffe) {
 9249:           // noop
 9250:         } else if (
 9251:           (cp >= 0x01 && cp <= 0x08) ||
 9252:           cp === 0x0b ||
 9253:           (cp >= 0x0d && cp <= 0x1f) ||
 9254:           (cp >= 0x7f && cp <= 0x9f)
 9255:         ) {
 9256:           cp = CCR_REPLACEMENTS[cp] || cp
 9257:         }
 9258:         decodedText += String.fromCodePoint(cp)
 9259:         advance(body[0].length)
 9260:       }
 9261:     }
 9262:   }
 9263:   return decodedText
 9264: }
 9265: 
 9266: // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/parsing.html#numeric-character-reference-end-state
 9267: const CCR_REPLACEMENTS = {
 9268:   0x80: 0x20ac,
 9269:   0x82: 0x201a,
 9270:   0x83: 0x0192,
 9271:   0x84: 0x201e,
 9272:   0x85: 0x2026,
 9273:   0x86: 0x2020,
 9274:   0x87: 0x2021,
 9275:   0x88: 0x02c6,
 9276:   0x89: 0x2030,
 9277:   0x8a: 0x0160,
 9278:   0x8b: 0x2039,
 9279:   0x8c: 0x0152,
 9280:   0x8e: 0x017d,
 9281:   0x91: 0x2018,
 9282:   0x92: 0x2019,
 9283:   0x93: 0x201c,
 9284:   0x94: 0x201d,
 9285:   0x95: 0x2022,
 9286:   0x96: 0x2013,
 9287:   0x97: 0x2014,
 9288:   0x98: 0x02dc,
 9289:   0x99: 0x2122,
 9290:   0x9a: 0x0161,
 9291:   0x9b: 0x203a,
 9292:   0x9c: 0x0153,
 9293:   0x9e: 0x017e,
 9294:   0x9f: 0x0178
 9295: }
 9296: 
 9297: let decoder
 9298: 
 9299: function decodeHtmlBrowser(raw, asAttr = false) {
 9300:   if (!decoder) {
 9301:     decoder = document.createElement('div')
 9302:   }
 9303:   if (asAttr) {
 9304:     decoder.innerHTML = `<div foo="${raw.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}">`
 9305:     return decoder.children[0].getAttribute('foo')
 9306:   } else {
 9307:     decoder.innerHTML = raw
 9308:     return decoder.textContent
 9309:   }
 9310: }

 9340:  * On the client we only need to offer special cases for boolean attributes that
 9341:  * have different names from their corresponding dom properties:
 9342:  * - itemscope -> N/A
 9343:  * - allowfullscreen -> allowFullscreen
 9344:  * - formnovalidate -> formNoValidate
 9345:  * - ismap -> isMap
 9346:  * - nomodule -> noModule
 9347:  * - novalidate -> noValidate
 9348:  * - readonly -> readOnly
 9349:  */

 9357:   specialBooleanAttrs +
 9358:     `,async,autofocus,autoplay,controls,default,defer,disabled,hidden,` +

 9363: /**
 9364:  * Boolean attributes should be included if the value is truthy or ''.
 9365:  * e.g. `<select multiple>` compiles to `{ multiple: '' }`
 9366:  */
 9367: function includeBooleanAttr(value) {
 9368:   return !!value || value === ''
 9369: }

 9371: const unsafeAttrCharRE = /[>/="'\u0009\u000a\u000c\u0020]/
 9372: const attrValidationCache = {}
 9373: 
 9374: function isSSRSafeAttrName(name) {
 9375:   if (attrValidationCache.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
 9376:     return attrValidationCache[name]
 9377:   }
 9378:   const isUnsafe = unsafeAttrCharRE.test(name)
 9379:   if (isUnsafe) {
 9380:     console.error(`unsafe attribute name: ${name}`)
 9381:   }
 9382:   return (attrValidationCache[name] = !isUnsafe)
 9383: }

 9513: function normalizeStyle(value) {
 9514:   if (isArray(value)) {
 9515:     const res = {}
 9516:     for (let i = 0; i < value.length; i++) {
 9517:       const item = value[i]
 9518:       const normalized = isString(item)
 9519:         ? parseStringStyle(item)
 9520:         : normalizeStyle(item)
 9521:       if (normalized) {
 9522:         for (const key in normalized) {
 9523:           res[key] = normalized[key]
 9524:         }
 9525:       }
 9526:     }
 9527:     return res
 9528:   } else if (isString(value)) {
 9529:     return value
 9530:   } else if (isObject(value)) {
 9531:     return value
 9532:   }
 9533: }
 9534: 
 9535: const listDelimiterRE = /;(?![^(]*\))/g
 9536: const propertyDelimiterRE = /:(.+)/
 9537: 
 9538: function parseStringStyle(cssText) {
 9539:   const ret = {}
 9540:   cssText.split(listDelimiterRE).forEach(item => {
 9541:     if (item) {
 9542:       const tmp = item.split(propertyDelimiterRE)
 9543:       tmp.length > 1 && (ret[tmp[0].trim()] = tmp[1].trim())
 9544:     }
 9545:   })
 9546:   return ret
 9547: }
 9548: 
 9549: function stringifyStyle(styles) {
 9550:   let ret = ''
 9551:   if (!styles || isString(styles)) {
 9552:     return ret
 9553:   }
 9554:   for (const key in styles) {
 9555:     const value = styles[key]
 9556:     const normalizedKey = key.startsWith(`--`) ? key : hyphenate(key)
 9557:     if (
 9558:       isString(value) ||
 9559:       (typeof value === 'number' && isNoUnitNumericStyleProp(normalizedKey))
 9560:     ) {
 9561:       // only render valid values
 9562:       ret += `${normalizedKey}:${value};`
 9563:     }
 9564:   }
 9565:   return ret
 9566: }
 9567: 
 9568: function normalizeClass(value) {
 9569:   let res = ''
 9570:   if (isString(value)) {
 9571:     res = value
 9572:   } else if (isArray(value)) {
 9573:     for (let i = 0; i < value.length; i++) {
 9574:       const normalized = normalizeClass(value[i])
 9575:       if (normalized) {
 9576:         res += normalized + ' '
 9577:       }
 9578:     }
 9579:   } else if (isObject(value)) {
 9580:     for (const name in value) {
 9581:       if (value[name]) {
 9582:         res += name + ' '
 9583:       }
 9584:     }
 9585:   }
 9586:   return res.trim()
 9587: }
 9588: 
 9589: function normalizeProps(props) {
 9590:   if (!props) return null
 9591:   let { class: klass, style } = props
 9592:   if (klass && !isString(klass)) {
 9593:     props.class = normalizeClass(klass)
 9594:   }
 9595:   if (style) {
 9596:     props.style = normalizeStyle(style)
 9597:   }
 9598:   return props
 9599: }

 9601: const escapeRE = /["'&<>]/
 9602: 
 9603: function escapeHtml(string) {
 9604:   const str = '' + string
 9605:   const match = escapeRE.exec(str)
 9606: 
 9607:   if (!match) {
 9608:     return str
 9609:   }
 9610: 
 9611:   let html = ''
 9612:   let escaped
 9613:   let index
 9614:   let lastIndex = 0
 9615:   for (index = match.index; index < str.length; index++) {
 9616:     switch (str.charCodeAt(index)) {
 9617:       case 34: // "
 9618:         escaped = '&quot;'
 9619:         break
 9620:       case 38: // &
 9621:         escaped = '&amp;'
 9622:         break
 9623:       case 39: // '
 9624:         escaped = '&#39;'
 9625:         break
 9626:       case 60: // <
 9627:         escaped = '&lt;'
 9628:         break
 9629:       case 62: // >
 9630:         escaped = '&gt;'
 9631:         break
 9632:       default:
 9633:         continue
 9634:     }
 9635: 
 9636:     if (lastIndex !== index) {
 9637:       html += str.slice(lastIndex, index)
 9638:     }
 9639: 
 9640:     lastIndex = index + 1
 9641:     html += escaped
 9642:   }
 9643: 
 9644:   return lastIndex !== index ? html + str.slice(lastIndex, index) : html
 9645: }
 9646: 
 9647: // https://www.w3.org/TR/html52/syntax.html#comments
 9648: const commentStripRE = /^-?>|<!--|-->|--!>|<!-$/g
 9649: 
 9650: function escapeHtmlComment(src) {
 9651:   return src.replace(commentStripRE, '')
 9652: }
 9653: 
 9654: const toDisplayString = (val) => {
 9655:   return isString(val)
 9656:     ? val
 9657:     : val == null
 9658:     ? ''
 9659:     : isArray(val) ||
 9660:       (isObject(val) &&
 9661:         (val.toString === objectToString || !isFunction(val.toString)))
 9662:     ? JSON.stringify(val, replacer, 2)
 9663:     : String(val)
 9664: }
 9665: 
 9666: const replacer = (_key, val) => {
 9667:   // can't use isRef here since @vue/shared has no deps
 9668:   if (val && val.__v_isRef) {
 9669:     return replacer(_key, val.value)
 9670:   } else if (isMap(val)) {
 9671:     return {
 9672:       [`Map(${val.size})`]: [...val.entries()].reduce((entries, [key, val]) => {
 9673:         ;entries[`${key} =>`] = val
 9674:         return entries
 9675:       }, {})
 9676:     }
 9677:   } else if (isSet(val)) {
 9678:     return {
 9679:       [`Set(${val.size})`]: [...val.values()]
 9680:     }
 9681:   } else if (isObject(val) && !isArray(val) && !isPlainObject(val)) {
 9682:     return String(val)
 9683:   }
 9684:   return val
 9685: }

 9695: const DOMNamespaces = {
 9696:   HTML: Namespaces.HTML,
 9697:   SVG: 1,
 9698:   MATH_ML: 2

 9701: const parserOptions = {
 9702:   isVoidTag,
 9703:   isNativeTag: tag => isHTMLTag(tag) || isSVGTag(tag),
 9704:   isPreTag: tag => tag === 'pre',
 9705:   decodeEntities: __BROWSER__ ? decodeHtmlBrowser : decodeHtml,
 9706: 
 9707:   isBuiltInComponent: tag => {
 9708:     if (isBuiltInType(tag, `Transition`)) {
 9709:       return TRANSITION
 9710:     } else if (isBuiltInType(tag, `TransitionGroup`)) {
 9711:       return TRANSITION_GROUP
 9712:     }
 9713:   },
 9714: 
 9715:   // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/parsing.html#tree-construction-dispatcher
 9716:   getNamespace(tag, parent) {
 9717:     let ns = parent ? parent.ns : DOMNamespaces.HTML
 9718: 
 9719:     if (parent && ns === DOMNamespaces.MATH_ML) {
 9720:       if (parent.tag === 'annotation-xml') {
 9721:         if (tag === 'svg') {
 9722:           return DOMNamespaces.SVG
 9723:         }
 9724:         if (
 9725:           parent.props.some(
 9726:             a =>
 9727:               a.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE &&
 9728:               a.name === 'encoding' &&
 9729:               a.value != null &&
 9730:               (a.value.content === 'text/html' ||
 9731:                 a.value.content === 'application/xhtml+xml')
 9732:           )
 9733:         ) {
 9734:           ns = DOMNamespaces.HTML
 9735:         }
 9736:       } else if (
 9737:         /^m(?:[ions]|text)$/.test(parent.tag) &&
 9738:         tag !== 'mglyph' &&
 9739:         tag !== 'malignmark'
 9740:       ) {
 9741:         ns = DOMNamespaces.HTML
 9742:       }
 9743:     } else if (parent && ns === DOMNamespaces.SVG) {
 9744:       if (
 9745:         parent.tag === 'foreignObject' ||
 9746:         parent.tag === 'desc' ||
 9747:         parent.tag === 'title'
 9748:       ) {
 9749:         ns = DOMNamespaces.HTML
 9750:       }
 9751:     }
 9752: 
 9753:     if (ns === DOMNamespaces.HTML) {
 9754:       if (tag === 'svg') {
 9755:         return DOMNamespaces.SVG
 9756:       }
 9757:       if (tag === 'math') {
 9758:         return DOMNamespaces.MATH_ML
 9759:       }
 9760:     }
 9761:     return ns
 9762:   },
 9763: 
 9764:   // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/parsing.html#parsing-html-fragments
 9765:   getTextMode({ tag, ns }) {
 9766:     if (ns === DOMNamespaces.HTML) {
 9767:       if (tag === 'textarea' || tag === 'title') {
 9768:         return TextModes.RCDATA
 9769:       }
 9770:       if (isRawTextContainer(tag)) {
 9771:         return TextModes.RAWTEXT
 9772:       }
 9773:     }
 9774:     return TextModes.DATA
 9775:   }
 9776: }

 9792:   const children = (node.children = node.children.filter(

 9908: const transformModelCD = (dir, node, context) => {
 9909:   const baseResult = transformModel(dir, node, context)
 9910:   // base transform has errors OR component v-model (only need props)
 9911:   if (!baseResult.props.length || node.tagType === ElementTypes.COMPONENT) {
 9912:     return baseResult

 9919:   function checkDuplicatedValue() {
 9920:     const value = findProp(node, 'value')
 9921:     if (value) {
 9922:       logg("transfromModelCD - X_V_MODEL_UNNECESSARY_VALUE")
 9923:     }
 9924:   }
 9925: 
 9926:   const { tag } = node
 9927:   const isCustomElement = context.isCustomElement(tag)
 9928:   if (
 9929:     tag === 'input' ||
 9930:     tag === 'textarea' ||
 9931:     tag === 'select' ||
 9932:     isCustomElement
 9933:   ) {
 9934:     let directiveToUse = V_MODEL_TEXT
 9935:     let isInvalidType = false
 9936:     if (tag === 'input' || isCustomElement) {
 9937:       const type = findProp(node, `type`)
 9938:       if (type) {
 9939:         if (type.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE) {
 9940:           // :type="foo"
 9941:           directiveToUse = V_MODEL_DYNAMIC
 9942:         } else if (type.value) {
 9943:           switch (type.value.content) {
 9944:             case 'radio':
 9945:               directiveToUse = V_MODEL_RADIO
 9946:               break
 9947:             case 'checkbox':
 9948:               directiveToUse = V_MODEL_CHECKBOX
 9949:               break
 9950:             case 'file':
 9951:               isInvalidType = true
 9952:               logg("[DOM]transformModel - X_V_MODEL_ON_FILE_INPUT_ELEMENT")
 9953:               break
 9954:             default:
 9955:               // text type
 9956:               __DEV__ && checkDuplicatedValue()
 9957:               break
 9958:           }
 9959:         }
 9960:       } else if (hasDynamicKeyVBind(node)) {
 9961:         // element has bindings with dynamic keys, which can possibly contain
 9962:         // "type".
 9963:         directiveToUse = V_MODEL_DYNAMIC
 9964:       } else {
 9965:         // text type
 9966:         __DEV__ && checkDuplicatedValue()
 9967:       }
 9968:     } else if (tag === 'select') {
 9969:       directiveToUse = V_MODEL_SELECT
 9970:     } else {
 9971:       // textarea
 9972:       __DEV__ && checkDuplicatedValue()
 9973:     }
 9974:     // inject runtime directive
 9975:     // by returning the helper symbol via needRuntime
 9976:     // the import will replaced a resolveDirective call.
 9977:     if (!isInvalidType) {
 9978:       baseResult.needRuntime = context.helper(directiveToUse)
 9979:     }
 9980:   } else {
 9981:     logg("[DOM]transformModel - X_V_MODEL_ON_INVALID_ELEMENT")
 9982:   }

 9985:   // passed to the runtime as `binding.value`. removing it reduces code size.
 9986:   baseResult.props = baseResult.props.filter(
 9987:     p =>

 9990:         p.key.content === 'modelValue'
 9991:       )
 9992:   )
 9993: 
 9994:   return baseResult
 9995: }
 9996: const isEventOptionModifier = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap(`passive,once,capture`)
 9997: const isNonKeyModifier = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap(
 9998:   // event propagation management
 9999:   `stop,prevent,self,` +
10000:     // system modifiers + exact
10001:     `ctrl,shift,alt,meta,exact,` +
10002:     // mouse
10003:     `middle`
10004: )
10005: // left & right could be mouse or key modifiers based on event type
10006: const maybeKeyModifier = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap('left,right')
10007: const isKeyboardEvent = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap(
10008:   `onkeyup,onkeydown,onkeypress`,
10009:   true

10013: const resolveModifiers = (key, modifiers, context, loc) => {
10014:   const keyModifiers = []
10015:   const nonKeyModifiers = []
10016:   const eventOptionModifiers = []
10017: 
10018:   for (let i = 0; i < modifiers.length; i++) {
10019:     const modifier = modifiers[i]
10020: 
10021:     if (isEventOptionModifier(modifier)) {
10022:       // eventOptionModifiers: modifiers for addEventListener() options,
10023:       // e.g. .passive & .capture
10024:       eventOptionModifiers.push(modifier)
10025:     } else {
10026:       // runtimeModifiers: modifiers that needs runtime guards
10027:       if (maybeKeyModifier(modifier)) {
10028:         if (isStaticExp(key)) {
10029:           if (isKeyboardEvent(key.content)) {
10030:             keyModifiers.push(modifier)
10031:           } else {
10032:             nonKeyModifiers.push(modifier)
10033:           }
10034:         } else {
10035:           keyModifiers.push(modifier)
10036:           nonKeyModifiers.push(modifier)
10037:         }
10038:       } else {
10039:         if (isNonKeyModifier(modifier)) {
10040:           nonKeyModifiers.push(modifier)
10041:         } else {
10042:           keyModifiers.push(modifier)
10043:         }
10044:       }
10045:     }
10046:   }
10047: 
10048:   return {
10049:     keyModifiers,
10050:     nonKeyModifiers,
10051:     eventOptionModifiers
10052:   }
10053: }

10056: const transformClick = (key, event) => {
10057:   const isStaticClick =
10058:     isStaticExp(key) && key.content.toLowerCase() === 'onclick'
10059:   return isStaticClick
10060:     ? createSimpleExpression(event, true)
10061:     : key.type !== NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION
10062:     ? createCompoundExpression([
10063:         `(`,
10064:         key,
10065:         `) === "onClick" ? "${event}" : (`,
10066:         key,
10067:         `)`
10068:       ])
10069:     : key
10070: }

10072: const transformOnCD = (dir, node, context) => {
10073:   return transformOn(dir, node, context, baseResult => {
10074:     const { modifiers } = dir
10075:     if (!modifiers.length) return baseResult
10076: 
10077:     let { key, value: handlerExp } = baseResult.props[0]
10078:     const { keyModifiers, nonKeyModifiers, eventOptionModifiers } =
10079:       resolveModifiers(key, modifiers, context, dir.loc)
10080: 
10081:     // normalize click.right and click.middle since they don't actually fire
10082:     if (nonKeyModifiers.includes('right')) {
10083:       key = transformClick(key, `onContextmenu`)
10084:     }
10085:     if (nonKeyModifiers.includes('middle')) {
10086:       key = transformClick(key, `onMouseup`)
10087:     }
10088: 
10089:     if (nonKeyModifiers.length) {
10090:       handlerExp = createCallExpression(context.helper(V_ON_WITH_MODIFIERS), [
10091:         handlerExp,
10092:         JSON.stringify(nonKeyModifiers)
10093:       ])
10094:     }
10095: 
10096:     if (
10097:       keyModifiers.length &&
10098:       // if event name is dynamic, always wrap with keys guard
10099:       (!isStaticExp(key) || isKeyboardEvent(key.content))
10100:     ) {
10101:       handlerExp = createCallExpression(context.helper(V_ON_WITH_KEYS), [
10102:         handlerExp,
10103:         JSON.stringify(keyModifiers)
10104:       ])
10105:     }
10106: 
10107:     if (eventOptionModifiers.length) {
10108:       const modifierPostfix = eventOptionModifiers.map(capitalize).join('')

10110:         ? createSimpleExpression(`${key.content}${modifierPostfix}`, true)
10111:         : createCompoundExpression([`(`, key, `) + "${modifierPostfix}"`])
10112:     }
10113: 
10114:     return {
10115:       props: [createObjectProperty(key, handlerExp)]
10116:     }
10117:   })
10118: }

10140: 
10141: /**
10142:  * Turn eligible hoisted static trees into stringified static nodes, e.g.
10143:  *
10144:  * ```js
10145:  * const _hoisted_1 = createStaticVNode(`<div class="foo">bar</div>`)
10146:  * ```
10147:  *
10148:  * A single static vnode can contain stringified content for **multiple**
10149:  * consecutive nodes (element and plain text), called a "chunk".
10150:  * `@vue/runtime-dom` will create the content via innerHTML in a hidden
10151:  * container element and insert all the nodes in place. The call must also
10152:  * provide the number of nodes contained in the chunk so that during hydration
10153:  * we can know how many nodes the static vnode should adopt.
10154:  *
10155:  * The optimization scans a children list that contains hoisted nodes, and
10156:  * tries to find the largest chunk of consecutive hoisted nodes before running
10157:  * into a non-hoisted node or the end of the list. A chunk is then converted
10158:  * into a single static vnode and replaces the hoisted expression of the first
10159:  * node in the chunk. Other nodes in the chunk are considered "merged" and
10160:  * therefore removed from both the hoist list and the children array.
10161:  *
10162:  * This optimization is only performed in Node.js.
10163:  */
10164: const stringifyStatic = (children, context, parent) => {
10165:   // bail stringification for slot content
10166:   if (context.scopes.vSlot > 0) {
10167:     return
10168:   }
10169: 
10170:   let nc = 0 // current node count
10171:   let ec = 0 // current element with binding count
10172:   const currentChunk = []
10173: 
10174:   logg(`stringifyStatic - children.length = ${children.length}`)
10175:   const stringifyCurrentChunk = (currentIndex) => {
10176:     if (
10177:       nc >= StringifyThresholds.NODE_COUNT ||
10178:       ec >= StringifyThresholds.ELEMENT_WITH_BINDING_COUNT
10179:     ) {
10180:       logg(`stringifyCurrentChunk - index = ${currentIndex}`)
10181:       // combine all currently eligible nodes into a single static vnode call
10182:       const staticCall = createCallExpression(context.helper(CREATE_STATIC), [
10183:         JSON.stringify(
10184:           currentChunk.map(node => stringifyNode(node, context)).join('')
10185:         ).replace(expReplaceRE, `" + $1 + "`),
10186:         // the 2nd argument indicates the number of DOM nodes this static vnode
10187:         // will insert / hydrate
10188:         String(currentChunk.length)
10189:       ])
10190:       // replace the first node's hoisted expression with the static vnode call
10191:       replaceHoist(currentChunk[0], staticCall, context)
10192: 
10193:       if (currentChunk.length > 1) {
10194:         for (let i = 1; i < currentChunk.length; i++) {
10195:           // for the merged nodes, set their hoisted expression to null
10196:           replaceHoist(currentChunk[i], null, context)
10197:         }
10198: 
10199:         // also remove merged nodes from children
10200:         const deleteCount = currentChunk.length - 1
10201:         children.splice(currentIndex - currentChunk.length + 1, deleteCount)
10202:         return deleteCount
10203:       }
10204:     }
10205:     return 0
10206:   }
10207: 
10208:   let i = 0
10209:   for (; i < children.length; i++) {
10210:     const child = children[i]
10211:     const hoisted = getHoistedNode(child)
10212:     if (hoisted) {
10213:       // presence of hoisted means child must be a stringifiable node
10214:       const node = child
10215:       const result = analyzeNode(node)
10216:       if (result) {
10217:         // node is stringifiable, record state
10218:         nc += result[0]
10219:         ec += result[1]
10220:         currentChunk.push(node)
10221:         continue
10222:       }
10223:     }
10224:     // we only reach here if we ran into a node that is not stringifiable
10225:     // check if currently analyzed nodes meet criteria for stringification.
10226:     // adjust iteration index
10227:     i -= stringifyCurrentChunk(i)
10228:     // reset state
10229:     nc = 0
10230:     ec = 0
10231:     currentChunk.length = 0
10232:   }
10233:   // in case the last node was also stringifiable
10234:   stringifyCurrentChunk(i)
10235: }
10236: 
10237: const getHoistedNode = (node) =>
10238:   ((node.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT && node.tagType === ElementTypes.ELEMENT) ||
10239:     node.type == NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL) &&
10240:   node.codegenNode &&
10241:   node.codegenNode.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION &&
10242:   node.codegenNode.hoisted
10243: 
10244: const dataAriaRE = /^(data|aria)-/
10245: const isStringifiableAttr = (name, ns) => {
10246:   return (
10247:     (ns === DOMNamespaces.HTML
10248:       ? isKnownHtmlAttr(name)
10249:       : ns === DOMNamespaces.SVG
10250:       ? isKnownSvgAttr(name)
10251:       : false) || dataAriaRE.test(name)
10252:   )
10253: }
10254: 
10255: const replaceHoist = (node,replacement,context) => {
10256:   const hoistToReplace = node.codegenNode.hoisted
10257:   context.hoists[context.hoists.indexOf(hoistToReplace)] = replacement
10258: }
10259: 
10260: const isNonStringifiable = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap(
10261:   `caption,thead,tr,th,tbody,td,tfoot,colgroup,col`
10262: )
10263: 
10264: /**
10265:  * for a hoisted node, analyze it and return:
10266:  * - false: bailed (contains non-stringifiable props or runtime constant)
10267:  * - [nc, ec] where
10268:  *   - nc is the number of nodes inside
10269:  *   - ec is the number of element with bindings inside
10270:  */
10271: function analyzeNode(node) {
10272:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT && isNonStringifiable(node.tag)) {
10273:     return false
10274:   }
10275: 
10276:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL) {
10277:     return [1, 0]
10278:   }
10279: 
10280:   let nc = 1 // node count
10281:   let ec = node.props.length > 0 ? 1 : 0 // element w/ binding count
10282:   let bailed = false
10283:   const bail = () => {
10284:     bailed = true
10285:     return false
10286:   }
10287: 
10288:   // TODO: check for cases where using innerHTML will result in different
10289:   // output compared to imperative node insertions.
10290:   // probably only need to check for most common case
10291:   // i.e. non-phrasing-content tags inside `<p>`
10292:   function walk(node) {
10293:     for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
10294:       const p = node.props[i]
10295:       // bail on non-attr bindings
10296:       if (
10297:         p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE &&
10298:         !isStringifiableAttr(p.name, node.ns)
10299:       ) {
10300:         return bail()
10301:       }
10302:       if (p.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE && p.name === 'bind') {
10303:         // bail on non-attr bindings
10304:         if (
10305:           p.arg &&
10306:           (p.arg.type === NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION ||
10307:             (p.arg.isStatic && !isStringifiableAttr(p.arg.content, node.ns)))
10308:         ) {
10309:           return bail()
10310:         }
10311:         if (
10312:           p.exp &&
10313:           (p.exp.type === NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION ||
10314:             p.exp.constType < ConstantTypes.CAN_STRINGIFY)
10315:         ) {
10316:           return bail()
10317:         }
10318:       }
10319:     }
10320:     for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
10321:       nc++
10322:       const child = node.children[i]
10323:       if (child.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT) {
10324:         if (child.props.length > 0) {
10325:           ec++
10326:         }
10327:         walk(child)
10328:         if (bailed) {
10329:           return false
10330:         }
10331:       }
10332:     }
10333:     return true
10334:   }
10335: 
10336:   return walk(node) ? [nc, ec] : false
10337: }
10338: 
10339: function stringifyNode(node, context) {
10340:   if (isString(node)) {
10341:     return node
10342:   }
10343:   if (isSymbol(node)) {
10344:     return ``
10345:   }
10346:   switch (node.type) {
10347:     case NodeTypes.ELEMENT:
10348:       return stringifyElement(node, context)
10349:     case NodeTypes.TEXT:
10350:       return escapeHtml(node.content)
10351:     case NodeTypes.COMMENT:
10352:       return `<!--${escapeHtml(node.content)}-->`
10353:     case NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION:
10354:       return escapeHtml(toDisplayString(evaluateConstant(node.content)))
10355:     case NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION:
10356:       return escapeHtml(evaluateConstant(node))
10357:     case NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL:
10358:       return stringifyNode(node.content, context)
10359:     default:
10360:       // static trees will not contain if/for nodes
10361:       return ''
10362:   }
10363: }
10364: 
10365: function stringifyElement(node, context) {
10366:   let res = `<${node.tag}`
10367:   for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
10368:     const p = node.props[i]
10369:     if (p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE) {
10370:       res += ` ${p.name}`
10371:       if (p.value) {
10372:         res += `="${escapeHtml(p.value.content)}"`
10373:       }
10374:     } else if (p.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE && p.name === 'bind') {
10375:       const exp = p.exp
10376:       if (exp.content[0] === '_') {
10377:         // internally generated string constant references
10378:         // e.g. imported URL strings via compiler-sfc transformAssetUrl plugin
10379:         res += ` ${p.arg.content}="__VUE_EXP_START__${
10380:           exp.content
10381:         }__VUE_EXP_END__"`
10382:         continue
10383:       }
10384:       // constant v-bind, e.g. :foo="1"
10385:       let evaluated = evaluateConstant(exp)
10386:       if (evaluated != null) {
10387:         const arg = p.arg && p.arg.content
10388:         if (arg === 'class') {
10389:           evaluated = normalizeClass(evaluated)
10390:         } else if (arg === 'style') {
10391:           evaluated = stringifyStyle(normalizeStyle(evaluated))
10392:         }
10393:         res += ` ${p.arg.content}="${escapeHtml(evaluated)}"`
10394:       }
10395:     }
10396:   }
10397:   if (context.scopeId) {
10398:     res += ` ${context.scopeId}`
10399:   }
10400:   res += `>`
10401:   for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
10402:     res += stringifyNode(node.children[i], context)
10403:   }
10404:   if (!isVoidTag(node.tag)) {
10405:     res += `</${node.tag}>`
10406:   }
10407:   return res
10408: }
10409: 
10410: // __UNSAFE__
10411: // Reason: eval.
10412: // It's technically safe to eval because only constant expressions are possible
10413: // here, e.g. `{{ 1 }}` or `{{ 'foo' }}`
10414: // in addition, constant exps bail on presence of parens so you can't even
10415: // run JSFuck in here. But we mark it unsafe for security review purposes.
10416: // (see compiler-core/src/transformExpressions)
10417: function evaluateConstant(exp) {
10418:   if (exp.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION) {
10419:     return new Function(`return ${exp.content}`)()
10420:   } else {
10421:     // compound
10422:     let res = ``
10423:     exp.children.forEach(c => {
10424:       if (isString(c) || isSymbol(c)) {
10425:         return
10426:       }
10427:       if (c.type === NodeTypes.TEXT) {
10428:         res += c.content
10429:       } else if (c.type === NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION) {
10430:         res += toDisplayString(evaluateConstant(c.content))
10431:       } else {
10432:         res += evaluateConstant(c)
10433:       }
10434:     })
10435:     return res
10436:   }
10437: }
10438:

   18: function syntaxHighlight(json) {
   19:   if (typeof json != 'string') {
   20:     json = JSON.stringify(json, undefined, 2)
   21:   }
   22:   json = json.replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;')
   23:   return json.replace(
   24:     /("(\\u[a-zA-Z0-9]{4}|\\[^u]|[^\\"])*"(\s*:)?|\b(true|false|null)\b|-?\d+(?:\.\d*)?(?:[eE][+\-]?\d+)?)/g,
   25:     function (match) {
   26:       var cls = 'number'
   27:       if (/^"/.test(match)) {
   28:         if (/:$/.test(match)) {
   29:           cls = 'key'
   30:         } else {
   31:           cls = 'string'
   32:         }
   33:       } else if (/true|false/.test(match)) {
   34:         cls = 'boolean'
   35:       } else if (/null/.test(match)) {
   36:         cls = 'null'
   37:       }
   38:       return '<span class="' + cls + '">' + match + '</span>'
   39:     }
   40:   )
   41: }

  288: 
  289: function advancePositionWithMutation(pos, source, numberOfCharacters = source.length) {
  290:   let linesCount = 0
  291:   let lastNewLinePos = -1
  292:   for (let i = 0; i < numberOfCharacters; i++) {
  293:     if (source.charCodeAt(i) === 10 /* newline char code */) {
  294:       linesCount++
  295:       lastNewLinePos = i
  296:     }
  297:   }
  298: 
  299:   pos.offset += numberOfCharacters
  300:   pos.line += linesCount
  301:   pos.column =
  302:     lastNewLinePos === -1
  303:       ? pos.column + numberOfCharacters
  304:       : numberOfCharacters - lastNewLinePos
  305: 
  306:   return pos
  307: }
  308: 
  309: function advancePositionWithClone(
  310:   pos,
  311:   source,
  312:   numberOfCharacters = source.length
  313: ) {
  314:   return advancePositionWithMutation(
  315:     extend({}, pos),
  316:     source,
  317:     numberOfCharacters
  318:   )
  319: }
  320: 
  321: 
  322: function advanceBy(context, numberOfCharacters) {
  323:   const { source } = context
  324:   advancePositionWithMutation(context, source, numberOfCharacters)
  325:   context.source = source.slice(numberOfCharacters)
  326: }
  327: 
  328: function advanceSpaces(context) {
  329:   const match = /^[\t\r\n\f ]+/.exec(context.source)
  330:   if (match) {
  331:     advanceBy(context, match[0].length)
  332:   }
  333: }
  334: 
  335: function getNewPosition(context, start, numberOfCharacters) {
  336:   return advancePositionWithClone(
  337:     start,
  338:     context.originalSource.slice(start.offset, numberOfCharacters),
  339:     numberOfCharacters
  340:   )
  341: }

  351: function isEnd(context, mode, ancestors) {
  352:   const s = context.source
  353: 
  354:   switch (mode) {
  355:     case TextModes.DATA:
  356:       if (startsWith(s, '</')) {
  357:         // TODO: probably bad performance
  358:         for (let i = ancestors.length - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
  359:           if (startsWithEndTagOpen(s, ancestors[i].tag)) {
  360:             return true
  361:           }
  362:         }
  363:       }
  364:       break
  365: 
  366:     case TextModes.RCDATA:
  367:     case TextModes.RAWTEXT: {
  368:       const parent = last(ancestors)
  369:       if (parent && startsWithEndTagOpen(s, parent.tag)) {
  370:         return true
  371:       }
  372:       break
  373:     }
  374: 
  375:     case TextModes.CDATA:
  376:       if (startsWith(s, ']]>')) {
  377:         return true
  378:       }
  379:       break
  380:   }
  381: 
  382:   return !s
  383: }
  384: 
  385: function startsWithEndTagOpen(source, tag) {
  386:   return (
  387:     startsWith(source, '</') &&
  388:     source.slice(2, 2 + tag.length).toLowerCase() === tag.toLowerCase() &&
  389:     /[\t\r\n\f />]/.test(source[2 + tag.length] || '>')
  390:   )
  391: }
  392: 
  393: const cacheStringFunction = (fn) => {
  394:   const cache = Object.create(null)
  395:   return ((str) => {
  396:     const hit = cache[str]
  397:     return hit || (cache[str] = fn(str))
  398:   })
  399: }
  400: 
  401: const camelizeRE = /-(\w)/g
  402: const camelize = cacheStringFunction((str) => {
  403:   return str.replace(camelizeRE, (_, c) => (c ? c.toUpperCase() : ''))
  404: })
  405: 
  406: const hyphenateRE = /\B([A-Z])/g
  407: const hyphenate = cacheStringFunction((str) =>
  408:   str.replace(hyphenateRE, '-$1').toLowerCase()
  409: )
  410: const capitalize = cacheStringFunction(
  411:   (str) => str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1)
  412: )
  413: const toHandlerKey = cacheStringFunction((str) => str ? `on${capitalize(str)}` : ``)
  414: 
  415: const isBuiltInType = (tag, expected) => tag === expected || tag === hyphenate(expected)
  416: 
  417: function isCoreComponent(tag) {
  418:   if (isBuiltInType(tag, 'Teleport')) {
  419:     return TELEPORT
  420:   } else if (isBuiltInType(tag, 'Suspense')) {
  421:     return SUSPENSE
  422:   } else if (isBuiltInType(tag, 'KeepAlive')) {
  423:     return KEEP_ALIVE
  424:   } else if (isBuiltInType(tag, 'BaseTransition')) {
  425:     return BASE_TRANSITION
  426:   }

  433: function isComponent(tag, props, context) {
  434:   const options = context.options
  435:   if (options.isCustomElement(tag)) {
  436:     return false
  437:   }
  438:   if (
  439:     tag === 'component' ||
  440:     /^[A-Z]/.test(tag) ||
  441:     isCoreComponent(tag) ||
  442:     (options.isBuiltInComponent && options.isBuiltInComponent(tag)) ||
  443:     (options.isNativeTag && !options.isNativeTag(tag))
  444:   ) {
  445:     return true
  446:   }
  447:   // at this point the tag should be a native tag, but check for potential "is"
  448:   // casting
  449:   for (let i = 0; i < props.length; i++) {
  450:     const p = props[i]
  451:     if (p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE) {
  452:       if (p.name === 'is' && p.value) {
  453:         if (p.value.content.startsWith('vue:')) {
  454:           return true
  455:         }
  456:       }
  457:     } else {
  458:       // directive
  459:       // v-is (TODO Deprecate)
  460:       if (p.name === 'is') {
  461:         return true
  462:       }
  463:     }
  464:   }
  465: }
  466: function pushNode(nodes, node) {
  467:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.TEXT) {
  468:     const prev = last(nodes)
  469:     // Merge if both this and the previous node are text and those are
  470:     // consecutive. This happens for cases like "a < b".
  471:     if (
  472:       prev &&
  473:       prev.type === NodeTypes.TEXT &&
  474:       prev.loc.end.offset === node.loc.start.offset
  475:     ) {
  476:       prev.content += node.content
  477:       prev.loc.end = node.loc.end
  478:       prev.loc.source += node.loc.source
  479:       return
  480:     }
  481:   }
  482: 
  483:   nodes.push(node)
  484: }

  507: function findDir(node, name, allowEmpty = false) {
  508:   for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
  509:     const p = node.props[i]
  510:     if (
  511:       p.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE &&
  512:       (allowEmpty || p.exp) &&
  513:       (isString(name) ? p.name === name : name.test(p.name))
  514:     ) {
  515:       return p
  516:     }
  517:   }
  518: }

  520: function findProp(node, name, dynamicOnly = false, allowEmpty = false) {
  521:   for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
  522:     const p = node.props[i]
  523:     if (p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE) {
  524:       if (dynamicOnly) continue
  525:       if (p.name === name && (p.value || allowEmpty)) {
  526:         return p
  527:       }
  528:     } else if (
  529:       p.name === 'bind' &&
  530:       (p.exp || allowEmpty) &&
  531:       isStaticArgOf(p.arg, name)
  532:     ) {
  533:       return p
  534:     }
  535:   }
  536: }
  537: 
  538: const isStaticExp = (p) => p.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION && p.isStatic
  539: 
  540: function isStaticArgOf(arg, name) {
  541:   return !!(arg && isStaticExp(arg) && arg.content === name)
  542: }
  543:

  548: function getMemoedVNodeCall(node) {
  549:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.JS_CALL_EXPRESSION && node.callee === WITH_MEMO) {
  550:     return node.arguments[1].returns
  551:   } else {
  552:     return node

  556: function getInnerRange(loc, offset, length) {
  557:   const source = loc.source.slice(offset, offset + length)
  558:   const newLoc = {
  559:     source,
  560:     start: advancePositionWithClone(loc.start, loc.source, offset),
  561:     end: loc.end
  562:   }
  563: 
  564:   if (length != null) {
  565:     newLoc.end = advancePositionWithClone(
  566:       loc.start,
  567:       loc.source,
  568:       offset + length
  569:     )
  570:   }
  571: 
  572:   return newLoc
  573: }

  681: 
  682: /**
  683:  * Patch flags are optimization hints generated by the compiler.
  684:  * when a block with dynamicChildren is encountered during diff, the algorithm
  685:  * enters "optimized mode". In this mode, we know that the vdom is produced by
  686:  * a render function generated by the compiler, so the algorithm only needs to
  687:  * handle updates explicitly marked by these patch flags.
  688:  *
  689:  * Patch flags can be combined using the | bitwise operator and can be checked
  690:  * using the & operator, e.g.
  691:  *
  692:  * ```js
  693:  * const flag = TEXT | CLASS
  694:  * if (flag & TEXT) { ... }
  695:  * ```
  696:  *
  697:  * Check the `patchElement` function in '../../runtime-core/src/renderer.ts' to see how the
  698:  * flags are handled during diff.
  699:  */
  700: const PatchFlags = {
  701:   /**
  702:    * Indicates an element with dynamic textContent (children fast path)
  703:    */
  704:   TEXT: 1,
  705: 
  706:   /**
  707:    * Indicates an element with dynamic class binding.
  708:    */
  709:   CLASS: 1 << 1,
  710: 
  711:   /**
  712:    * Indicates an element with dynamic style
  713:    * The compiler pre-compiles static string styles into static objects
  714:    * + detects and hoists inline static objects
  715:    * e.g. `style="color: red"` and `:style="{ color: 'red' }"` both get hoisted
  716:    * as:
  717:    * ```js
  718:    * const style = { color: 'red' }
  719:    * render() { return e('div', { style }) }
  720:    * ```
  721:    */
  722:   STYLE: 1 << 2,
  723: 
  724:   /**
  725:    * Indicates an element that has non-class/style dynamic props.
  726:    * Can also be on a component that has any dynamic props (includes
  727:    * class/style). when this flag is present, the vnode also has a dynamicProps
  728:    * array that contains the keys of the props that may change so the runtime
  729:    * can diff them faster (without having to worry about removed props)
  730:    */
  731:   PROPS: 1 << 3,
  732: 
  733:   /**
  734:    * Indicates an element with props with dynamic keys. When keys change, a full
  735:    * diff is always needed to remove the old key. This flag is mutually
  736:    * exclusive with CLASS, STYLE and PROPS.
  737:    */
  738:   FULL_PROPS: 1 << 4,
  739: 
  740:   /**
  741:    * Indicates an element with event listeners (which need to be attached
  742:    * during hydration)
  743:    */
  744:   HYDRATE_EVENTS: 1 << 5,
  745: 
  746:   /**
  747:    * Indicates a fragment whose children order doesn't change.
  748:    */
  749:   STABLE_FRAGMENT: 1 << 6,
  750: 
  751:   /**
  752:    * Indicates a fragment with keyed or partially keyed children
  753:    */
  754:   KEYED_FRAGMENT: 1 << 7,
  755: 
  756:   /**
  757:    * Indicates a fragment with unkeyed children.
  758:    */
  759:   UNKEYED_FRAGMENT: 1 << 8,
  760: 
  761:   /**
  762:    * Indicates an element that only needs non-props patching, e.g. ref or
  763:    * directives (onVnodeXXX hooks). since every patched vnode checks for refs
  764:    * and onVnodeXXX hooks, it simply marks the vnode so that a parent block
  765:    * will track it.
  766:    */
  767:   NEED_PATCH: 1 << 9,
  768: 
  769:   /**
  770:    * Indicates a component with dynamic slots (e.g. slot that references a v-for
  771:    * iterated value, or dynamic slot names).
  772:    * Components with this flag are always force updated.
  773:    */
  774:   DYNAMIC_SLOTS: 1 << 10,
  775: 
  776:   /**
  777:    * Indicates a fragment that was created only because the user has placed
  778:    * comments at the root level of a template. This is a dev-only flag since
  779:    * comments are stripped in production.
  780:    */
  781:   DEV_ROOT_FRAGMENT: 1 << 11,
  782: 
  783:   /**
  784:    * SPECIAL FLAGS -------------------------------------------------------------
  785:    * Special flags are negative integers. They are never matched against using
  786:    * bitwise operators (bitwise matching should only happen in branches where
  787:    * patchFlag > 0), and are mutually exclusive. When checking for a special
  788:    * flag, simply check patchFlag === FLAG.
  789:    */
  790: 
  791:   /**
  792:    * Indicates a hoisted static vnode. This is a hint for hydration to skip
  793:    * the entire sub tree since static content never needs to be updated.
  794:    */
  795:   HOISTED: -1,
  796:   /**
  797:    * A special flag that indicates that the diffing algorithm should bail out
  798:    * of optimized mode. For example, on block fragments created by renderSlot()
  799:    * when encountering non-compiler generated slots (i.e. manually written
  800:    * render functions, which should always be fully diffed)
  801:    * OR manually cloneVNodes
  802:    */
  803:   BAIL: -2
  804: }
  805: 
  806: /**
  807:  * dev only flag -> name mapping
  808:  */
  809: const PatchFlagNames = {
  810:   [PatchFlags.TEXT]: `TEXT`,
  811:   [PatchFlags.CLASS]: `CLASS`,
  812:   [PatchFlags.STYLE]: `STYLE`,
  813:   [PatchFlags.PROPS]: `PROPS`,
  814:   [PatchFlags.FULL_PROPS]: `FULL_PROPS`,
  815:   [PatchFlags.HYDRATE_EVENTS]: `HYDRATE_EVENTS`,
  816:   [PatchFlags.STABLE_FRAGMENT]: `STABLE_FRAGMENT`,
  817:   [PatchFlags.KEYED_FRAGMENT]: `KEYED_FRAGMENT`,
  818:   [PatchFlags.UNKEYED_FRAGMENT]: `UNKEYED_FRAGMENT`,
  819:   [PatchFlags.NEED_PATCH]: `NEED_PATCH`,
  820:   [PatchFlags.DYNAMIC_SLOTS]: `DYNAMIC_SLOTS`,
  821:   [PatchFlags.DEV_ROOT_FRAGMENT]: `DEV_ROOT_FRAGMENT`,
  822:   [PatchFlags.HOISTED]: `HOISTED`,
  823:   [PatchFlags.BAIL]: `BAIL`
  824: }
  825: 
  826: function genFlagText(flag, names = PatchFlagNames) {
  827:   if (isArray(flag)) {
  828:     let f = 0
  829:     flag.forEach(ff => {
  830:       f |= ff
  831:     })
  832:     return `${f} /* ${flag.map(f => names[f]).join(', ')} */`
  833:   } else {
  834:     return `${flag} /* ${names[flag]} */`
  835:   }
  836: }

  838: const propsHelperSet = new Set([NORMALIZE_PROPS, GUARD_REACTIVE_PROPS])
  839: 
  840: function getUnnormalizedProps(props, callPath = []) {
  841:   if (
  842:     props &&
  843:     !isString(props) &&
  844:     props.type === NodeTypes.JS_CALL_EXPRESSION
  845:   ) {
  846:     const callee = props.callee
  847:     if (!isString(callee) && propsHelperSet.has(callee)) {
  848:       return getUnnormalizedProps(
  849:         props.arguments[0],
  850:         callPath.concat(props)
  851:       )
  852:     }
  853:   }
  854:   return [props, callPath]
  855: }
