10130:  const StringifyThresholds = {
10131:    ELEMENT_WITH_BINDING_COUNT: 5,
10132:    NODE_COUNT: 20
10133: }
10134: 
10135: /**
10136:  * Regex for replacing placeholders for embedded constant variables
10137:  * (e.g. import URL string constants generated by compiler-sfc)
10138:  */
10139: const expReplaceRE = /__VUE_EXP_START__(.*?)__VUE_EXP_END__/g
10140: 
10141: /**
10142:  * Turn eligible hoisted static trees into stringified static nodes, e.g.
10143:  *
10144:  * ```js
10145:  * const _hoisted_1 = createStaticVNode(`<div class="foo">bar</div>`)
10146:  * ```
10147:  *
10148:  * A single static vnode can contain stringified content for **multiple**
10149:  * consecutive nodes (element and plain text), called a "chunk".
10150:  * `@vue/runtime-dom` will create the content via innerHTML in a hidden
10151:  * container element and insert all the nodes in place. The call must also
10152:  * provide the number of nodes contained in the chunk so that during hydration
10153:  * we can know how many nodes the static vnode should adopt.
10154:  *
10155:  * The optimization scans a children list that contains hoisted nodes, and
10156:  * tries to find the largest chunk of consecutive hoisted nodes before running
10157:  * into a non-hoisted node or the end of the list. A chunk is then converted
10158:  * into a single static vnode and replaces the hoisted expression of the first
10159:  * node in the chunk. Other nodes in the chunk are considered "merged" and
10160:  * therefore removed from both the hoist list and the children array.
10161:  *
10162:  * This optimization is only performed in Node.js.
10163:  */
10164: const stringifyStatic = (children, context, parent) => {
10165:   // bail stringification for slot content
10166:   if (context.scopes.vSlot > 0) {
10167:     return
10168:   }
10169: 
10170:   let nc = 0 // current node count
10171:   let ec = 0 // current element with binding count
10172:   const currentChunk = []
10173: 
10174:   logg(`stringifyStatic - children.length = ${children.length}`)
10175:   const stringifyCurrentChunk = (currentIndex) => {
10176:     if (
10177:       nc >= StringifyThresholds.NODE_COUNT ||
10178:       ec >= StringifyThresholds.ELEMENT_WITH_BINDING_COUNT
10179:     ) {
10180:       logg(`stringifyCurrentChunk - index = ${currentIndex}`)
10181:       // combine all currently eligible nodes into a single static vnode call
10182:       const staticCall = createCallExpression(context.helper(CREATE_STATIC), [
10183:         JSON.stringify(
10184:           currentChunk.map(node => stringifyNode(node, context)).join('')
10185:         ).replace(expReplaceRE, `" + $1 + "`),
10186:         // the 2nd argument indicates the number of DOM nodes this static vnode
10187:         // will insert / hydrate
10188:         String(currentChunk.length)
10189:       ])
10190:       // replace the first node's hoisted expression with the static vnode call
10191:       replaceHoist(currentChunk[0], staticCall, context)
10192: 
10193:       if (currentChunk.length > 1) {
10194:         for (let i = 1; i < currentChunk.length; i++) {
10195:           // for the merged nodes, set their hoisted expression to null
10196:           replaceHoist(currentChunk[i], null, context)
10197:         }
10198: 
10199:         // also remove merged nodes from children
10200:         const deleteCount = currentChunk.length - 1
10201:         children.splice(currentIndex - currentChunk.length + 1, deleteCount)
10202:         return deleteCount
10203:       }
10204:     }
10205:     return 0
10206:   }
10207: 
10208:   let i = 0
10209:   for (; i < children.length; i++) {
10210:     const child = children[i]
10211:     const hoisted = getHoistedNode(child)
10212:     if (hoisted) {
10213:       // presence of hoisted means child must be a stringifiable node
10214:       const node = child
10215:       const result = analyzeNode(node)
10216:       if (result) {
10217:         // node is stringifiable, record state
10218:         nc += result[0]
10219:         ec += result[1]
10220:         currentChunk.push(node)
10221:         continue
10222:       }
10223:     }
10224:     // we only reach here if we ran into a node that is not stringifiable
10225:     // check if currently analyzed nodes meet criteria for stringification.
10226:     // adjust iteration index
10227:     i -= stringifyCurrentChunk(i)
10228:     // reset state
10229:     nc = 0
10230:     ec = 0
10231:     currentChunk.length = 0
10232:   }
10233:   // in case the last node was also stringifiable
10234:   stringifyCurrentChunk(i)
10235: }
10236: 
10237: const getHoistedNode = (node) =>
10238:   ((node.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT && node.tagType === ElementTypes.ELEMENT) ||
10239:     node.type == NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL) &&
10240:   node.codegenNode &&
10241:   node.codegenNode.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION &&
10242:   node.codegenNode.hoisted
10243: 
10244: const dataAriaRE = /^(data|aria)-/
10245: const isStringifiableAttr = (name, ns) => {
10246:   return (
10247:     (ns === DOMNamespaces.HTML
10248:       ? isKnownHtmlAttr(name)
10249:       : ns === DOMNamespaces.SVG
10250:       ? isKnownSvgAttr(name)
10251:       : false) || dataAriaRE.test(name)
10252:   )
10253: }
10254: 
10255: const replaceHoist = (node,replacement,context) => {
10256:   const hoistToReplace = node.codegenNode.hoisted
10257:   context.hoists[context.hoists.indexOf(hoistToReplace)] = replacement
10258: }
10259: 
10260: const isNonStringifiable = /*#__PURE__*/ makeMap(
10261:   `caption,thead,tr,th,tbody,td,tfoot,colgroup,col`
10262: )
10263: 
10264: /**
10265:  * for a hoisted node, analyze it and return:
10266:  * - false: bailed (contains non-stringifiable props or runtime constant)
10267:  * - [nc, ec] where
10268:  *   - nc is the number of nodes inside
10269:  *   - ec is the number of element with bindings inside
10270:  */
10271: function analyzeNode(node) {
10272:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT && isNonStringifiable(node.tag)) {
10273:     return false
10274:   }
10275: 
10276:   if (node.type === NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL) {
10277:     return [1, 0]
10278:   }
10279: 
10280:   let nc = 1 // node count
10281:   let ec = node.props.length > 0 ? 1 : 0 // element w/ binding count
10282:   let bailed = false
10283:   const bail = () => {
10284:     bailed = true
10285:     return false
10286:   }
10287: 
10288:   // TODO: check for cases where using innerHTML will result in different
10289:   // output compared to imperative node insertions.
10290:   // probably only need to check for most common case
10291:   // i.e. non-phrasing-content tags inside `<p>`
10292:   function walk(node) {
10293:     for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
10294:       const p = node.props[i]
10295:       // bail on non-attr bindings
10296:       if (
10297:         p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE &&
10298:         !isStringifiableAttr(p.name, node.ns)
10299:       ) {
10300:         return bail()
10301:       }
10302:       if (p.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE && p.name === 'bind') {
10303:         // bail on non-attr bindings
10304:         if (
10305:           p.arg &&
10306:           (p.arg.type === NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION ||
10307:             (p.arg.isStatic && !isStringifiableAttr(p.arg.content, node.ns)))
10308:         ) {
10309:           return bail()
10310:         }
10311:         if (
10312:           p.exp &&
10313:           (p.exp.type === NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION ||
10314:             p.exp.constType < ConstantTypes.CAN_STRINGIFY)
10315:         ) {
10316:           return bail()
10317:         }
10318:       }
10319:     }
10320:     for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
10321:       nc++
10322:       const child = node.children[i]
10323:       if (child.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT) {
10324:         if (child.props.length > 0) {
10325:           ec++
10326:         }
10327:         walk(child)
10328:         if (bailed) {
10329:           return false
10330:         }
10331:       }
10332:     }
10333:     return true
10334:   }
10335: 
10336:   return walk(node) ? [nc, ec] : false
10337: }
10338: 
10339: function stringifyNode(node, context) {
10340:   if (isString(node)) {
10341:     return node
10342:   }
10343:   if (isSymbol(node)) {
10344:     return ``
10345:   }
10346:   switch (node.type) {
10347:     case NodeTypes.ELEMENT:
10348:       return stringifyElement(node, context)
10349:     case NodeTypes.TEXT:
10350:       return escapeHtml(node.content)
10351:     case NodeTypes.COMMENT:
10352:       return `<!--${escapeHtml(node.content)}-->`
10353:     case NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION:
10354:       return escapeHtml(toDisplayString(evaluateConstant(node.content)))
10355:     case NodeTypes.COMPOUND_EXPRESSION:
10356:       return escapeHtml(evaluateConstant(node))
10357:     case NodeTypes.TEXT_CALL:
10358:       return stringifyNode(node.content, context)
10359:     default:
10360:       // static trees will not contain if/for nodes
10361:       return ''
10362:   }
10363: }
10364: 
10365: function stringifyElement(node, context) {
10366:   let res = `<${node.tag}`
10367:   for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
10368:     const p = node.props[i]
10369:     if (p.type === NodeTypes.ATTRIBUTE) {
10370:       res += ` ${p.name}`
10371:       if (p.value) {
10372:         res += `="${escapeHtml(p.value.content)}"`
10373:       }
10374:     } else if (p.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE && p.name === 'bind') {
10375:       const exp = p.exp
10376:       if (exp.content[0] === '_') {
10377:         // internally generated string constant references
10378:         // e.g. imported URL strings via compiler-sfc transformAssetUrl plugin
10379:         res += ` ${p.arg.content}="__VUE_EXP_START__${
10380:           exp.content
10381:         }__VUE_EXP_END__"`
10382:         continue
10383:       }
10384:       // constant v-bind, e.g. :foo="1"
10385:       let evaluated = evaluateConstant(exp)
10386:       if (evaluated != null) {
10387:         const arg = p.arg && p.arg.content
10388:         if (arg === 'class') {
10389:           evaluated = normalizeClass(evaluated)
10390:         } else if (arg === 'style') {
10391:           evaluated = stringifyStyle(normalizeStyle(evaluated))
10392:         }
10393:         res += ` ${p.arg.content}="${escapeHtml(evaluated)}"`
10394:       }
10395:     }
10396:   }
10397:   if (context.scopeId) {
10398:     res += ` ${context.scopeId}`
10399:   }
10400:   res += `>`
10401:   for (let i = 0; i < node.children.length; i++) {
10402:     res += stringifyNode(node.children[i], context)
10403:   }
10404:   if (!isVoidTag(node.tag)) {
10405:     res += `</${node.tag}>`
10406:   }
10407:   return res
10408: }
10409: 
10410: // __UNSAFE__
10411: // Reason: eval.
10412: // It's technically safe to eval because only constant expressions are possible
10413: // here, e.g. `{{ 1 }}` or `{{ 'foo' }}`
10414: // in addition, constant exps bail on presence of parens so you can't even
10415: // run JSFuck in here. But we mark it unsafe for security review purposes.
10416: // (see compiler-core/src/transformExpressions)
10417: function evaluateConstant(exp) {
10418:   if (exp.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION) {
10419:     return new Function(`return ${exp.content}`)()
10420:   } else {
10421:     // compound
10422:     let res = ``
10423:     exp.children.forEach(c => {
10424:       if (isString(c) || isSymbol(c)) {
10425:         return
10426:       }
10427:       if (c.type === NodeTypes.TEXT) {
10428:         res += c.content
10429:       } else if (c.type === NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION) {
10430:         res += toDisplayString(evaluateConstant(c.content))
10431:       } else {
10432:         res += evaluateConstant(c)
10433:       }
10434:     })
10435:     return res
10436:   }
10437: }

10488: /**
10489:  * Utility for rewriting `export default` in a script block into a variable
10490:  * declaration so that we can inject things into it
10491:  */
10492: function rewriteDefault(input, as, parserPlugins) {
10493:   if (!hasDefaultExport(input)) {
10494:     return input + `\nconst ${as} = {}`
10495:   }
10496: 
10497:   let replaced
10498: 
10499:   const classMatch = input.match(exportDefaultClassRE)
10500:   if (classMatch) {
10501:     replaced =
10502:       input.replace(exportDefaultClassRE, '$1class $2') +
10503:       `\nconst ${as} = ${classMatch[2]}`
10504:   } else {
10505:     replaced = input.replace(defaultExportRE, `$1const ${as} =`)
10506:   }
10507:   if (!hasDefaultExport(replaced)) {
10508:     return replaced
10509:   }
10510: 
10511:   // if the script somehow still contains `default export`, it probably has
10512:   // multi-line comments or template strings. fallback to a full parse.
10513:   const s = new MagicString(input)
10514:   const ast = babelParser.parse(input, {
10515:     sourceType: 'module',
10516:     plugins: parserPlugins
10517:   }).program.body
10518:   ast.forEach(node => {
10519:     if (node.type === 'ExportDefaultDeclaration') {
10520:       s.overwrite(node.start, node.declaration.start, `const ${as} = `)
10521:     }
10522:     if (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration') {
10523:       node.specifiers.forEach(specifier => {
10524:         if (
10525:           specifier.type === 'ExportSpecifier' &&
10526:           specifier.exported.type === 'Identifier' &&
10527:           specifier.exported.name === 'default'
10528:         ) {
10529:           const end = specifier.end
10530:           s.overwrite(
10531:             specifier.start,
10532:             input.charAt(end) === ',' ? end + 1 : end,
10533:             ``
10534:           )
10535:           s.append(`\nconst ${as} = ${specifier.local.name}`)
10536:         }
10537:       })
10538:     }
10539:   })
10540:   return s.toString()
10541: }
10542: 
10543: function hasDefaultExport(input) {
10544:   return defaultExportRE.test(input) || namedDefaultExportRE.test(input)
10545: }
10546: const RT = (function() {
10547:   const CONVERT_SYMBOL = '$'
10548: const ESCAPE_SYMBOL = '$$'
10549: const shorthands = ['ref', 'computed', 'shallowRef', 'toRef', 'customRef']
10550: const transformCheckRE = /[^\w]\$(?:\$|ref|computed|shallowRef)?\s*(\(|\<)/
10551: 
10552: function shouldTransform(src) {
10553:   return transformCheckRE.test(src)
10554: }
10555: 
10556: function transform(
10557:   src,
10558:   {
10559:     filename,
10560:     sourceMap,
10561:     parserPlugins,
10562:     importHelpersFrom = 'vue'
10563:   } = {}
10564: ) {
10565:   const plugins = parserPlugins || []
10566:   if (filename) {
10567:     if (/\.tsx?$/.test(filename)) {
10568:       plugins.push('typescript')
10569:     }
10570:     if (filename.endsWith('x')) {
10571:       plugins.push('jsx')
10572:     }
10573:   }
10574: 
10575:   const ast = babelParser.parse(src, {
10576:     sourceType: 'module',
10577:     plugins
10578:   })
10579:   const s = new MagicString(src)
10580:   const res = transformAST(ast.program, s, 0)
10581: 
10582:   // inject helper imports
10583:   if (res.importedHelpers.length) {
10584:     s.prepend(
10585:       `import { ${res.importedHelpers
10586:         .map(h => `${h} as _${h}`)
10587:         .join(', ')} } from '${importHelpersFrom}'\n`
10588:     )
10589:   }
10590: 
10591:   return {
10592:     ...res,
10593:     code: s.toString(),
10594:     map: sourceMap
10595:       ? s.generateMap({
10596:           source: filename,
10597:           hires: true,
10598:           includeContent: true
10599:         })
10600:       : null
10601:   }
10602: }
10603: 
10604: function transformAST(
10605:   ast,
10606:   s,
10607:   offset = 0,
10608:   knownRefs,
10609:   knownProps
10610: ) {
10611:   let convertSymbol = CONVERT_SYMBOL
10612:   let escapeSymbol = ESCAPE_SYMBOL
10613: 
10614:   // macro import handling
10615:   for (const node of ast.body) {
10616:     if (
10617:       node.type === 'ImportDeclaration' &&
10618:       node.source.value === 'vue/macros'
10619:     ) {
10620:       // remove macro imports
10621:       s.remove(node.start + offset, node.end + offset)
10622:       // check aliasing
10623:       for (const specifier of node.specifiers) {
10624:         if (specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier') {
10625:           const imported = specifier.imported.name
10626:           const local = specifier.local.name
10627:           if (local !== imported) {
10628:             if (imported === ESCAPE_SYMBOL) {
10629:               escapeSymbol = local
10630:             } else if (imported === CONVERT_SYMBOL) {
10631:               convertSymbol = local
10632:             } else {
10633:               error(
10634:                 `macro imports for ref-creating methods do not support aliasing.`,
10635:                 specifier
10636:               )
10637:             }
10638:           }
10639:         }
10640:       }
10641:     }
10642:   }
10643: 
10644:   const importedHelpers = new Set()
10645:   const rootScope = {}
10646:   const scopeStack = [rootScope]
10647:   let currentScope = rootScope
10648:   let escapeScope // inside $$()
10649:   const excludedIds = new WeakSet()
10650:   const parentStack = []
10651:   const propsLocalToPublicMap = Object.create(null)
10652: 
10653:   if (knownRefs) {
10654:     for (const key of knownRefs) {
10655:       rootScope[key] = true
10656:     }
10657:   }
10658:   if (knownProps) {
10659:     for (const key in knownProps) {
10660:       const { local } = knownProps[key]
10661:       rootScope[local] = 'prop'
10662:       propsLocalToPublicMap[local] = key
10663:     }
10664:   }
10665: 
10666:   function isRefCreationCall(callee) {
10667:     if (callee === convertSymbol) {
10668:       return convertSymbol
10669:     }
10670:     if (callee[0] === '$' && shorthands.includes(callee.slice(1))) {
10671:       return callee
10672:     }
10673:     return false
10674:   }
10675: 
10676:   function error(msg, node) {
10677:     const e = new Error(msg)
10678:     e.node = node
10679:     throw e
10680:   }
10681: 
10682:   function helper(msg) {
10683:     importedHelpers.add(msg)
10684:     return `_${msg}`
10685:   }
10686: 
10687:   function registerBinding(id, isRef = false) {
10688:     excludedIds.add(id)
10689:     if (currentScope) {
10690:       currentScope[id.name] = isRef
10691:     } else {
10692:       error(
10693:         'registerBinding called without active scope, something is wrong.',
10694:         id
10695:       )
10696:     }
10697:   }
10698: 
10699:   const registerRefBinding = (id) => registerBinding(id, true)
10700: 
10701:   let tempVarCount = 0
10702:   function genTempVar() {
10703:     return `__$temp_${++tempVarCount}`
10704:   }
10705: 
10706:   function snip(nod) {
10707:     return s.original.slice(node.start + offset, node.end + offset)
10708:   }
10709: 
10710:   function walkScope(node, isRoot = false) {
10711:     for (const stmt of node.body) {
10712:       if (stmt.type === 'VariableDeclaration') {
10713:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt, isRoot)
10714:       } else if (
10715:         stmt.type === 'FunctionDeclaration' ||
10716:         stmt.type === 'ClassDeclaration'
10717:       ) {
10718:         if (stmt.declare || !stmt.id) continue
10719:         registerBinding(stmt.id)
10720:       } else if (
10721:         (stmt.type === 'ForOfStatement' || stmt.type === 'ForInStatement') &&
10722:         stmt.left.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
10723:       ) {
10724:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.left)
10725:       } else if (
10726:         stmt.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' &&
10727:         stmt.declaration &&
10728:         stmt.declaration.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
10729:       ) {
10730:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.declaration, isRoot)
10731:       } else if (
10732:         stmt.type === 'LabeledStatement' &&
10733:         stmt.body.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
10734:       ) {
10735:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.body, isRoot)
10736:       }
10737:     }
10738:   }
10739: 
10740:   function walkVariableDeclaration(stmt, isRoot = false) {
10741:     if (stmt.declare) {
10742:       return
10743:     }
10744:     for (const decl of stmt.declarations) {
10745:       let refCall
10746:       const isCall =
10747:         decl.init &&
10748:         decl.init.type === 'CallExpression' &&
10749:         decl.init.callee.type === 'Identifier'
10750:       if (
10751:         isCall &&
10752:         (refCall = isRefCreationCall(decl.init.callee.name))
10753:       ) {
10754:         processRefDeclaration(refCall, decl.id, decl.init)
10755:       } else {
10756:         const isProps =
10757:           isRoot && isCall && decl.init.callee.name === 'defineProps'
10758:         for (const id of extractIdentifiers(decl.id)) {
10759:           if (isProps) {
10760:             // for defineProps destructure, only exclude them since they
10761:             // are already passed in as knownProps
10762:             excludedIds.add(id)
10763:           } else {
10764:             registerBinding(id)
10765:           }
10766:         }
10767:       }
10768:     }
10769:   }
10770: 
10771:   function processRefDeclaration(method, id, call) {
10772:     excludedIds.add(call.callee)
10773:     if (method === convertSymbol) {
10774:       // $
10775:       // remove macro
10776:       s.remove(call.callee.start + offset, call.callee.end + offset)
10777:       if (id.type === 'Identifier') {
10778:         // single variable
10779:         registerRefBinding(id)
10780:       } else if (id.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
10781:         processRefObjectPattern(id, call)
10782:       } else if (id.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
10783:         processRefArrayPattern(id, call)
10784:       }
10785:     } else {
10786:       // shorthands
10787:       if (id.type === 'Identifier') {
10788:         registerRefBinding(id)
10789:         // replace call
10790:         s.overwrite(
10791:           call.start + offset,
10792:           call.start + method.length + offset,
10793:           helper(method.slice(1))
10794:         )
10795:       } else {
10796:         error(`${method}() cannot be used with destructure patterns.`, call)
10797:       }
10798:     }
10799:   }
10800: 
10801:   function processRefObjectPattern(pattern, call, tempVar, path = []) {
10802:     if (!tempVar) {
10803:       tempVar = genTempVar()
10804:       // const { x } = $(useFoo()) --> const __$temp_1 = useFoo()
10805:       s.overwrite(pattern.start + offset, pattern.end + offset, tempVar)
10806:     }
10807: 
10808:     for (const p of pattern.properties) {
10809:       let nameId
10810:       let key
10811:       let defaultValue
10812:       if (p.type === 'ObjectProperty') {
10813:         if (p.key.start === p.value.start) {
10814:           // shorthand { foo }
10815:           nameId = p.key
10816:           if (p.value.type === 'Identifier') {
10817:             // avoid shorthand value identifier from being processed
10818:             excludedIds.add(p.value)
10819:           } else if (
10820:             p.value.type === 'AssignmentPattern' &&
10821:             p.value.left.type === 'Identifier'
10822:           ) {
10823:             // { foo = 1 }
10824:             excludedIds.add(p.value.left)
10825:             defaultValue = p.value.right
10826:           }
10827:         } else {
10828:           key = p.computed ? p.key : p.key.name
10829:           if (p.value.type === 'Identifier') {
10830:             // { foo: bar }
10831:             nameId = p.value
10832:           } else if (p.value.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
10833:             processRefObjectPattern(p.value, call, tempVar, [...path, key])
10834:           } else if (p.value.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
10835:             processRefArrayPattern(p.value, call, tempVar, [...path, key])
10836:           } else if (p.value.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
10837:             if (p.value.left.type === 'Identifier') {
10838:               // { foo: bar = 1 }
10839:               nameId = p.value.left
10840:               defaultValue = p.value.right
10841:             } else if (p.value.left.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
10842:               processRefObjectPattern(p.value.left, call, tempVar, [
10843:                 ...path,
10844:                 [key, p.value.right]
10845:               ])
10846:             } else if (p.value.left.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
10847:               processRefArrayPattern(p.value.left, call, tempVar, [
10848:                 ...path,
10849:                 [key, p.value.right]
10850:               ])
10851:             } else {
10852:               // MemberExpression case is not possible here, ignore
10853:             }
10854:           }
10855:         }
10856:       } else {
10857:         // rest element { ...foo }
10858:         error(`reactivity destructure does not support rest elements.`, p)
10859:       }
10860:       if (nameId) {
10861:         registerRefBinding(nameId)
10862:         // inject toRef() after original replaced pattern
10863:         const source = pathToString(tempVar, path)
10864:         const keyStr = isString(key)
10865:           ? `'${key}'`
10866:           : key
10867:           ? snip(key)
10868:           : `'${nameId.name}'`
10869:         const defaultStr = defaultValue ? `, ${snip(defaultValue)}` : ``
10870:         s.appendLeft(
10871:           call.end + offset,
10872:           `,\n  ${nameId.name} = ${helper(
10873:             'toRef'
10874:           )}(${source}, ${keyStr}${defaultStr})`
10875:         )
10876:       }
10877:     }
10878:   }
10879: 
10880:   function processRefArrayPattern(pattern, call, tempVar, path = []) {
10881:     if (!tempVar) {
10882:       // const [x] = $(useFoo()) --> const __$temp_1 = useFoo()
10883:       tempVar = genTempVar()
10884:       s.overwrite(pattern.start + offset, pattern.end + offset, tempVar)
10885:     }
10886: 
10887:     for (let i = 0; i < pattern.elements.length; i++) {
10888:       const e = pattern.elements[i]
10889:       if (!e) continue
10890:       let nameId
10891:       let defaultValue
10892:       if (e.type === 'Identifier') {
10893:         // [a] --> [__a]
10894:         nameId = e
10895:       } else if (e.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
10896:         // [a = 1]
10897:         nameId = e.left
10898:         defaultValue = e.right
10899:       } else if (e.type === 'RestElement') {
10900:         // [...a]
10901:         error(`reactivity destructure does not support rest elements.`, e)
10902:       } else if (e.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
10903:         processRefObjectPattern(e, call, tempVar, [...path, i])
10904:       } else if (e.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
10905:         processRefArrayPattern(e, call, tempVar, [...path, i])
10906:       }
10907:       if (nameId) {
10908:         registerRefBinding(nameId)
10909:         // inject toRef() after original replaced pattern
10910:         const source = pathToString(tempVar, path)
10911:         const defaultStr = defaultValue ? `, ${snip(defaultValue)}` : ``
10912:         s.appendLeft(
10913:           call.end + offset,
10914:           `,\n  ${nameId.name} = ${helper(
10915:             'toRef'
10916:           )}(${source}, ${i}${defaultStr})`
10917:         )
10918:       }
10919:     }
10920:   }
10921: 
10922:   function pathToString(source, path) {
10923:     if (path.length) {
10924:       for (const seg of path) {
10925:         if (isArray(seg)) {
10926:           source = `(${source}${segToString(seg[0])} || ${snip(seg[1])})`
10927:         } else {
10928:           source += segToString(seg)
10929:         }
10930:       }
10931:     }
10932:     return source
10933:   }
10934: 
10935:   function segToString(seg) {
10936:     if (typeof seg === 'number') {
10937:       return `[${seg}]`
10938:     } else if (typeof seg === 'string') {
10939:       return `.${seg}`
10940:     } else {
10941:       return snip(seg)
10942:     }
10943:   }
10944: 
10945:   function rewriteId(scope, id, parent, parentStack) {
10946:     if (hasOwn(scope, id.name)) {
10947:       const bindingType = scope[id.name]
10948:       if (bindingType) {
10949:         const isProp = bindingType === 'prop'
10950:         if (isStaticProperty(parent) && parent.shorthand) {
10951:           // let binding used in a property shorthand
10952:           // skip for destructure patterns
10953:           if (
10954:             !parent.inPattern ||
10955:             isInDestructureAssignment(parent, parentStack)
10956:           ) {
10957:             if (isProp) {
10958:               if (escapeScope) {
10959:                 // prop binding in $$()
10960:                 // { prop } -> { prop: __prop_prop }
10961:                 registerEscapedPropBinding(id)
10962:                 s.appendLeft(
10963:                   id.end + offset,
10964:                   `: __props_${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
10965:                 )
10966:               } else {
10967:                 // { prop } -> { prop: __prop.prop }
10968:                 s.appendLeft(
10969:                   id.end + offset,
10970:                   `: __props.${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
10971:                 )
10972:               }
10973:             } else {
10974:               // { foo } -> { foo: foo.value }
10975:               s.appendLeft(id.end + offset, `: ${id.name}.value`)
10976:             }
10977:           }
10978:         } else {
10979:           if (isProp) {
10980:             if (escapeScope) {
10981:               // x --> __props_x
10982:               registerEscapedPropBinding(id)
10983:               s.overwrite(
10984:                 id.start + offset,
10985:                 id.end + offset,
10986:                 `__props_${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
10987:               )
10988:             } else {
10989:               // x --> __props.x
10990:               s.overwrite(
10991:                 id.start + offset,
10992:                 id.end + offset,
10993:                 `__props.${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
10994:               )
10995:             }
10996:           } else {
10997:             // x --> x.value
10998:             s.appendLeft(id.end + offset, '.value')
10999:           }
11000:         }
11001:       }
11002:       return true
11003:     }
11004:     return false
11005:   }
11006: 
11007:   const propBindingRefs = {}
11008:   function registerEscapedPropBinding(id) {
11009:     if (!propBindingRefs.hasOwnProperty(id.name)) {
11010:       propBindingRefs[id.name] = true
11011:       const publicKey = propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]
11012:       s.prependRight(
11013:         offset,
11014:         `const __props_${publicKey} = ${helper(
11015:           `toRef`
11016:         )}(__props, '${publicKey}')\n`
11017:       )
11018:     }
11019:   }
11020: 
11021:   // check root scope first
11022:   walkScope(ast, true)
11023:   walk(ast, {
11024:     enter(node, parent) {
11025:       parent && parentStack.push(parent)
11026: 
11027:       // function scopes
11028:       if (isFunctionType(node)) {
11029:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
11030:         walkFunctionParams(node, registerBinding)
11031:         if (node.body.type === 'BlockStatement') {
11032:           walkScope(node.body)
11033:         }
11034:         return
11035:       }
11036: 
11037:       // catch param
11038:       if (node.type === 'CatchClause') {
11039:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
11040:         if (node.param && node.param.type === 'Identifier') {
11041:           registerBinding(node.param)
11042:         }
11043:         walkScope(node.body)
11044:         return
11045:       }
11046: 
11047:       // non-function block scopes
11048:       if (node.type === 'BlockStatement' && !isFunctionType(parent)) {
11049:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
11050:         walkScope(node)
11051:         return
11052:       }
11053: 
11054:       // skip type nodes
11055:       if (
11056:         parent &&
11057:         parent.type.startsWith('TS') &&
11058:         parent.type !== 'TSAsExpression' &&
11059:         parent.type !== 'TSNonNullExpression' &&
11060:         parent.type !== 'TSTypeAssertion'
11061:       ) {
11062:         return this.skip()
11063:       }
11064: 
11065:       if (
11066:         node.type === 'Identifier' &&
11067:         // if inside $$(), skip unless this is a destructured prop binding
11068:         !(escapeScope && rootScope[node.name] !== 'prop') &&
11069:         isReferencedIdentifier(node, parent, parentStack) &&
11070:         !excludedIds.has(node)
11071:       ) {
11072:         // walk up the scope chain to check if id should be appended .value
11073:         let i = scopeStack.length
11074:         while (i--) {
11075:           if (rewriteId(scopeStack[i], node, parent, parentStack)) {
11076:             return
11077:           }
11078:         }
11079:       }
11080: 
11081:       if (node.type === 'CallExpression' && node.callee.type === 'Identifier') {
11082:         const callee = node.callee.name
11083: 
11084:         const refCall = isRefCreationCall(callee)
11085:         if (refCall && (!parent || parent.type !== 'VariableDeclarator')) {
11086:           return error(
11087:             `${refCall} can only be used as the initializer of ` +
11088:               `a variable declaration.`,
11089:             node
11090:           )
11091:         }
11092: 
11093:         if (callee === escapeSymbol) {
11094:           s.remove(node.callee.start + offset, node.callee.end + offset)
11095:           escapeScope = node
11096:         }
11097: 
11098:         // TODO remove when out of experimental
11099:         if (callee === '$raw') {
11100:           error(
11101:             `$raw() has been replaced by $$(). ` +
11102:               `See ${RFC_LINK} for latest updates.`,
11103:             node
11104:           )
11105:         }
11106:         if (callee === '$fromRef') {
11107:           error(
11108:             `$fromRef() has been replaced by $(). ` +
11109:               `See ${RFC_LINK} for latest updates.`,
11110:             node
11111:           )
11112:         }
11113:       }
11114:     },
11115:     leave(node, parent) {
11116:       parent && parentStack.pop()
11117:       if (
11118:         (node.type === 'BlockStatement' && !isFunctionType(parent)) ||
11119:         isFunctionType(node)
11120:       ) {
11121:         scopeStack.pop()
11122:         currentScope = scopeStack[scopeStack.length - 1] || null
11123:       }
11124:       if (node === escapeScope) {
11125:         escapeScope = undefined
11126:       }
11127:     }
11128:   })
11129: 
11130:   return {
11131:     rootRefs: Object.keys(rootScope).filter(key => rootScope[key] === true),
11132:     importedHelpers: [...importedHelpers]
11133:   }
11134: }
11135: 
11136:   return { transformAST, transform, shouldTransform }
11137: }())
11138: 
11139: const range = 2
11140: 
11141: function generateCodeFrame(
11142:   source,
11143:   start = 0,
11144:   end = source.length
11145: ) {
11146:   // Split the content into individual lines but capture the newline sequence
11147:   // that separated each line. This is important because the actual sequence is
11148:   // needed to properly take into account the full line length for offset
11149:   // comparison
11150:   let lines = source.split(/(\r?\n)/)
11151: 
11152:   // Separate the lines and newline sequences into separate arrays for easier referencing
11153:   const newlineSequences = lines.filter((_, idx) => idx % 2 === 1)
11154:   lines = lines.filter((_, idx) => idx % 2 === 0)
11155: 
11156:   let count = 0
11157:   const res = []
11158:   for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
11159:     count +=
11160:       lines[i].length +
11161:       ((newlineSequences[i] && newlineSequences[i].length) || 0)
11162:     if (count >= start) {
11163:       for (let j = i - range; j <= i + range || end > count; j++) {
11164:         if (j < 0 || j >= lines.length) continue
11165:         const line = j + 1
11166:         res.push(
11167:           `${line}${' '.repeat(Math.max(3 - String(line).length, 0))}|  ${
11168:             lines[j]
11169:           }`
11170:         )
11171:         const lineLength = lines[j].length
11172:         const newLineSeqLength =
11173:           (newlineSequences[j] && newlineSequences[j].length) || 0
11174: 
11175:         if (j === i) {
11176:           // push underline
11177:           const pad = start - (count - (lineLength + newLineSeqLength))
11178:           const length = Math.max(
11179:             1,
11180:             end > count ? lineLength - pad : end - start
11181:           )
11182:           res.push(`   |  ` + ' '.repeat(pad) + '^'.repeat(length))
11183:         } else if (j > i) {
11184:           if (end > count) {
11185:             const length = Math.max(Math.min(end - count, lineLength), 1)
11186:             res.push(`   |  ` + '^'.repeat(length))
11187:           }
11188: 
11189:           count += lineLength + newLineSeqLength
11190:         }
11191:       }
11192:       break
11193:     }
11194:   }
11195:   return res.join('\n')
11196: }
11197: 
11198: function registerBinding(bindings, node, type) {
11199:   bindings[node.name] = type
11200: }
11201: function walkDeclaration(node, bindings, userImportAlias) {
11202:   if (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration') {
11203:     const isConst = node.kind === 'const'
11204:     // export const foo = ...
11205:     for (const { id, init } of node.declarations) {
11206:       const isDefineCall = !!(
11207:         isConst &&
11208:         isCallOf(
11209:           init,
11210:           c => c === DEFINE_PROPS || c === DEFINE_EMITS || c === WITH_DEFAULTS
11211:         )
11212:       )
11213:       if (id.type === 'Identifier') {
11214:         let bindingType
11215:         const userReactiveBinding = userImportAlias['reactive'] || 'reactive'
11216:         if (isCallOf(init, userReactiveBinding)) {
11217:           // treat reactive() calls as let since it's meant to be mutable
11218:           bindingType = BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11219:         } else if (
11220:           // if a declaration is a const literal, we can mark it so that
11221:           // the generated render fn code doesn't need to unref() it
11222:           isDefineCall ||
11223:           (isConst && canNeverBeRef(init, userReactiveBinding))
11224:         ) {
11225:           bindingType = BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
11226:         } else if (isConst) {
11227:           if (isCallOf(init, userImportAlias['ref'] || 'ref')) {
11228:             bindingType = BindingTypes.SETUP_REF
11229:           } else {
11230:             bindingType = BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
11231:           }
11232:         } else {
11233:           bindingType = BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11234:         }
11235:         registerBinding(bindings, id, bindingType)
11236:       } else {
11237:         if (isCallOf(init, DEFINE_PROPS)) {
11238:           // skip walking props destructure
11239:           return
11240:         }
11241:         if (id.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
11242:           walkObjectPattern(id, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall)
11243:         } else if (id.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
11244:           walkArrayPattern(id, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall)
11245:         }
11246:       }
11247:     }
11248:   } else if (
11249:     node.type === 'TSEnumDeclaration' ||
11250:     node.type === 'FunctionDeclaration' ||
11251:     node.type === 'ClassDeclaration'
11252:   ) {
11253:     // export function foo() {} / export class Foo {}
11254:     // export declarations must be named.
11255:     bindings[node.id.name] = BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
11256:   }
11257: }
11258: 
11259: function walkObjectPattern(node, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall = false) {
11260:   for (const p of node.properties) {
11261:     if (p.type === 'ObjectProperty') {
11262:       if (p.key.type === 'Identifier' && p.key === p.value) {
11263:         // shorthand: const { x } = ...
11264:         const type = isDefineCall
11265:           ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
11266:           : isConst
11267:           ? BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
11268:           : BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11269:         registerBinding(bindings, p.key, type)
11270:       } else {
11271:         walkPattern(p.value, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall)
11272:       }
11273:     } else {
11274:       // ...rest
11275:       // argument can only be identifier when destructuring
11276:       const type = isConst ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST : BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11277:       registerBinding(bindings, p.argument, type)
11278:     }
11279:   }
11280: }
11281: 
11282: 
11283: function walkArrayPattern(node, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall = false) {
11284:   for (const e of node.elements) {
11285:     e && walkPattern(e, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall)
11286:   }
11287: }
11288: function walkPattern(node, bindings, isConst, isDefineCall = false) {
11289:   if (node.type === 'Identifier') {
11290:     const type = isDefineCall
11291:       ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
11292:       : isConst
11293:       ? BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
11294:       : BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11295:     registerBinding(bindings, node, type)
11296:   } else if (node.type === 'RestElement') {
11297:     // argument can only be identifier when destructuring
11298:     const type = isConst ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST : BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11299:     registerBinding(bindings, node.argument, type)
11300:   } else if (node.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
11301:     walkObjectPattern(node, bindings, isConst)
11302:   } else if (node.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
11303:     walkArrayPattern(node, bindings, isConst)
11304:   } else if (node.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
11305:     if (node.left.type === 'Identifier') {
11306:       const type = isDefineCall
11307:         ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
11308:         : isConst
11309:         ? BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
11310:         : BindingTypes.SETUP_LET
11311:       registerBinding(bindings, node.left, type)
11312:     } else {
11313:       walkPattern(node.left, bindings, isConst)
11314:     }
11315:   }
11316: }
11317: function recordType(node, declaredTypes) {
11318:   if (node.type === 'TSInterfaceDeclaration') {
11319:     declaredTypes[node.id.name] = [`Object`]
11320:   } else if (node.type === 'TSTypeAliasDeclaration') {
11321:     declaredTypes[node.id.name] = inferRuntimeType(
11322:       node.typeAnnotation,
11323:       declaredTypes
11324:     )
11325:   } else if (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' && node.declaration) {
11326:     recordType(node.declaration, declaredTypes)
11327:   }
11328: }
11329: function extractRuntimeProps(node, props, declaredTypes, isProd) {
11330:   const members = node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral' ? node.members : node.body
11331:   for (const m of members) {
11332:     if (
11333:       (m.type === 'TSPropertySignature' || m.type === 'TSMethodSignature') &&
11334:       m.key.type === 'Identifier'
11335:     ) {
11336:       let type
11337:       if (m.type === 'TSMethodSignature') {
11338:         type = ['Function']
11339:       } else if (m.typeAnnotation) {
11340:         type = inferRuntimeType(m.typeAnnotation.typeAnnotation, declaredTypes)
11341:       }
11342:       props[m.key.name] = {
11343:         key: m.key.name,
11344:         required: !m.optional,
11345:         type: type || [`null`]
11346:       }
11347:     }
11348:   }
11349: }
11350: 
11351: 
11352: function inferRuntimeType(node, declaredTypes) {
11353:   switch (node.type) {
11354:     case 'TSStringKeyword':
11355:       return ['String']
11356:     case 'TSNumberKeyword':
11357:       return ['Number']
11358:     case 'TSBooleanKeyword':
11359:       return ['Boolean']
11360:     case 'TSObjectKeyword':
11361:       return ['Object']
11362:     case 'TSTypeLiteral':
11363:       // TODO (nice to have) generate runtime property validation
11364:       return ['Object']
11365:     case 'TSFunctionType':
11366:       return ['Function']
11367:     case 'TSArrayType':
11368:     case 'TSTupleType':
11369:       // TODO (nice to have) generate runtime element type/length checks
11370:       return ['Array']
11371: 
11372:     case 'TSLiteralType':
11373:       switch (node.literal.type) {
11374:         case 'StringLiteral':
11375:           return ['String']
11376:         case 'BooleanLiteral':
11377:           return ['Boolean']
11378:         case 'NumericLiteral':
11379:         case 'BigIntLiteral':
11380:           return ['Number']
11381:         default:
11382:           return [`null`]
11383:       }
11384: 
11385:     case 'TSTypeReference':
11386:       if (node.typeName.type === 'Identifier') {
11387:         if (declaredTypes[node.typeName.name]) {
11388:           return declaredTypes[node.typeName.name]
11389:         }
11390:         switch (node.typeName.name) {
11391:           case 'Array':
11392:           case 'Function':
11393:           case 'Object':
11394:           case 'Set':
11395:           case 'Map':
11396:           case 'WeakSet':
11397:           case 'WeakMap':
11398:           case 'Date':
11399:             return [node.typeName.name]
11400:           case 'Record':
11401:           case 'Partial':
11402:           case 'Readonly':
11403:           case 'Pick':
11404:           case 'Omit':
11405:           case 'Exclude':
11406:           case 'Extract':
11407:           case 'Required':
11408:           case 'InstanceType':
11409:             return ['Object']
11410:         }
11411:       }
11412:       return [`null`]
11413: 
11414:     case 'TSParenthesizedType':
11415:       return inferRuntimeType(node.typeAnnotation, declaredTypes)
11416:     case 'TSUnionType':
11417:       return [
11418:         ...new Set(
11419:           [].concat(
11420:             ...(node.types.map(t => inferRuntimeType(t, declaredTypes)))
11421:           )
11422:         )
11423:       ]
11424:     case 'TSIntersectionType':
11425:       return ['Object']
11426: 
11427:     case 'TSSymbolKeyword':
11428:       return ['Symbol']
11429: 
11430:     default:
11431:       return [`null`] // no runtime check
11432:   }
11433: }
11434: function toRuntimeTypeString(types) {
11435:   return types.length > 1 ? `[${types.join(', ')}]` : types[0]
11436: }
11437: function extractRuntimeEmits(node, emits) {
11438:   if (node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral' || node.type === 'TSInterfaceBody') {
11439:     const members = node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral' ? node.members : node.body
11440:     for (let t of members) {
11441:       if (t.type === 'TSCallSignatureDeclaration') {
11442:         extractEventNames(t.parameters[0], emits)
11443:       }
11444:     }
11445:     return
11446:   } else {
11447:     extractEventNames(node.parameters[0], emits)
11448:   }
11449: }
11450: function extractEventNames(eventName, emits) {
11451:   if (
11452:     eventName.type === 'Identifier' &&
11453:     eventName.typeAnnotation &&
11454:     eventName.typeAnnotation.type === 'TSTypeAnnotation'
11455:   ) {
11456:     const typeNode = eventName.typeAnnotation.typeAnnotation
11457:     if (typeNode.type === 'TSLiteralType') {
11458:       if (typeNode.literal.type !== 'UnaryExpression') {
11459:         emits.add(String(typeNode.literal.value))
11460:       }
11461:     } else if (typeNode.type === 'TSUnionType') {
11462:       for (const t of typeNode.types) {
11463:         if (
11464:           t.type === 'TSLiteralType' &&
11465:           t.literal.type !== 'UnaryExpression'
11466:         ) {
11467:           emits.add(String(t.literal.value))
11468:         }
11469:       }
11470:     }
11471:   }
11472: }
11473: function genRuntimeEmits(emits) {
11474:   return emits.size
11475:     ? `\n  emits: [${Array.from(emits)
11476:         .map(p => JSON.stringify(p))
11477:         .join(', ')}],`
11478:     : ``
11479: }
11480: function isCallOf(node, test) {
11481:   return !!(
11482:     node &&
11483:     node.type === 'CallExpression' &&
11484:     node.callee.type === 'Identifier' &&
11485:     (typeof test === 'string'
11486:       ? node.callee.name === test
11487:       : test(node.callee.name))
11488:   )
11489: }
11490: function canNeverBeRef(node, userReactiveImport) {
11491:   if (isCallOf(node, userReactiveImport)) {
11492:     return true
11493:   }
11494:   switch (node.type) {
11495:     case 'UnaryExpression':
11496:     case 'BinaryExpression':
11497:     case 'ArrayExpression':
11498:     case 'ObjectExpression':
11499:     case 'FunctionExpression':
11500:     case 'ArrowFunctionExpression':
11501:     case 'UpdateExpression':
11502:     case 'ClassExpression':
11503:     case 'TaggedTemplateExpression':
11504:       return true
11505:     case 'SequenceExpression':
11506:       return canNeverBeRef(
11507:         node.expressions[node.expressions.length - 1],
11508:         userReactiveImport
11509:       )
11510:     default:
11511:       if (node.type.endsWith('Literal')) {
11512:         return true
11513:       }
11514:       return false
11515:   }
11516: }
11517: 
11518: 
11519: /**
11520:  * Analyze bindings in normal `<script>`
11521:  * Note that `compileScriptSetup` already analyzes bindings as part of its
11522:  * compilation process so this should only be used on single `<script>` SFCs.
11523:  */
11524: function analyzeScriptBindings(ast) {
11525:   for (const node of ast) {
11526:     if (
11527:       node.type === 'ExportDefaultDeclaration' &&
11528:       node.declaration.type === 'ObjectExpression'
11529:     ) {
11530:       return analyzeBindingsFromOptions(node.declaration)
11531:     }
11532:   }
11533:   return {}
11534: }
11535: function analyzeBindingsFromOptions(node) {
11536:   const bindings = {}
11537:   // #3270, #3275
11538:   // mark non-script-setup so we don't resolve components/directives from these
11539:   Object.defineProperty(bindings, '__isScriptSetup', {
11540:     enumerable: false,
11541:     value: false
11542:   })
11543:   for (const property of node.properties) {
11544:     if (
11545:       property.type === 'ObjectProperty' &&
11546:       !property.computed &&
11547:       property.key.type === 'Identifier'
11548:     ) {
11549:       // props
11550:       if (property.key.name === 'props') {
11551:         // props: ['foo']
11552:         // props: { foo: ... }
11553:         for (const key of getObjectOrArrayExpressionKeys(property.value)) {
11554:           bindings[key] = BindingTypes.PROPS
11555:         }
11556:       }
11557: 
11558:       // inject
11559:       else if (property.key.name === 'inject') {
11560:         // inject: ['foo']
11561:         // inject: { foo: {} }
11562:         for (const key of getObjectOrArrayExpressionKeys(property.value)) {
11563:           bindings[key] = BindingTypes.OPTIONS
11564:         }
11565:       }
11566: 
11567:       // computed & methods
11568:       else if (
11569:         property.value.type === 'ObjectExpression' &&
11570:         (property.key.name === 'computed' || property.key.name === 'methods')
11571:       ) {
11572:         // methods: { foo() {} }
11573:         // computed: { foo() {} }
11574:         for (const key of getObjectExpressionKeys(property.value)) {
11575:           bindings[key] = BindingTypes.OPTIONS
11576:         }
11577:       }
11578:     }
11579: 
11580:     // setup & data
11581:     else if (
11582:       property.type === 'ObjectMethod' &&
11583:       property.key.type === 'Identifier' &&
11584:       (property.key.name === 'setup' || property.key.name === 'data')
11585:     ) {
11586:       for (const bodyItem of property.body.body) {
11587:         // setup() {
11588:         //   return {
11589:         //     foo: null
11590:         //   }
11591:         // }
11592:         if (
11593:           bodyItem.type === 'ReturnStatement' &&
11594:           bodyItem.argument &&
11595:           bodyItem.argument.type === 'ObjectExpression'
11596:         ) {
11597:           for (const key of getObjectExpressionKeys(bodyItem.argument)) {
11598:             bindings[key] =
11599:               property.key.name === 'setup'
11600:                 ? BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
11601:                 : BindingTypes.DATA
11602:           }
11603:         }
11604:       }
11605:     }
11606:   }
11607: 
11608:   return bindings
11609: }
11610: function getObjectExpressionKeys(node) {
11611:   const keys = []
11612:   for (const prop of node.properties) {
11613:     if (
11614:       (prop.type === 'ObjectProperty' || prop.type === 'ObjectMethod') &&
11615:       !prop.computed
11616:     ) {
11617:       if (prop.key.type === 'Identifier') {
11618:         keys.push(prop.key.name)
11619:       } else if (prop.key.type === 'StringLiteral') {
11620:         keys.push(prop.key.value)
11621:       }
11622:     }
11623:   }
11624:   return keys
11625: }
11626: function getArrayExpressionKeys(node) {
11627:   const keys = []
11628:   for (const element of node.elements) {
11629:     if (element && element.type === 'StringLiteral') {
11630:       keys.push(element.value)
11631:     }
11632:   }
11633:   return keys
11634: }
11635: function getObjectOrArrayExpressionKeys(value) {
11636:   if (value.type === 'ArrayExpression') {
11637:     return getArrayExpressionKeys(value)
11638:   }
11639:   if (value.type === 'ObjectExpression') {
11640:     return getObjectExpressionKeys(value)
11641:   }
11642:   return []
11643: }
11644: function resolveTemplateUsageCheckString(sfc) {
11645:   const { content, ast } = sfc.template
11646:   const cached = templateUsageCheckCache.get(content)
11647:   if (cached) {
11648:     return cached
11649:   }
11650: 
11651:   let code = ''
11652:   transform(createRoot([ast]), {
11653:     nodeTransforms: [
11654:       node => {
11655:         if (node.type === NodeTypes.ELEMENT) {
11656:           if (
11657:             !parserOptions.isNativeTag(node.tag) &&
11658:             !parserOptions.isBuiltInComponent(node.tag)
11659:           ) {
11660:             code += `,${camelize(node.tag)},${capitalize(camelize(node.tag))}`
11661:           }
11662:           for (let i = 0; i < node.props.length; i++) {
11663:             const prop = node.props[i]
11664:             if (prop.type === NodeTypes.DIRECTIVE) {
11665:               if (!isBuiltInDir(prop.name)) {
11666:                 code += `,v${capitalize(camelize(prop.name))}`
11667:               }
11668:               if (prop.exp) {
11669:                 code += `,${stripStrings(prop.exp.content)}`
11670:               }
11671:             }
11672:           }
11673:         } else if (node.type === NodeTypes.INTERPOLATION) {
11674:           code += `,${stripStrings(node.content.content)}`
11675:         }
11676:       }
11677:     ]
11678:   })
11679: 
11680:   code += ';'
11681:   templateUsageCheckCache.set(content, code)
11682:   return code
11683: }
11684: function stripStrings(exp) {
11685:   return exp
11686:     .replace(/'[^']*'|"[^"]*"/g, '')
11687:     .replace(/`[^`]+`/g, stripTemplateString)
11688: }
11689: function isImportUsed(local, sfc) {
11690:   return new RegExp(
11691:     // #4274 escape $ since it's a special char in regex
11692:     // (and is the only regex special char that is valid in identifiers)
11693:     `[^\\w$_]${local.replace(/\$/g, '\\$')}[^\\w$_]`
11694:   ).test(resolveTemplateUsageCheckString(sfc))
11695: }
11696: /**
11697:  * Note: this comparison assumes the prev/next script are already identical,
11698:  * and only checks the special case where <script setup lang="ts"> unused import
11699:  * pruning result changes due to template changes.
11700:  */
11701: function hmrShouldReload(prevImports, next) {
11702:   if (
11703:     !next.scriptSetup ||
11704:     (next.scriptSetup.lang !== 'ts' && next.scriptSetup.lang !== 'tsx')
11705:   ) {
11706:     return false
11707:   }
11708: 
11709:   // for each previous import, check if its used status remain the same based on
11710:   // the next descriptor's template
11711:   for (const key in prevImports) {
11712:     // if an import was previous unused, but now is used, we need to force
11713:     // reload so that the script now includes that import.
11714:     if (!prevImports[key].isUsedInTemplate && isImportUsed(key, next)) {
11715:       return true
11716:     }
11717:   }
11718: 
11719:   return false
11720: }
11721: function compileTemplate(options) {
11722:   // ... compile
11723: 
11724:   return doCompileTemplate(options)
11725: }
11726: 
11727: function doCompileTemplate({
11728:   filename,
11729:   id,
11730:   scoped,
11731:   slotted,
11732:   inMap,
11733:   source,
11734:   ssr = false,
11735:   ssrCssVars,
11736:   isProd = false,
11737:   compiler,
11738:   compilerOptions = {},
11739:   transformAssetUrls
11740: }) {
11741:   const errors = []
11742:   const warnings = []
11743: 
11744:   let nodeTransforms = []
11745:   if (isObject(transformAssetUrls)) {
11746:     const assetOptions = normalizeOptions(transformAssetUrls)
11747:     nodeTransforms = [
11748:       createAssetUrlTransformWithOptions(assetOptions),
11749:       createSrcsetTransformWithOptions(assetOptions)
11750:     ]
11751:   } else if (transformAssetUrls !== false) {
11752:     nodeTransforms = [transformAssetUrl, transformSrcset]
11753:   }
11754: 
11755:   if (!id) {
11756:     id = ''
11757:   }
11758: 
11759:   const shortId = id.replace(/^data-v-/, '')
11760:   const longId = `data-v-${shortId}`
11761: 
11762:   let { code, ast, preamble, map } = baseCompile(source, {
11763:     mode: 'module',
11764:     prefixIdentifiers: true,
11765:     hoistStatic: true,
11766:     cacheHandlers: true,
11767:     ssrCssVars:
11768:       ssr && ssrCssVars && ssrCssVars.length
11769:         ? genCssVarsFromList(ssrCssVars, shortId, isProd)
11770:         : '',
11771:     scopeId: scoped ? longId : undefined,
11772:     slotted,
11773:     sourceMap: true,
11774:     ...compilerOptions,
11775:     nodeTransforms: nodeTransforms.concat(compilerOptions.nodeTransforms || []),
11776:     filename,
11777:     onError: e => errors.push(e),
11778:     onWarn: w => warnings.push(w)
11779:   })
11780: 
11781:   return { code, ast, preamble, source, errors, tips, map }
11782: }
11783: const hash = require(process.env.NODE_LIB + '/hash-sum')
11784: const CSS_VARS_HELPER = `useCssVars`
11785: // match v-bind() with max 2-levels of nested parens.
11786: const cssVarRE = /v-bind\s*\(((?:[^)(]+|\((?:[^)(]+|\([^)(]*\))*\))*)\)/g
11787: 
11788: function genCssVarsFromList(
11789:   vars,
11790:   id,
11791:   isProd
11792: ) {
11793:   return `{\n  ${vars
11794:     .map(key => `"${genVarName(id, key, isProd)}": (${key})`)
11795:     .join(',\n  ')}\n}`
11796: }
11797: 
11798: function genVarName(id, raw, isProd) {
11799:   if (isProd) {
11800:     return hash(id + raw)
11801:   } else {
11802:     return `${id}-${raw.replace(/([^\w-])/g, '_')}`
11803:   }
11804: }
11805: 
11806: function noramlizeExpression(exp) {
11807:   exp = exp.trim()
11808:   if (
11809:     (exp[0] === `'` && exp[exp.length - 1] === `'`) ||
11810:     (exp[0] === `"` && exp[exp.length - 1] === `"`)
11811:   ) {
11812:     return exp.slice(1, -1)
11813:   }
11814:   return exp
11815: }
11816: 
11817: function parseCssVars(sfc) {
11818:   const vars = []
11819:   sfc.styles.forEach(style => {
11820:     let match
11821:     // ignore v-bind() in comments /* ... */
11822:     const content = style.content.replace(/\/\*([\s\S]*?)\*\//g, '')
11823:     while ((match = cssVarRE.exec(content))) {
11824:       const variable = noramlizeExpression(match[1])
11825:       if (!vars.includes(variable)) {
11826:         vars.push(variable)
11827:       }
11828:     }
11829:   })
11830:   return vars
11831: }
11832: 
11833: // for compileStyle
11834: 
11835: const cssVarsPlugin = opts => {
11836:   const { id, isProd } = opts
11837:   return {
11838:     postcssPlugin: 'vue-sfc-vars',
11839:     Declaration(decl) {
11840:       // rewrite CSS variables
11841:       if (cssVarRE.test(decl.value)) {
11842:         decl.value = decl.value.replace(cssVarRE, (_, $1) => {
11843:           return `var(--${genVarName(id, noramlizeExpression($1), isProd)})`
11844:         })
11845:       }
11846:     }
11847:   }
11848: }
11849: cssVarsPlugin.postcss = true
11850: 
11851: function genCssVarsCode(
11852:   vars,
11853:   bindings,
11854:   id,
11855:   isProd
11856: ) {
11857:   const varsExp = genCssVarsFromList(vars, id, isProd)
11858:   const exp = createSimpleExpression(varsExp, false)
11859:   const context = createTransformContext(createRoot([]), {
11860:     prefixIdentifiers: true,
11861:     inline: true,
11862:     bindingMetadata: bindings.__isScriptSetup === false ? undefined : bindings
11863:   })
11864:   const transformed = processExpression(exp, context)
11865:   const transformedString =
11866:     transformed.type === NodeTypes.SIMPLE_EXPRESSION
11867:       ? transformed.content
11868:       : transformed.children
11869:           .map(c => {
11870:             return typeof c === 'string'
11871:               ? c
11872:               : c.content
11873:           })
11874:           .join('')
11875: 
11876:   return `_${CSS_VARS_HELPER}(_ctx => (${transformedString}))`
11877: }
11878: 
11879: // <script setup> already gets the calls injected as part of the transform
11880: // this is only for single normal <script>
11881: function genNormalScriptCssVarsCode(
11882:   cssVars,
11883:   bindings,
11884:   id,
11885:   isProd
11886: ) {
11887:   return (
11888:     `\nimport { ${CSS_VARS_HELPER} as _${CSS_VARS_HELPER} } from 'vue'\n` +
11889:     `const __injectCSSVars__ = () => {\n${genCssVarsCode(
11890:       cssVars,
11891:       bindings,
11892:       id,
11893:       isProd
11894:     )}}\n` +
11895:     `const __setup__ = __default__.setup\n` +
11896:     `__default__.setup = __setup__\n` +
11897:     `  ? (props, ctx) => { __injectCSSVars__();return __setup__(props, ctx) }\n` +
11898:     `  : __injectCSSVars__\n`
11899:   )
11900: }
11901: 
11902: 
11903: // Special compiler macros
11904: const DEFINE_PROPS = 'defineProps'
11905: const DEFINE_EMITS = 'defineEmits'
11906: const DEFINE_EXPOSE = 'defineExpose'
11907: const WITH_DEFAULTS = 'withDefaults'
11908: const templateUsageCheckCache = createCache()
11909:

11911: const DEFAULT_VAR = `__default__`
11912: 
11913: const isBuiltInDir = makeMap(
11914:   `once,memo,if,else,else-if,slot,text,html,on,bind,model,show,cloak,is`
11915: )
