11917: function compileScript(sfc, options) {
11918:   let { script, scriptSetup, source, filename } = sfc
11919:   // feature flags
11920:   // TODO remove support for deprecated options when out of experimental
11921:   const enableReactivityTransform =
11922:     !!options.reactivityTransform ||
11923:     !!options.refSugar ||
11924:     !!options.refTransform
11925:   const enablePropsTransform =
11926:     !!options.reactivityTransform || !!options.propsDestructureTransform
11927:   const isProd = !!options.isProd
11928:   const genSourceMap = options.sourceMap !== false
11929:   // ref 
11930:   let refBindings
11931: 
11932:   const scopeId = options.id ? options.id.replace(/^data-v-/, '') : ''
11933:   const cssVars = sfc.cssVars
11934:   const scriptLang = script && script.lang
11935:   const scriptSetupLang = scriptSetup && scriptSetup.lang
11936:   const isTS =
11937:     scriptLang === 'ts' ||
11938:     scriptLang === 'tsx' ||
11939:     scriptSetupLang === 'ts' ||
11940:     scriptSetupLang === 'tsx'
11941: 
11942:   // resolve parser plugins
11943:   const plugins = []
11944:   if (!isTS || scriptLang === 'tsx' || scriptSetupLang === 'tsx') {
11945:     plugins.push('jsx')
11946:   }
11947:   if (options.babelParserPlugins) plugins.push(...options.babelParserPlugins)
11948:   if (isTS) plugins.push('typescript', 'decorators-legacy')
11949: 
11950:   if (!scriptSetup) {
11951:     if (!script) {
11952:       throw new Error(`[@vue/compiler-sfc] SFC contains no <script> tags.`)
11953:     }
11954:     if (scriptLang && !isTS && scriptLang !== 'jsx') {
11955:       // do not process non js/ts script blocks
11956:       return script
11957:     }
11958:     try {
11959:       let content = script.content
11960:       let map = script.map
11961:       const scriptAst = babelParser.parse(content, {
11962:         plugins,
11963:         sourceType: 'module'
11964:       }).program
11965:       const bindings = analyzeScriptBindings(scriptAst.body)
11966:       if (enableReactivityTransform && RT.shouldTransform(content)) {
11967:         const s = new MagicString(source)
11968:         const startOffset = script.loc.start.offset
11969:         const endOffset = script.loc.end.offset
11970:         const { importedHelpers } = RT.transformAST(scriptAst, s, startOffset)
11971:         if (importedHelpers.length) {
11972:           s.prepend(
11973:             `import { ${importedHelpers
11974:               .map(h => `${h} as _${h}`)
11975:               .join(', ')} } from 'vue'\n`
11976:           )
11977:         }
11978:         s.remove(0, startOffset)
11979:         s.remove(endOffset, source.length)
11980:         content = s.toString()
11981:         if (genSourceMap) {
11982:           map = s.generateMap({
11983:             source: filename,
11984:             hires: true,
11985:             includeContent: true
11986:           })
11987:         }
11988:       }
11989:       if (cssVars.length) {
11990:         content = rewriteDefault(content, DEFAULT_VAR, plugins)
11991:         content += genNormalScriptCssVarsCode(
11992:           cssVars,
11993:           bindings,
11994:           scopeId,
11995:           isProd
11996:         )
11997:         content += `\nexport default ${DEFAULT_VAR}`
11998:       }
11999:       return {
12000:         ...script,
12001:         content,
12002:         map,
12003:         bindings,
12004:         scriptAst: scriptAst.body
12005:       }
12006:     } catch (e) {
12007:       // silently fallback if parse fails since user may be using custom
12008:       // babel syntax
12009:       return script
12010:     }
12011:   }
12012: 
12013:   // script  script setup 
12014:   if (script && scriptLang !== scriptSetupLang) {
12015:     throw new Error(
12016:       `[@vue/compiler-sfc] <script> and <script setup> must have the same ` +
12017:         `language type.`
12018:     )
12019:   }
12020: 
12021:   //  js/ts script
12022:   if (scriptSetupLang && !isTS && scriptSetupLang !== 'jsx') {
12023:     return scriptSetup
12024:   }
12025: 
12026:   // imports 
12027:   const bindingMetadata = {}
12028:   const helperImports = new Set()
12029:   const userImports = Object.create(null)
12030:   const userImportAlias = Object.create(null)
12031:   const scriptBindings = Object.create(null)
12032:   const setupBindings = Object.create(null)
12033: 
12034:   let defaultExport // export default
12035:   let hasDefinePropsCall = false // defineProps()
12036:   let hasDefineEmitCall = false // defineEmits()
12037:   let hasDefineExposeCall = false // defineExpose()
12038:   let propsRuntimeDecl // 
12039:   let propsRuntimeDefaults // 
12040:   let propsDestructureDecl // 
12041:   let propsDestructureRestId //  ... 
12042:   let propsTypeDecl // 
12043:   let propsTypeDeclRaw
12044:   let propsIdentifier
12045:   let emitsRuntimeDecl
12046:   let emitsTypeDecl
12047:   let emitsTypeDeclRaw
12048:   let emitIdentifier
12049:   let hasAwait = false //  await  async setup
12050:   let hasInlinedSsrRenderFn = false
12051:   // props/emits declared via types
12052:   const typeDeclaredProps = {}
12053:   const typeDeclaredEmits = new Set()
12054:   // record declared types for runtime props type generation
12055:   const declaredTypes = {}
12056:   // props destructure data
12057:   const propsDestructuredBindings = Object.create(null)
12058: 
12059:   // magic-string state
12060:   const s = new MagicString(source)
12061:   const startOffset = scriptSetup.loc.start.offset
12062:   const endOffset = scriptSetup.loc.end.offset
12063:   const scriptStartOffset = script && script.loc.start.offset
12064:   const scriptEndOffset = script && script.loc.end.offset
12065: 
12066:   function helper(key) {
12067:     helperImports.add(key)
12068:     return `_${key}`
12069:   }
12070:     function parse(input, options, offset) {
12071:       try {
12072:         return babelParser.parse(input, options).program
12073:       } catch (e) {
12074:         e.message = `[@vue/compiler-sfc] ${e.message}\n\n${
12075:           sfc.filename
12076:         }\n${generateCodeFrame(source, e.pos + offset, e.pos + offset + 1)}`
12077:         throw e
12078:       }
12079:     }
12080:   
12081:   
12082:   function error(msg, node, end = node.end + startOffset) {
12083:     throw new Error(
12084:       `[@vue/compiler-sfc] ${msg}\n\n${sfc.filename}\n${generateCodeFrame(
12085:       source,
12086:       node.start + startOffset,
12087:       end
12088:       )}`
12089:     )
12090:   }
12091:     function registerUserImport(source, local, imported, isType, isFromSetup) {
12092:       if (source === 'vue' && imported) {
12093:         userImportAlias[imported] = local
12094:       }
12095:   
12096:       let isUsedInTemplate = true
12097:       if (isTS && sfc.template && !sfc.template.src && !sfc.template.lang) {
12098:         isUsedInTemplate = isImportUsed(local, sfc)
12099:       }
12100:   
12101:       userImports[local] = {
12102:         isType,
12103:         imported: imported || 'default',
12104:         source,
12105:         isFromSetup,
12106:         isUsedInTemplate
12107:       }
12108:     }
12109:   
12110:     function processDefineProps(node, declId) {
12111:       if (!isCallOf(node, DEFINE_PROPS)) {
12112:         return false
12113:       }
12114:   
12115:       if (hasDefinePropsCall) {
12116:         error(`duplicate ${DEFINE_PROPS}() call`, node)
12117:       }
12118:       hasDefinePropsCall = true
12119:   
12120:       propsRuntimeDecl = node.arguments[0]
12121:   
12122:       // call has type parameters - infer runtime types from it
12123:       if (node.typeParameters) {
12124:         if (propsRuntimeDecl) {
12125:           error(
12126:             `${DEFINE_PROPS}() cannot accept both type and non-type arguments ` +
12127:               `at the same time. Use one or the other.`,
12128:             node
12129:           )
12130:         }
12131:   
12132:         propsTypeDeclRaw = node.typeParameters.params[0]
12133:         propsTypeDecl = resolveQualifiedType(
12134:           propsTypeDeclRaw,
12135:           node => node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral'
12136:         )
12137:   
12138:         if (!propsTypeDecl) {
12139:           error(
12140:             `type argument passed to ${DEFINE_PROPS}() must be a literal type, ` +
12141:               `or a reference to an interface or literal type.`,
12142:             propsTypeDeclRaw
12143:           )
12144:         }
12145:       }
12146:   
12147:       if (declId) {
12148:         if (enablePropsTransform && declId.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
12149:           propsDestructureDecl = declId
12150:           // props destructure - handle compilation sugar
12151:           for (const prop of declId.properties) {
12152:             if (prop.type === 'ObjectProperty') {
12153:               if (prop.computed) {
12154:                 error(
12155:                   `${DEFINE_PROPS}() destructure cannot use computed key.`,
12156:                   prop.key
12157:                 )
12158:               }
12159:               const propKey = prop.key.name
12160:               if (prop.value.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
12161:                 // default value { foo = 123 }
12162:                 const { left, right } = prop.value
12163:                 if (left.type !== 'Identifier') {
12164:                   error(
12165:                     `${DEFINE_PROPS}() destructure does not support nested patterns.`,
12166:                     left
12167:                   )
12168:                 }
12169:                 // store default value
12170:                 propsDestructuredBindings[propKey] = {
12171:                   local: left.name,
12172:                   default: right
12173:                 }
12174:               } else if (prop.value.type === 'Identifier') {
12175:                 // simple destructure
12176:                 propsDestructuredBindings[propKey] = {
12177:                   local: prop.value.name
12178:                 }
12179:               } else {
12180:                 error(
12181:                   `${DEFINE_PROPS}() destructure does not support nested patterns.`,
12182:                   prop.value
12183:                 )
12184:               }
12185:             } else {
12186:               // rest spread
12187:               propsDestructureRestId = prop.argument.name
12188:             }
12189:           }
12190:         } else {
12191:           propsIdentifier = scriptSetup.content.slice(declId.start, declId.end)
12192:         }
12193:       }
12194:   
12195:       return true
12196:     }
12197:   
12198:   
12199:     function processWithDefaults(node, declId) {
12200:       if (!isCallOf(node, WITH_DEFAULTS)) {
12201:         return false
12202:       }
12203:       if (processDefineProps(node.arguments[0], declId)) {
12204:         if (propsRuntimeDecl) {
12205:           error(
12206:             `${WITH_DEFAULTS} can only be used with type-based ` +
12207:               `${DEFINE_PROPS} declaration.`,
12208:             node
12209:           )
12210:         }
12211:         if (propsDestructureDecl) {
12212:           error(
12213:             `${WITH_DEFAULTS}() is unnecessary when using destructure with ${DEFINE_PROPS}().\n` +
12214:               `Prefer using destructure default values, e.g. const { foo = 1 } = defineProps(...).`,
12215:             node.callee
12216:           )
12217:         }
12218:         propsRuntimeDefaults = node.arguments[1]
12219:         if (
12220:           !propsRuntimeDefaults ||
12221:           propsRuntimeDefaults.type !== 'ObjectExpression'
12222:         ) {
12223:           error(
12224:             `The 2nd argument of ${WITH_DEFAULTS} must be an object literal.`,
12225:             propsRuntimeDefaults || node
12226:           )
12227:         }
12228:       } else {
12229:         error(
12230:           `${WITH_DEFAULTS}' first argument must be a ${DEFINE_PROPS} call.`,
12231:           node.arguments[0] || node
12232:         )
12233:       }
12234:       return true
12235:     }
12236:   
12237:   
12238:   
12239:     function processDefineEmits(node, declId) {
12240:       if (!isCallOf(node, DEFINE_EMITS)) {
12241:         return false
12242:       }
12243:       if (hasDefineEmitCall) {
12244:         error(`duplicate ${DEFINE_EMITS}() call`, node)
12245:       }
12246:       hasDefineEmitCall = true
12247:       emitsRuntimeDecl = node.arguments[0]
12248:       if (node.typeParameters) {
12249:         if (emitsRuntimeDecl) {
12250:           error(
12251:             `${DEFINE_EMITS}() cannot accept both type and non-type arguments ` +
12252:               `at the same time. Use one or the other.`,
12253:             node
12254:           )
12255:         }
12256:   
12257:         emitsTypeDeclRaw = node.typeParameters.params[0]
12258:         emitsTypeDecl = resolveQualifiedType(
12259:           emitsTypeDeclRaw,
12260:           node => node.type === 'TSFunctionType' || node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral'
12261:         )
12262:   
12263:         if (!emitsTypeDecl) {
12264:           error(
12265:             `type argument passed to ${DEFINE_EMITS}() must be a function type, ` +
12266:               `a literal type with call signatures, or a reference to the above types.`,
12267:             emitsTypeDeclRaw
12268:           )
12269:         }
12270:       }
12271:   
12272:       if (declId) {
12273:         emitIdentifier = scriptSetup.content.slice(declId.start, declId.end)
12274:       }
12275:   
12276:       return true
12277:     }
12278:   
12279:   
12280:   
12281:     function resolveQualifiedType(node, qualifier) {
12282:       if (qualifier(node)) {
12283:         return node
12284:       }
12285:       if (
12286:         node.type === 'TSTypeReference' &&
12287:         node.typeName.type === 'Identifier'
12288:       ) {
12289:         const refName = node.typeName.name
12290:         const isQualifiedType = (node) => {
12291:           if (
12292:             node.type === 'TSInterfaceDeclaration' &&
12293:             node.id.name === refName
12294:           ) {
12295:             return node.body
12296:           } else if (
12297:             node.type === 'TSTypeAliasDeclaration' &&
12298:             node.id.name === refName &&
12299:             qualifier(node.typeAnnotation)
12300:           ) {
12301:             return node.typeAnnotation
12302:           } else if (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' && node.declaration) {
12303:             return isQualifiedType(node.declaration)
12304:           }
12305:         }
12306:         const body = scriptAst
12307:           ? [...scriptSetupAst.body, ...scriptAst.body]
12308:           : scriptSetupAst.body
12309:         for (const node of body) {
12310:           const qualified = isQualifiedType(node)
12311:           if (qualified) {
12312:             return qualified
12313:           }
12314:         }
12315:       }
12316:     }
12317:   
12318:   
12319:   function processDefineExpose(node) {
12320:       if (isCallOf(node, DEFINE_EXPOSE)) {
12321:         if (hasDefineExposeCall) {
12322:           error(`duplicate ${DEFINE_EXPOSE}() call`, node)
12323:         }
12324:         hasDefineExposeCall = true
12325:         return true
12326:       }
12327:       return false
12328:     }
12329:   
12330:   /**
12331:      * await foo()
12332:      * -->
12333:      * ;(
12334:      *   ([__temp,__restore] = withAsyncContext(() => foo())),
12335:      *   await __temp,
12336:      *   __restore()
12337:      * )
12338:      *
12339:      * const a = await foo()
12340:      * -->
12341:      * const a = (
12342:      *   ([__temp, __restore] = withAsyncContext(() => foo())),
12343:      *   __temp = await __temp,
12344:      *   __restore(),
12345:      *   __temp
12346:      * )
12347:      */
12348:     function processAwait(node, needSemi, isStatement) {
12349:       const argumentStart =
12350:         node.argument.extra && node.argument.extra.parenthesized
12351:           ? node.argument.extra.parenStart
12352:           : node.argument.start
12353:   
12354:       const argumentStr = source.slice(
12355:         argumentStart + startOffset,
12356:         node.argument.end + startOffset
12357:       )
12358:   
12359:       const containsNestedAwait = /\bawait\b/.test(argumentStr)
12360:   
12361:       s.overwrite(
12362:         node.start + startOffset,
12363:         argumentStart + startOffset,
12364:         `${needSemi ? `;` : ``}(\n  ([__temp,__restore] = ${helper(
12365:           `withAsyncContext`
12366:         )}(${containsNestedAwait ? `async ` : ``}() => `
12367:       )
12368:       s.appendLeft(
12369:         node.end + startOffset,
12370:         `)),\n  ${isStatement ? `` : `__temp = `}await __temp,\n  __restore()${
12371:           isStatement ? `` : `,\n  __temp`
12372:         }\n)`
12373:       )
12374:     }
12375:   
12376:   
12377:   /**
12378:      * check defaults. If the default object is an object literal with only
12379:      * static properties, we can directly generate more optimized default
12380:      * declarations. Otherwise we will have to fallback to runtime merging.
12381:      */
12382:     function hasStaticWithDefaults() {
12383:       return (
12384:         propsRuntimeDefaults &&
12385:         propsRuntimeDefaults.type === 'ObjectExpression' &&
12386:         propsRuntimeDefaults.properties.every(
12387:           node =>
12388:             (node.type === 'ObjectProperty' && !node.computed) ||
12389:             node.type === 'ObjectMethod'
12390:         )
12391:       )
12392:     }
12393:   function genRuntimeProps(props) {
12394:       const keys = Object.keys(props)
12395:       if (!keys.length) {
12396:         return ``
12397:       }
12398:       const hasStaticDefaults = hasStaticWithDefaults()
12399:       const scriptSetupSource = scriptSetup.content
12400:       let propsDecls = `{
12401:       ${keys
12402:         .map(key => {
12403:           let defaultString
12404:           const destructured = genDestructuredDefaultValue(key)
12405:           if (destructured) {
12406:             defaultString = `default: ${destructured}`
12407:           } else if (hasStaticDefaults) {
12408:             const prop = propsRuntimeDefaults.properties.find(
12409:               (node) => node.key.name === key
12410:             )
12411:             if (prop) {
12412:               if (prop.type === 'ObjectProperty') {
12413:                 // prop has corresponding static default value
12414:                 defaultString = `default: ${scriptSetupSource.slice(
12415:                   prop.value.start,
12416:                   prop.value.end
12417:                 )}`
12418:               } else {
12419:                 defaultString = `default() ${scriptSetupSource.slice(
12420:                   prop.body.start,
12421:                   prop.body.end
12422:                 )}`
12423:               }
12424:             }
12425:           }
12426:   
12427:           const { type, required } = props[key]
12428:           if (!isProd) {
12429:             return `${key}: { type: ${toRuntimeTypeString(
12430:               type
12431:             )}, required: ${required}${
12432:               defaultString ? `, ${defaultString}` : ``
12433:             } }`
12434:           } else if (
12435:             type.some(
12436:               el => el === 'Boolean' || (defaultString && el === 'Function')
12437:             )
12438:           ) {
12439:             // #4783 production: if boolean or defaultString and function exists, should keep the type.
12440:             return `${key}: { type: ${toRuntimeTypeString(type)}${
12441:               defaultString ? `, ${defaultString}` : ``
12442:             } }`
12443:           } else {
12444:             // production: checks are useless
12445:             return `${key}: ${defaultString ? `{ ${defaultString} }` : 'null'}`
12446:           }
12447:         })
12448:         .join(',\n    ')}\n  }`
12449:   
12450:       if (propsRuntimeDefaults && !hasStaticDefaults) {
12451:         propsDecls = `${helper('mergeDefaults')}(${propsDecls}, ${source.slice(
12452:           propsRuntimeDefaults.start + startOffset,
12453:           propsRuntimeDefaults.end + startOffset
12454:         )})`
12455:       }
12456:   
12457:       return `\n  props: ${propsDecls},`
12458:     }
12459:   
12460:   
12461:   function genDestructuredDefaultValue(key) {
12462:       const destructured = propsDestructuredBindings[key]
12463:       if (destructured && destructured.default) {
12464:         const value = scriptSetup.content.slice(
12465:           destructured.default.start,
12466:           destructured.default.end
12467:         )
12468:         const isLiteral = destructured.default.type.endsWith('Literal')
12469:         return isLiteral ? value : `() => ${value}`
12470:       }
12471:     }
12472:   
12473:     function genSetupPropsType(node) {
12474:       const scriptSetupSource = scriptSetup.content
12475:       if (hasStaticWithDefaults()) {
12476:         // if withDefaults() is used, we need to remove the optional flags
12477:         // on props that have default values
12478:         let res = `{ `
12479:         const members = node.type === 'TSTypeLiteral' ? node.members : node.body
12480:         for (const m of members) {
12481:           if (
12482:             (m.type === 'TSPropertySignature' ||
12483:               m.type === 'TSMethodSignature') &&
12484:             m.typeAnnotation &&
12485:             m.key.type === 'Identifier'
12486:           ) {
12487:             if (
12488:               propsRuntimeDefaults.properties.some(
12489:                 (p) => p.key.name === m.key.name
12490:               )
12491:             ) {
12492:               res +=
12493:                 m.key.name +
12494:                 (m.type === 'TSMethodSignature' ? '()' : '') +
12495:                 scriptSetupSource.slice(
12496:                   m.typeAnnotation.start,
12497:                   m.typeAnnotation.end
12498:                 ) +
12499:                 ', '
12500:             } else {
12501:               res +=
12502:                 scriptSetupSource.slice(m.start, m.typeAnnotation.end) + `, `
12503:             }
12504:           }
12505:         }
12506:         return (res.length ? res.slice(0, -2) : res) + ` }`
12507:       } else {
12508:         return scriptSetupSource.slice(node.start, node.end)
12509:       }
12510:     }
12511:   function processNormalScript() {
12512:     let scriptAst
12513:     if (script) {
12514:       scriptAst = parse(
12515:         script.content,
12516:         {
12517:           plugins,
12518:           sourceType: 'module'
12519:         },
12520:         scriptStartOffset
12521:       )
12522:   
12523:       for (const node of scriptAst.body) {
12524:         if (node.type === 'ImportDeclaration') {
12525:           // record imports for dedupe
12526:           for (const specifier of node.specifiers) {
12527:             const imported =
12528:               specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier' &&
12529:               specifier.imported.type === 'Identifier' &&
12530:               specifier.imported.name
12531:             registerUserImport(
12532:               node.source.value,
12533:               specifier.local.name,
12534:               imported,
12535:               node.importKind === 'type' ||
12536:                 (specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier' &&
12537:                   specifier.importKind === 'type'),
12538:               false
12539:             )
12540:           }
12541:         } else if (node.type === 'ExportDefaultDeclaration') {
12542:           // export default
12543:           defaultExport = node
12544:           // export default { ... } --> const __default__ = { ... }
12545:           const start = node.start + scriptStartOffset
12546:           const end = node.declaration.start + scriptStartOffset
12547:           s.overwrite(start, end, `const ${DEFAULT_VAR} = `)
12548:         } else if (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration') {
12549:           const defaultSpecifier = node.specifiers.find(
12550:             s => s.exported.type === 'Identifier' && s.exported.name === 'default'
12551:           )
12552:           if (defaultSpecifier) {
12553:             defaultExport = node
12554:             // 1. remove specifier
12555:             if (node.specifiers.length > 1) {
12556:               s.remove(
12557:                 defaultSpecifier.start + scriptStartOffset,
12558:                 defaultSpecifier.end + scriptStartOffset
12559:               )
12560:             } else {
12561:               s.remove(
12562:                 node.start + scriptStartOffset,
12563:                 node.end + scriptStartOffset
12564:               )
12565:             }
12566:             if (node.source) {
12567:               // export { x as default } from './x'
12568:               // rewrite to `import { x as __default__ } from './x'` and
12569:               // add to top
12570:               s.prepend(
12571:                 `import { ${defaultSpecifier.local.name} as ${DEFAULT_VAR} } from '${node.source.value}'\n`
12572:               )
12573:             } else {
12574:               // export { x as default }
12575:               // rewrite to `const __default__ = x` and move to end
12576:               s.appendLeft(
12577:                 scriptEndOffset,
12578:                 `\nconst ${DEFAULT_VAR} = ${defaultSpecifier.local.name}\n`
12579:               )
12580:             }
12581:           }
12582:           if (node.declaration) {
12583:             walkDeclaration(node.declaration, scriptBindings, userImportAlias)
12584:           }
12585:         } else if (
12586:           (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration' ||
12587:             node.type === 'FunctionDeclaration' ||
12588:             node.type === 'ClassDeclaration' ||
12589:             node.type === 'TSEnumDeclaration') &&
12590:           !node.declare
12591:         ) {
12592:           walkDeclaration(node, scriptBindings, userImportAlias)
12593:         }
12594:       }
12595:   
12596:       // apply reactivity transform
12597:       if (enableReactivityTransform && RT.shouldTransform(script.content)) {
12598:         const { rootRefs, importedHelpers } = transformAST(
12599:           scriptAst,
12600:           s,
12601:           scriptStartOffset
12602:         )
12603:         refBindings = rootRefs
12604:         for (const h of importedHelpers) {
12605:           helperImports.add(h)
12606:         }
12607:       }
12608:   
12609:       // <script> after <script setup>
12610:       // we need to move the block up so that `const __default__` is
12611:       // declared before being used in the actual component definition
12612:       if (scriptStartOffset > startOffset) {
12613:         s.move(scriptStartOffset, scriptEndOffset, 0)
12614:       }
12615:     }
12616:   
12617:     return scriptAst
12618:   }
12619:   function processSetupScript() {
12620:     const scriptSetupAst = babelParser.parse(
12621:       scriptSetup.content,
12622:       {
12623:         plugins: [
12624:           ...plugins,
12625:           // allow top level await but only inside <script setup>
12626:           'topLevelAwait'
12627:         ],
12628:         sourceType: 'module'
12629:       },
12630:       startOffset
12631:     )
12632:   
12633:     for (const node of scriptSetupAst.body) {
12634:       const start = node.start + startOffset
12635:       let end = node.end + startOffset
12636:       // locate comment
12637:       if (node.trailingComments && node.trailingComments.length > 0) {
12638:         const lastCommentNode =
12639:           node.trailingComments[node.trailingComments.length - 1]
12640:         end = lastCommentNode.end + startOffset
12641:       }
12642:       // locate the end of whitespace between this statement and the next
12643:       while (end <= source.length) {
12644:         if (!/\s/.test(source.charAt(end))) {
12645:           break
12646:         }
12647:         end++
12648:       }
12649:   
12650:       // (Dropped) `ref: x` bindings
12651:       if (
12652:         node.type === 'LabeledStatement' &&
12653:         node.label.name === 'ref' &&
12654:         node.body.type === 'ExpressionStatement'
12655:       ) {
12656:         error(
12657:           `ref sugar using the label syntax was an experimental proposal and ` +
12658:             `has been dropped based on community feedback. Please check out ` +
12659:             `the new proposal at https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/discussions/369`,
12660:           node
12661:         )
12662:       }
12663:   
12664:       if (node.type === 'ImportDeclaration') {
12665:         // import declarations are moved to top
12666:         s.move(start, end, 0)
12667:   
12668:         // dedupe imports
12669:         let removed = 0
12670:         const removeSpecifier = (i) => {
12671:           const removeLeft = i > removed
12672:           removed++
12673:           const current = node.specifiers[i]
12674:           const next = node.specifiers[i + 1]
12675:           s.remove(
12676:             removeLeft
12677:               ? node.specifiers[i - 1].end + startOffset
12678:               : current.start + startOffset,
12679:             next && !removeLeft
12680:               ? next.start + startOffset
12681:               : current.end + startOffset
12682:           )
12683:         }
12684:   
12685:         for (let i = 0; i < node.specifiers.length; i++) {
12686:           const specifier = node.specifiers[i]
12687:           const local = specifier.local.name
12688:           const imported =
12689:             specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier' &&
12690:             specifier.imported.type === 'Identifier' &&
12691:             specifier.imported.name
12692:           const source = node.source.value
12693:           const existing = userImports[local]
12694:           if (
12695:             source === 'vue' &&
12696:             (imported === DEFINE_PROPS ||
12697:               imported === DEFINE_EMITS ||
12698:               imported === DEFINE_EXPOSE)
12699:           ) {
12700:             removeSpecifier(i)
12701:           } else if (existing) {
12702:             if (existing.source === source && existing.imported === imported) {
12703:               // already imported in <script setup>, dedupe
12704:               removeSpecifier(i)
12705:             } else {
12706:               error(`different imports aliased to same local name.`, specifier)
12707:             }
12708:           } else {
12709:             registerUserImport(
12710:               source,
12711:               local,
12712:               imported,
12713:               node.importKind === 'type' ||
12714:                 (specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier' &&
12715:                   specifier.importKind === 'type'),
12716:               true
12717:             )
12718:           }
12719:         }
12720:         if (node.specifiers.length && removed === node.specifiers.length) {
12721:           s.remove(node.start + startOffset, node.end + startOffset)
12722:         }
12723:       }
12724:   
12725:       if (node.type === 'ExpressionStatement') {
12726:         // process `defineProps` and `defineEmit(s)` calls
12727:         if (
12728:           processDefineProps(node.expression) ||
12729:           processDefineEmits(node.expression) ||
12730:           processWithDefaults(node.expression)
12731:         ) {
12732:           s.remove(node.start + startOffset, node.end + startOffset)
12733:         } else if (processDefineExpose(node.expression)) {
12734:           // defineExpose({}) -> expose({})
12735:           const callee = node.expression.callee
12736:           s.overwrite(
12737:             callee.start + startOffset,
12738:             callee.end + startOffset,
12739:             'expose'
12740:           )
12741:         }
12742:       }
12743:   
12744:       if (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration' && !node.declare) {
12745:         const total = node.declarations.length
12746:         let left = total
12747:         for (let i = 0; i < total; i++) {
12748:           const decl = node.declarations[i]
12749:           if (decl.init) {
12750:             // defineProps / defineEmits
12751:             const isDefineProps =
12752:               processDefineProps(decl.init, decl.id) ||
12753:               processWithDefaults(decl.init, decl.id)
12754:             const isDefineEmits = processDefineEmits(decl.init, decl.id)
12755:             if (isDefineProps || isDefineEmits) {
12756:               if (left === 1) {
12757:                 s.remove(node.start + startOffset, node.end + startOffset)
12758:               } else {
12759:                 let start = decl.start + startOffset
12760:                 let end = decl.end + startOffset
12761:                 if (i < total - 1) {
12762:                   // not the last one, locate the start of the next
12763:                   end = node.declarations[i + 1].start + startOffset
12764:                 } else {
12765:                   // last one, locate the end of the prev
12766:                   start = node.declarations[i - 1].end + startOffset
12767:                 }
12768:                 s.remove(start, end)
12769:                 left--
12770:               }
12771:             }
12772:           }
12773:         }
12774:       }
12775:   
12776:       // walk declarations to record declared bindings
12777:       if (
12778:         (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration' ||
12779:           node.type === 'FunctionDeclaration' ||
12780:           node.type === 'ClassDeclaration') &&
12781:         !node.declare
12782:       ) {
12783:         walkDeclaration(node, setupBindings, userImportAlias)
12784:       }
12785:   
12786:       // walk statements & named exports / variable declarations for top level
12787:       // await
12788:       if (
12789:         (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration' && !node.declare) ||
12790:         node.type.endsWith('Statement')
12791:       ) {
12792:         walk(node, {
12793:           enter(child, parent) {
12794:             if (isFunctionType(child)) {
12795:               this.skip()
12796:             }
12797:             if (child.type === 'AwaitExpression') {
12798:               hasAwait = true
12799:               const needsSemi = scriptSetupAst.body.some(n => {
12800:                 return n.type === 'ExpressionStatement' && n.start === child.start
12801:               })
12802:               processAwait(
12803:                 child,
12804:                 needsSemi,
12805:                 parent.type === 'ExpressionStatement'
12806:               )
12807:             }
12808:           }
12809:         })
12810:       }
12811:   
12812:       if (
12813:         (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' && node.exportKind !== 'type') ||
12814:         node.type === 'ExportAllDeclaration' ||
12815:         node.type === 'ExportDefaultDeclaration'
12816:       ) {
12817:         error(
12818:           `<script setup> cannot contain ES module exports. ` +
12819:             `If you are using a previous version of <script setup>, please ` +
12820:             `consult the updated RFC at https://github.com/vuejs/rfcs/pull/227.`,
12821:           node
12822:         )
12823:       }
12824:   
12825:       if (isTS) {
12826:         // runtime enum
12827:         if (node.type === 'TSEnumDeclaration') {
12828:           registerBinding(setupBindings, node.id, BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST)
12829:         }
12830:   
12831:         // move all Type declarations to outer scope
12832:         if (
12833:           node.type.startsWith('TS') ||
12834:           (node.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' &&
12835:             node.exportKind === 'type') ||
12836:           (node.type === 'VariableDeclaration' && node.declare)
12837:         ) {
12838:           recordType(node, declaredTypes)
12839:           s.move(start, end, 0)
12840:         }
12841:       }
12842:     }
12843:   
12844:     return scriptSetupAst
12845:   }
12846:   function applyReactivityTransform() {
12847:     if (
12848:       (enableReactivityTransform &&
12849:         // normal <script> had ref bindings that maybe used in <script setup>
12850:         (refBindings || RT.shouldTransform(scriptSetup.content))) ||
12851:       propsDestructureDecl
12852:     ) {
12853:       const { rootRefs, importedHelpers } = transformAST(
12854:         scriptSetupAst,
12855:         s,
12856:         startOffset,
12857:         refBindings,
12858:         propsDestructuredBindings
12859:       )
12860:       refBindings = refBindings ? [...refBindings, ...rootRefs] : rootRefs
12861:       for (const h of importedHelpers) {
12862:         helperImports.add(h)
12863:       }
12864:     }
12865:   }
12866:   function extractRuntimePropsEmits() {
12867:     if (propsTypeDecl) {
12868:       extractRuntimeProps(propsTypeDecl, typeDeclaredProps, declaredTypes, isProd)
12869:     }
12870:     if (emitsTypeDecl) {
12871:       extractRuntimeEmits(emitsTypeDecl, typeDeclaredEmits)
12872:     }
12873:   }
12874:   function checkUseOptions() {
12875:     checkInvalidScopeReference(propsRuntimeDecl, DEFINE_PROPS)
12876:     checkInvalidScopeReference(propsRuntimeDefaults, DEFINE_PROPS)
12877:     checkInvalidScopeReference(propsDestructureDecl, DEFINE_PROPS)
12878:     checkInvalidScopeReference(emitsRuntimeDecl, DEFINE_PROPS)
12879:   }
12880:   function removeNonScriptContent() {
12881:     if (script) {
12882:       if (startOffset < scriptStartOffset) {
12883:         // <script setup> before <script>
12884:         s.remove(0, startOffset)
12885:         s.remove(endOffset, scriptStartOffset)
12886:         s.remove(scriptEndOffset, source.length)
12887:       } else {
12888:         // <script> before <script setup>
12889:         s.remove(0, scriptStartOffset)
12890:         s.remove(scriptEndOffset, startOffset)
12891:         s.remove(endOffset, source.length)
12892:       }
12893:     } else {
12894:       // only <script setup>
12895:       s.remove(0, startOffset)
12896:       s.remove(endOffset, source.length)
12897:     }
12898:   }
12899:   function analyzeBindingMetadata() {
12900:     if (scriptAst) {
12901:       Object.assign(bindingMetadata, analyzeScriptBindings(scriptAst.body))
12902:     }
12903:     if (propsRuntimeDecl) {
12904:       for (const key of getObjectOrArrayExpressionKeys(propsRuntimeDecl)) {
12905:         bindingMetadata[key] = BindingTypes.PROPS
12906:       }
12907:     }
12908:     for (const key in typeDeclaredProps) {
12909:       bindingMetadata[key] = BindingTypes.PROPS
12910:     }
12911:     // props aliases
12912:     if (propsDestructureDecl) {
12913:       if (propsDestructureRestId) {
12914:         bindingMetadata[propsDestructureRestId] = BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
12915:       }
12916:       for (const key in propsDestructuredBindings) {
12917:         const { local } = propsDestructuredBindings[key]
12918:         if (local !== key) {
12919:           bindingMetadata[local] = BindingTypes.PROPS_ALIASED
12920:           ;(bindingMetadata.__propsAliases ||
12921:             (bindingMetadata.__propsAliases = {}))[local] = key
12922:         }
12923:       }
12924:     }
12925:     for (const [key, { isType, imported, source }] of Object.entries(
12926:       userImports
12927:     )) {
12928:       if (isType) continue
12929:       bindingMetadata[key] =
12930:         (imported === 'default' && source.endsWith('.vue')) || source === 'vue'
12931:           ? BindingTypes.SETUP_CONST
12932:           : BindingTypes.SETUP_MAYBE_REF
12933:     }
12934:     for (const key in scriptBindings) {
12935:       bindingMetadata[key] = scriptBindings[key]
12936:     }
12937:     for (const key in setupBindings) {
12938:       bindingMetadata[key] = setupBindings[key]
12939:     }
12940:     // known ref bindings
12941:     if (refBindings) {
12942:       for (const key of refBindings) {
12943:         bindingMetadata[key] = BindingTypes.SETUP_REF
12944:       }
12945:     }
12946:   }
12947:   function injectUseCssVarsCalls() {
12948:     if (cssVars.length) {
12949:       helperImports.add(CSS_VARS_HELPER)
12950:       helperImports.add('unref')
12951:       s.prependRight(
12952:         startOffset,
12953:         `\n${genCssVarsCode(cssVars, bindingMetadata, scopeId, isProd)}\n`
12954:       )
12955:     }
12956:   }
12957:   function finalizeSetupArgumentSignature() {
12958:     if (propsTypeDecl) {
12959:       // mark as any and only cast on assignment
12960:       // since the user defined complex types may be incompatible with the
12961:       // inferred type from generated runtime declarations
12962:       args += `: any`
12963:     }
12964:     // inject user assignment of props
12965:     // we use a default __props so that template expressions referencing props
12966:     // can use it directly
12967:     if (propsIdentifier) {
12968:       s.prependLeft(
12969:         startOffset,
12970:         `\nconst ${propsIdentifier} = __props${
12971:           propsTypeDecl ? ` as ${genSetupPropsType(propsTypeDecl)}` : ``
12972:         }\n`
12973:       )
12974:     }
12975:     if (propsDestructureRestId) {
12976:       s.prependLeft(
12977:         startOffset,
12978:         `\nconst ${propsDestructureRestId} = ${helper(
12979:           `createPropsRestProxy`
12980:         )}(__props, ${JSON.stringify(Object.keys(propsDestructuredBindings))})\n`
12981:       )
12982:     }
12983:     // inject temp variables for async context preservation
12984:     if (hasAwait) {
12985:       const any = isTS ? `: any` : ``
12986:       s.prependLeft(startOffset, `\nlet __temp${any}, __restore${any}\n`)
12987:     }
12988:   
12989:     const destructureElements =
12990:       hasDefineExposeCall || !options.inlineTemplate ? [`expose`] : []
12991:     if (emitIdentifier) {
12992:       destructureElements.push(
12993:         emitIdentifier === `emit` ? `emit` : `emit: ${emitIdentifier}`
12994:       )
12995:     }
12996:     if (destructureElements.length) {
12997:       args += `, { ${destructureElements.join(', ')} }`
12998:       if (emitsTypeDecl) {
12999:         args += `: { emit: (${scriptSetup.content.slice(
13000:           emitsTypeDecl.start,
13001:           emitsTypeDecl.end
13002:         )}), expose: any, slots: any, attrs: any }`
13003:       }
13004:     }
13005:   }
13006:   function finalizeSetupArgumentSignature() {
13007:     if (propsTypeDecl) {
13008:       // mark as any and only cast on assignment
13009:       // since the user defined complex types may be incompatible with the
13010:       // inferred type from generated runtime declarations
13011:       args += `: any`
13012:     }
13013:     // inject user assignment of props
13014:     // we use a default __props so that template expressions referencing props
13015:     // can use it directly
13016:     if (propsIdentifier) {
13017:       s.prependLeft(
13018:         startOffset,
13019:         `\nconst ${propsIdentifier} = __props${
13020:           propsTypeDecl ? ` as ${genSetupPropsType(propsTypeDecl)}` : ``
13021:         }\n`
13022:       )
13023:     }
13024:     if (propsDestructureRestId) {
13025:       s.prependLeft(
13026:         startOffset,
13027:         `\nconst ${propsDestructureRestId} = ${helper(
13028:           `createPropsRestProxy`
13029:         )}(__props, ${JSON.stringify(Object.keys(propsDestructuredBindings))})\n`
13030:       )
13031:     }
13032:     // inject temp variables for async context preservation
13033:     if (hasAwait) {
13034:       const any = isTS ? `: any` : ``
13035:       s.prependLeft(startOffset, `\nlet __temp${any}, __restore${any}\n`)
13036:     }
13037:   
13038:     const destructureElements =
13039:       hasDefineExposeCall || !options.inlineTemplate ? [`expose`] : []
13040:     if (emitIdentifier) {
13041:       destructureElements.push(
13042:         emitIdentifier === `emit` ? `emit` : `emit: ${emitIdentifier}`
13043:       )
13044:     }
13045:     if (destructureElements.length) {
13046:       args += `, { ${destructureElements.join(', ')} }`
13047:       if (emitsTypeDecl) {
13048:         args += `: { emit: (${scriptSetup.content.slice(
13049:           emitsTypeDecl.start,
13050:           emitsTypeDecl.end
13051:         )}), expose: any, slots: any, attrs: any }`
13052:       }
13053:     }
13054:   }
13055:   function generateReturnStatement() {
13056:     if (options.inlineTemplate) {
13057:       if (sfc.template && !sfc.template.src) {
13058:         if (options.templateOptions && options.templateOptions.ssr) {
13059:           hasInlinedSsrRenderFn = true
13060:         }
13061:         // inline render function mode - we are going to compile the template and
13062:         // inline it right here
13063:         const { code, ast, preamble, tips, errors } = compileTemplate({
13064:           filename,
13065:           source: sfc.template.content,
13066:           inMap: sfc.template.map,
13067:           ...options.templateOptions,
13068:           id: scopeId,
13069:           scoped: sfc.styles.some(s => s.scoped),
13070:           isProd: options.isProd,
13071:           ssrCssVars: sfc.cssVars,
13072:           compilerOptions: {
13073:             ...(options.templateOptions &&
13074:               options.templateOptions.compilerOptions),
13075:             inline: true,
13076:             isTS,
13077:             bindingMetadata
13078:           }
13079:         })
13080:   
13081:         const err = errors[0]
13082:         if (typeof err === 'string') {
13083:           throw new Error(err)
13084:         } else if (err) {
13085:           if (err.loc) {
13086:             err.message +=
13087:               `\n\n` +
13088:               sfc.filename +
13089:               '\n' +
13090:               generateCodeFrame(
13091:                 source,
13092:                 err.loc.start.offset,
13093:                 err.loc.end.offset
13094:               ) +
13095:               `\n`
13096:           }
13097:           throw err
13098:         }
13099:         if (preamble) {
13100:           s.prepend(preamble)
13101:         }
13102:         // avoid duplicated unref import
13103:         // as this may get injected by the render function preamble OR the
13104:         // css vars codegen
13105:         if (ast && ast.helpers.includes(UNREF)) {
13106:           helperImports.delete('unref')
13107:         }
13108:         returned = code
13109:       } else {
13110:         returned = `() => {}`
13111:       }
13112:     } else {
13113:       // return bindings from script and script setup
13114:       const allBindings= {
13115:         ...scriptBindings,
13116:         ...setupBindings
13117:       }
13118:       for (const key in userImports) {
13119:         if (!userImports[key].isType && userImports[key].isUsedInTemplate) {
13120:           allBindings[key] = true
13121:         }
13122:       }
13123:       returned = `{ ${Object.keys(allBindings).join(', ')} }`
13124:     }
13125:   
13126:     if (!options.inlineTemplate) {
13127:       // in non-inline mode, the `__isScriptSetup: true` flag is used by
13128:       // componentPublicInstance proxy to allow properties that start with $ or _
13129:       s.appendRight(
13130:         endOffset,
13131:         `\nconst __returned__ = ${returned}\n` +
13132:           `Object.defineProperty(__returned__, '__isScriptSetup', { enumerable: false, value: true })\n` +
13133:           `return __returned__` +
13134:           `\n}\n\n`
13135:       )
13136:     } else {
13137:       s.appendRight(endOffset, `\nreturn ${returned}\n}\n\n`)
13138:     }
13139:   }
13140:   function finalizeDefaultExport() {
13141:     let runtimeOptions = ``
13142:     if (hasInlinedSsrRenderFn) {
13143:       runtimeOptions += `\n  __ssrInlineRender: true,`
13144:     }
13145:     if (propsRuntimeDecl) {
13146:       let declCode = scriptSetup.content
13147:         .slice(propsRuntimeDecl.start, propsRuntimeDecl.end)
13148:         .trim()
13149:       if (propsDestructureDecl) {
13150:         const defaults = []
13151:         for (const key in propsDestructuredBindings) {
13152:           const d = genDestructuredDefaultValue(key)
13153:           if (d) defaults.push(`${key}: ${d}`)
13154:         }
13155:         if (defaults.length) {
13156:           declCode = `${helper(
13157:             `mergeDefaults`
13158:           )}(${declCode}, {\n  ${defaults.join(',\n  ')}\n})`
13159:         }
13160:       }
13161:       runtimeOptions += `\n  props: ${declCode},`
13162:     } else if (propsTypeDecl) {
13163:       runtimeOptions += genRuntimeProps(typeDeclaredProps)
13164:     }
13165:     if (emitsRuntimeDecl) {
13166:       runtimeOptions += `\n  emits: ${scriptSetup.content
13167:         .slice(emitsRuntimeDecl.start, emitsRuntimeDecl.end)
13168:         .trim()},`
13169:     } else if (emitsTypeDecl) {
13170:       runtimeOptions += genRuntimeEmits(typeDeclaredEmits)
13171:     }
13172:   
13173:     // <script setup> components are closed by default. If the user did not
13174:     // explicitly call `defineExpose`, call expose() with no args.
13175:     const exposeCall =
13176:       hasDefineExposeCall || options.inlineTemplate ? `` : `  expose();\n`
13177:     // wrap setup code with function.
13178:     if (isTS) {
13179:       // for TS, make sure the exported type is still valid type with
13180:       // correct props information
13181:       // we have to use object spread for types to be merged properly
13182:       // user's TS setting should compile it down to proper targets
13183:       // export default defineComponent({ ...__default__, ... })
13184:       const def = defaultExport ? `\n  ...${DEFAULT_VAR},` : ``
13185:       s.prependLeft(
13186:         startOffset,
13187:         `\nexport default /*#__PURE__*/${helper(
13188:           `defineComponent`
13189:         )}({${def}${runtimeOptions}\n  ${
13190:           hasAwait ? `async ` : ``
13191:         }setup(${args}) {\n${exposeCall}`
13192:       )
13193:       s.appendRight(endOffset, `})`)
13194:     } else {
13195:       if (defaultExport) {
13196:         // without TS, can't rely on rest spread, so we use Object.assign
13197:         // export default Object.assign(__default__, { ... })
13198:         s.prependLeft(
13199:           startOffset,
13200:           `\nexport default /*#__PURE__*/Object.assign(${DEFAULT_VAR}, {${runtimeOptions}\n  ` +
13201:             `${hasAwait ? `async ` : ``}setup(${args}) {\n${exposeCall}`
13202:         )
13203:         s.appendRight(endOffset, `})`)
13204:       } else {
13205:         s.prependLeft(
13206:           startOffset,
13207:           `\nexport default {${runtimeOptions}\n  ` +
13208:             `${hasAwait ? `async ` : ``}setup(${args}) {\n${exposeCall}`
13209:         )
13210:         s.appendRight(endOffset, `}`)
13211:       }
13212:     }
13213:   }
13214:   function finalizeVueHelperImports() {
13215:     if (helperImports.size > 0) {
13216:       s.prepend(
13217:         `import { ${[...helperImports]
13218:           .map(h => `${h} as _${h}`)
13219:           .join(', ')} } from 'vue'\n`
13220:       )
13221:     }
13222:   }
13223: 
13224:   // 1. process normal <script> first if it exists
13225:   let scriptAst = processNormalScript()
13226:   // 2. parse <script setup> and  walk over top level statements
13227:   const scriptSetupAst = processSetupScript()
13228: 
13229:   // 3. Apply reactivity transform
13230:   applyReactivityTransform()
13231:   // 4. extract runtime props/emits code from setup context type
13232:   extractRuntimePropsEmits()
13233:   // 5. check useOptions args to make sure it doesn't reference setup scope
13234:   // variables
13235:   checkUseOptions()
13236:   // 6. remove non-script content
13237:   removeNonScriptContent()
13238:   // 7. analyze binding metadata
13239:   analyzeBindingMetadata()
13240:   // 8. inject `useCssVars` calls
13241:   injectUseCssVarsCalls()
13242:   // 9. finalize setup() argument signature
13243:   let args = `__props`
13244:   finalizeSetupArgumentSignature()
13245:   // 10. generate return statement
13246:   let returned
13247:   generateReturnStatement()
13248:   // 11. finalize default export
13249:   let runtimeOptions = ''
13250:   finalizeDefaultExport()
13251:   // 12. finalize Vue helper imports
13252:   finalizeVueHelperImports()
13253: 
13254:   s.trim()
13255: 
13256:   return {
13257:     ...scriptSetup,
13258:     bindings: bindingMetadata,
13259:     imports: userImports,
13260:     content: s.toString(),
13261:     map: genSourceMap
13262:       ? (s.generateMap({
13263:           source: filename,
13264:           hires: true,
13265:           includeContent: true
13266:         }))
13267:       : undefined,
13268:     scriptAst: scriptAst?.body,
13269:     scriptSetupAst: scriptSetupAst?.body
13270:   }
13271: }

 2: const __ESM_BROWSER__ = false, __GLOBAL__ = true
 3: let MagicString = require(process.env.NODE_LIB + '/magic-string')

 5: function createCache(size = 500) {
 6:   return new Map()

 9: <<rewriteDefault>>
10: <<reactivity-transform>>
11: 
12: const range = 2
13: 
14: function generateCodeFrame(
15:   source,
16:   start = 0,
17:   end = source.length
18: ) {
19:   // Split the content into individual lines but capture the newline sequence
20:   // that separated each line. This is important because the actual sequence is
21:   // needed to properly take into account the full line length for offset
22:   // comparison
23:   let lines = source.split(/(\r?\n)/)
24: 
25:   // Separate the lines and newline sequences into separate arrays for easier referencing
26:   const newlineSequences = lines.filter((_, idx) => idx % 2 === 1)
27:   lines = lines.filter((_, idx) => idx % 2 === 0)
28: 
29:   let count = 0
30:   const res = []
31:   for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
32:     count +=
33:       lines[i].length +
34:       ((newlineSequences[i] && newlineSequences[i].length) || 0)
35:     if (count >= start) {
36:       for (let j = i - range; j <= i + range || end > count; j++) {
37:         if (j < 0 || j >= lines.length) continue
38:         const line = j + 1
39:         res.push(
40:           `${line}${' '.repeat(Math.max(3 - String(line).length, 0))}|  ${
41:             lines[j]
42:           }`
43:         )
44:         const lineLength = lines[j].length
45:         const newLineSeqLength =
46:           (newlineSequences[j] && newlineSequences[j].length) || 0
47: 
48:         if (j === i) {
49:           // push underline
50:           const pad = start - (count - (lineLength + newLineSeqLength))
51:           const length = Math.max(
52:             1,
53:             end > count ? lineLength - pad : end - start
54:           )
55:           res.push(`   |  ` + ' '.repeat(pad) + '^'.repeat(length))
56:         } else if (j > i) {
57:           if (end > count) {
58:             const length = Math.max(Math.min(end - count, lineLength), 1)
59:             res.push(`   |  ` + '^'.repeat(length))
60:           }
61: 
62:           count += lineLength + newLineSeqLength
63:         }
64:       }
65:       break
66:     }
67:   }
68:   return res.join('\n')
69: }
70:

1.1. reactivity-transform

core/README.md at main vuejs/core

script setup $ref(), $computed, $shallowRef(), $customRef(), $toRef(), import ... from "vue" 

  1: const RT = (function() {
  2:   const CONVERT_SYMBOL = '$'
  3: const ESCAPE_SYMBOL = '$$'
  4: const shorthands = ['ref', 'computed', 'shallowRef', 'toRef', 'customRef']
  5: const transformCheckRE = /[^\w]\$(?:\$|ref|computed|shallowRef)?\s*(\(|\<)/
  6: 
  7: function shouldTransform(src) {
  8:   return transformCheckRE.test(src)
  9: }
 10: 
 11: function transform(
 12:   src,
 13:   {
 14:     filename,
 15:     sourceMap,
 16:     parserPlugins,
 17:     importHelpersFrom = 'vue'
 18:   } = {}
 19: ) {
 20:   const plugins = parserPlugins || []
 21:   if (filename) {
 22:     if (/\.tsx?$/.test(filename)) {
 23:       plugins.push('typescript')
 24:     }
 25:     if (filename.endsWith('x')) {
 26:       plugins.push('jsx')
 27:     }
 28:   }
 29: 
 30:   const ast = babelParser.parse(src, {
 31:     sourceType: 'module',
 32:     plugins
 33:   })
 34:   const s = new MagicString(src)
 35:   const res = transformAST(ast.program, s, 0)
 36: 
 37:   // inject helper imports
 38:   if (res.importedHelpers.length) {
 39:     s.prepend(
 40:       `import { ${res.importedHelpers
 41:         .map(h => `${h} as _${h}`)
 42:         .join(', ')} } from '${importHelpersFrom}'\n`
 43:     )
 44:   }
 45: 
 46:   return {
 47:     ...res,
 48:     code: s.toString(),
 49:     map: sourceMap
 50:       ? s.generateMap({
 51:           source: filename,
 52:           hires: true,
 53:           includeContent: true
 54:         })
 55:       : null
 56:   }
 57: }
 58: 
 59: function transformAST(
 60:   ast,
 61:   s,
 62:   offset = 0,
 63:   knownRefs,
 64:   knownProps
 65: ) {
 66:   let convertSymbol = CONVERT_SYMBOL
 67:   let escapeSymbol = ESCAPE_SYMBOL
 68: 
 69:   // macro import handling
 70:   for (const node of ast.body) {
 71:     if (
 72:       node.type === 'ImportDeclaration' &&
 73:       node.source.value === 'vue/macros'
 74:     ) {
 75:       // remove macro imports
 76:       s.remove(node.start + offset, node.end + offset)
 77:       // check aliasing
 78:       for (const specifier of node.specifiers) {
 79:         if (specifier.type === 'ImportSpecifier') {
 80:           const imported = specifier.imported.name
 81:           const local = specifier.local.name
 82:           if (local !== imported) {
 83:             if (imported === ESCAPE_SYMBOL) {
 84:               escapeSymbol = local
 85:             } else if (imported === CONVERT_SYMBOL) {
 86:               convertSymbol = local
 87:             } else {
 88:               error(
 89:                 `macro imports for ref-creating methods do not support aliasing.`,
 90:                 specifier
 91:               )
 92:             }
 93:           }
 94:         }
 95:       }
 96:     }
 97:   }
 98: 
 99:   const importedHelpers = new Set()
100:   const rootScope = {}
101:   const scopeStack = [rootScope]
102:   let currentScope = rootScope
103:   let escapeScope // inside $$()
104:   const excludedIds = new WeakSet()
105:   const parentStack = []
106:   const propsLocalToPublicMap = Object.create(null)
107: 
108:   if (knownRefs) {
109:     for (const key of knownRefs) {
110:       rootScope[key] = true
111:     }
112:   }
113:   if (knownProps) {
114:     for (const key in knownProps) {
115:       const { local } = knownProps[key]
116:       rootScope[local] = 'prop'
117:       propsLocalToPublicMap[local] = key
118:     }
119:   }
120: 
121:   function isRefCreationCall(callee) {
122:     if (callee === convertSymbol) {
123:       return convertSymbol
124:     }
125:     if (callee[0] === '$' && shorthands.includes(callee.slice(1))) {
126:       return callee
127:     }
128:     return false
129:   }
130: 
131:   function error(msg, node) {
132:     const e = new Error(msg)
133:     e.node = node
134:     throw e
135:   }
136: 
137:   function helper(msg) {
138:     importedHelpers.add(msg)
139:     return `_${msg}`
140:   }
141: 
142:   function registerBinding(id, isRef = false) {
143:     excludedIds.add(id)
144:     if (currentScope) {
145:       currentScope[id.name] = isRef
146:     } else {
147:       error(
148:         'registerBinding called without active scope, something is wrong.',
149:         id
150:       )
151:     }
152:   }
153: 
154:   const registerRefBinding = (id) => registerBinding(id, true)
155: 
156:   let tempVarCount = 0
157:   function genTempVar() {
158:     return `__$temp_${++tempVarCount}`
159:   }
160: 
161:   function snip(nod) {
162:     return s.original.slice(node.start + offset, node.end + offset)
163:   }
164: 
165:   function walkScope(node, isRoot = false) {
166:     for (const stmt of node.body) {
167:       if (stmt.type === 'VariableDeclaration') {
168:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt, isRoot)
169:       } else if (
170:         stmt.type === 'FunctionDeclaration' ||
171:         stmt.type === 'ClassDeclaration'
172:       ) {
173:         if (stmt.declare || !stmt.id) continue
174:         registerBinding(stmt.id)
175:       } else if (
176:         (stmt.type === 'ForOfStatement' || stmt.type === 'ForInStatement') &&
177:         stmt.left.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
178:       ) {
179:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.left)
180:       } else if (
181:         stmt.type === 'ExportNamedDeclaration' &&
182:         stmt.declaration &&
183:         stmt.declaration.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
184:       ) {
185:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.declaration, isRoot)
186:       } else if (
187:         stmt.type === 'LabeledStatement' &&
188:         stmt.body.type === 'VariableDeclaration'
189:       ) {
190:         walkVariableDeclaration(stmt.body, isRoot)
191:       }
192:     }
193:   }
194: 
195:   function walkVariableDeclaration(stmt, isRoot = false) {
196:     if (stmt.declare) {
197:       return
198:     }
199:     for (const decl of stmt.declarations) {
200:       let refCall
201:       const isCall =
202:         decl.init &&
203:         decl.init.type === 'CallExpression' &&
204:         decl.init.callee.type === 'Identifier'
205:       if (
206:         isCall &&
207:         (refCall = isRefCreationCall(decl.init.callee.name))
208:       ) {
209:         processRefDeclaration(refCall, decl.id, decl.init)
210:       } else {
211:         const isProps =
212:           isRoot && isCall && decl.init.callee.name === 'defineProps'
213:         for (const id of extractIdentifiers(decl.id)) {
214:           if (isProps) {
215:             // for defineProps destructure, only exclude them since they
216:             // are already passed in as knownProps
217:             excludedIds.add(id)
218:           } else {
219:             registerBinding(id)
220:           }
221:         }
222:       }
223:     }
224:   }
225: 
226:   function processRefDeclaration(method, id, call) {
227:     excludedIds.add(call.callee)
228:     if (method === convertSymbol) {
229:       // $
230:       // remove macro
231:       s.remove(call.callee.start + offset, call.callee.end + offset)
232:       if (id.type === 'Identifier') {
233:         // single variable
234:         registerRefBinding(id)
235:       } else if (id.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
236:         processRefObjectPattern(id, call)
237:       } else if (id.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
238:         processRefArrayPattern(id, call)
239:       }
240:     } else {
241:       // shorthands
242:       if (id.type === 'Identifier') {
243:         registerRefBinding(id)
244:         // replace call
245:         s.overwrite(
246:           call.start + offset,
247:           call.start + method.length + offset,
248:           helper(method.slice(1))
249:         )
250:       } else {
251:         error(`${method}() cannot be used with destructure patterns.`, call)
252:       }
253:     }
254:   }
255: 
256:   function processRefObjectPattern(pattern, call, tempVar, path = []) {
257:     if (!tempVar) {
258:       tempVar = genTempVar()
259:       // const { x } = $(useFoo()) --> const __$temp_1 = useFoo()
260:       s.overwrite(pattern.start + offset, pattern.end + offset, tempVar)
261:     }
262: 
263:     for (const p of pattern.properties) {
264:       let nameId
265:       let key
266:       let defaultValue
267:       if (p.type === 'ObjectProperty') {
268:         if (p.key.start === p.value.start) {
269:           // shorthand { foo }
270:           nameId = p.key
271:           if (p.value.type === 'Identifier') {
272:             // avoid shorthand value identifier from being processed
273:             excludedIds.add(p.value)
274:           } else if (
275:             p.value.type === 'AssignmentPattern' &&
276:             p.value.left.type === 'Identifier'
277:           ) {
278:             // { foo = 1 }
279:             excludedIds.add(p.value.left)
280:             defaultValue = p.value.right
281:           }
282:         } else {
283:           key = p.computed ? p.key : p.key.name
284:           if (p.value.type === 'Identifier') {
285:             // { foo: bar }
286:             nameId = p.value
287:           } else if (p.value.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
288:             processRefObjectPattern(p.value, call, tempVar, [...path, key])
289:           } else if (p.value.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
290:             processRefArrayPattern(p.value, call, tempVar, [...path, key])
291:           } else if (p.value.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
292:             if (p.value.left.type === 'Identifier') {
293:               // { foo: bar = 1 }
294:               nameId = p.value.left
295:               defaultValue = p.value.right
296:             } else if (p.value.left.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
297:               processRefObjectPattern(p.value.left, call, tempVar, [
298:                 ...path,
299:                 [key, p.value.right]
300:               ])
301:             } else if (p.value.left.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
302:               processRefArrayPattern(p.value.left, call, tempVar, [
303:                 ...path,
304:                 [key, p.value.right]
305:               ])
306:             } else {
307:               // MemberExpression case is not possible here, ignore
308:             }
309:           }
310:         }
311:       } else {
312:         // rest element { ...foo }
313:         error(`reactivity destructure does not support rest elements.`, p)
314:       }
315:       if (nameId) {
316:         registerRefBinding(nameId)
317:         // inject toRef() after original replaced pattern
318:         const source = pathToString(tempVar, path)
319:         const keyStr = isString(key)
320:           ? `'${key}'`
321:           : key
322:           ? snip(key)
323:           : `'${nameId.name}'`
324:         const defaultStr = defaultValue ? `, ${snip(defaultValue)}` : ``
325:         s.appendLeft(
326:           call.end + offset,
327:           `,\n  ${nameId.name} = ${helper(
328:             'toRef'
329:           )}(${source}, ${keyStr}${defaultStr})`
330:         )
331:       }
332:     }
333:   }
334: 
335:   function processRefArrayPattern(pattern, call, tempVar, path = []) {
336:     if (!tempVar) {
337:       // const [x] = $(useFoo()) --> const __$temp_1 = useFoo()
338:       tempVar = genTempVar()
339:       s.overwrite(pattern.start + offset, pattern.end + offset, tempVar)
340:     }
341: 
342:     for (let i = 0; i < pattern.elements.length; i++) {
343:       const e = pattern.elements[i]
344:       if (!e) continue
345:       let nameId
346:       let defaultValue
347:       if (e.type === 'Identifier') {
348:         // [a] --> [__a]
349:         nameId = e
350:       } else if (e.type === 'AssignmentPattern') {
351:         // [a = 1]
352:         nameId = e.left
353:         defaultValue = e.right
354:       } else if (e.type === 'RestElement') {
355:         // [...a]
356:         error(`reactivity destructure does not support rest elements.`, e)
357:       } else if (e.type === 'ObjectPattern') {
358:         processRefObjectPattern(e, call, tempVar, [...path, i])
359:       } else if (e.type === 'ArrayPattern') {
360:         processRefArrayPattern(e, call, tempVar, [...path, i])
361:       }
362:       if (nameId) {
363:         registerRefBinding(nameId)
364:         // inject toRef() after original replaced pattern
365:         const source = pathToString(tempVar, path)
366:         const defaultStr = defaultValue ? `, ${snip(defaultValue)}` : ``
367:         s.appendLeft(
368:           call.end + offset,
369:           `,\n  ${nameId.name} = ${helper(
370:             'toRef'
371:           )}(${source}, ${i}${defaultStr})`
372:         )
373:       }
374:     }
375:   }
376: 
377:   function pathToString(source, path) {
378:     if (path.length) {
379:       for (const seg of path) {
380:         if (isArray(seg)) {
381:           source = `(${source}${segToString(seg[0])} || ${snip(seg[1])})`
382:         } else {
383:           source += segToString(seg)
384:         }
385:       }
386:     }
387:     return source
388:   }
389: 
390:   function segToString(seg) {
391:     if (typeof seg === 'number') {
392:       return `[${seg}]`
393:     } else if (typeof seg === 'string') {
394:       return `.${seg}`
395:     } else {
396:       return snip(seg)
397:     }
398:   }
399: 
400:   function rewriteId(scope, id, parent, parentStack) {
401:     if (hasOwn(scope, id.name)) {
402:       const bindingType = scope[id.name]
403:       if (bindingType) {
404:         const isProp = bindingType === 'prop'
405:         if (isStaticProperty(parent) && parent.shorthand) {
406:           // let binding used in a property shorthand
407:           // skip for destructure patterns
408:           if (
409:             !parent.inPattern ||
410:             isInDestructureAssignment(parent, parentStack)
411:           ) {
412:             if (isProp) {
413:               if (escapeScope) {
414:                 // prop binding in $$()
415:                 // { prop } -> { prop: __prop_prop }
416:                 registerEscapedPropBinding(id)
417:                 s.appendLeft(
418:                   id.end + offset,
419:                   `: __props_${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
420:                 )
421:               } else {
422:                 // { prop } -> { prop: __prop.prop }
423:                 s.appendLeft(
424:                   id.end + offset,
425:                   `: __props.${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
426:                 )
427:               }
428:             } else {
429:               // { foo } -> { foo: foo.value }
430:               s.appendLeft(id.end + offset, `: ${id.name}.value`)
431:             }
432:           }
433:         } else {
434:           if (isProp) {
435:             if (escapeScope) {
436:               // x --> __props_x
437:               registerEscapedPropBinding(id)
438:               s.overwrite(
439:                 id.start + offset,
440:                 id.end + offset,
441:                 `__props_${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
442:               )
443:             } else {
444:               // x --> __props.x
445:               s.overwrite(
446:                 id.start + offset,
447:                 id.end + offset,
448:                 `__props.${propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]}`
449:               )
450:             }
451:           } else {
452:             // x --> x.value
453:             s.appendLeft(id.end + offset, '.value')
454:           }
455:         }
456:       }
457:       return true
458:     }
459:     return false
460:   }
461: 
462:   const propBindingRefs = {}
463:   function registerEscapedPropBinding(id) {
464:     if (!propBindingRefs.hasOwnProperty(id.name)) {
465:       propBindingRefs[id.name] = true
466:       const publicKey = propsLocalToPublicMap[id.name]
467:       s.prependRight(
468:         offset,
469:         `const __props_${publicKey} = ${helper(
470:           `toRef`
471:         )}(__props, '${publicKey}')\n`
472:       )
473:     }
474:   }
475: 
476:   // check root scope first
477:   walkScope(ast, true)
478:   walk(ast, {
479:     enter(node, parent) {
480:       parent && parentStack.push(parent)
481: 
482:       // function scopes
483:       if (isFunctionType(node)) {
484:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
485:         walkFunctionParams(node, registerBinding)
486:         if (node.body.type === 'BlockStatement') {
487:           walkScope(node.body)
488:         }
489:         return
490:       }
491: 
492:       // catch param
493:       if (node.type === 'CatchClause') {
494:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
495:         if (node.param && node.param.type === 'Identifier') {
496:           registerBinding(node.param)
497:         }
498:         walkScope(node.body)
499:         return
500:       }
501: 
502:       // non-function block scopes
503:       if (node.type === 'BlockStatement' && !isFunctionType(parent)) {
504:         scopeStack.push((currentScope = {}))
505:         walkScope(node)
506:         return
507:       }
508: 
509:       // skip type nodes
510:       if (
511:         parent &&
512:         parent.type.startsWith('TS') &&
513:         parent.type !== 'TSAsExpression' &&
514:         parent.type !== 'TSNonNullExpression' &&
515:         parent.type !== 'TSTypeAssertion'
516:       ) {
517:         return this.skip()
518:       }
519: 
520:       if (
521:         node.type === 'Identifier' &&
522:         // if inside $$(), skip unless this is a destructured prop binding
523:         !(escapeScope && rootScope[node.name] !== 'prop') &&
524:         isReferencedIdentifier(node, parent, parentStack) &&
525:         !excludedIds.has(node)
526:       ) {
527:         // walk up the scope chain to check if id should be appended .value
528:         let i = scopeStack.length
529:         while (i--) {
530:           if (rewriteId(scopeStack[i], node, parent, parentStack)) {
531:             return
532:           }
533:         }
534:       }
535: 
536:       if (node.type === 'CallExpression' && node.callee.type === 'Identifier') {
537:         const callee = node.callee.name
538: 
539:         const refCall = isRefCreationCall(callee)
540:         if (refCall && (!parent || parent.type !== 'VariableDeclarator')) {
541:           return error(
542:             `${refCall} can only be used as the initializer of ` +
543:               `a variable declaration.`,
544:             node
545:           )
546:         }
547: 
548:         if (callee === escapeSymbol) {
549:           s.remove(node.callee.start + offset, node.callee.end + offset)
550:           escapeScope = node
551:         }
552: 
553:         // TODO remove when out of experimental
554:         if (callee === '$raw') {
555:           error(
556:             `$raw() has been replaced by $$(). ` +
557:               `See ${RFC_LINK} for latest updates.`,
558:             node
559:           )
560:         }
561:         if (callee === '$fromRef') {
562:           error(
563:             `$fromRef() has been replaced by $(). ` +
564:               `See ${RFC_LINK} for latest updates.`,
565:             node
566:           )
567:         }
568:       }
569:     },
570:     leave(node, parent) {
571:       parent && parentStack.pop()
572:       if (
573:         (node.type === 'BlockStatement' && !isFunctionType(parent)) ||
574:         isFunctionType(node)
575:       ) {
576:         scopeStack.pop()
577:         currentScope = scopeStack[scopeStack.length - 1] || null
578:       }
579:       if (node === escapeScope) {
580:         escapeScope = undefined
581:       }
582:     }
583:   })
584: 
585:   return {
586:     rootRefs: Object.keys(rootScope).filter(key => rootScope[key] === true),
587:     importedHelpers: [...importedHelpers]
588:   }
589: }
590: 
591:   return { transformAST, transform, shouldTransform }
592: }())
